null,"created_at":"2017-02-03 19:18:44 UTC","updated_at":"2017-02-03 19:20:35 UTC"},{"id":437,"user_id":4644,"text":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\r\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\r\n<div class=\"column\">\r\n<p>Data is collected digitally by remotely-operated marine vehicles (ROMV), tags that are surgically implanted in captured and released animals, static sensor buoys that measure ocean conditions, and communication lines that passively listen for signals from animal tags.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>","archived":1,"answer_id":4715,"archived_by":4644,"created_at":"2017-03-13 13:46:23 UTC","updated_at":"2017-03-13 16:31:08 UTC"},{"id":438,"user_id":4644,"text":"<p>need to keep each type of data in a separate place but connected&nbsp;through linked IDS, possibly each animal should have a number for the specific animal as well as for species. SQL database for everything but field notes and simulations...&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":4715,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-03-13 16:35:06 UTC","updated_at":"2017-03-13 16:35:06 UTC"},{"id":439,"user_id":4644,"text":"<p>need to convert information on different formats to one online cloud storage system.</p>\r\n<p>Creating a group in OneDrive, all communications and info and documents stored here. Might need to purchase cloud storage though &nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":4716,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-03-13 16:36:39 UTC","updated_at":"2017-03-13 16:36:39 UTC"},{"id":534,"user_id":117,"text":"<p>The metadata standard is Dublin Core--these are elements people will most familiar with when using a library catalogue</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":5477,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-06-08 23:54:43 UTC","updated_at":"2017-06-08 23:54:43 UTC"},{"id":535,"user_id":4883,"text":"<p>Hi Sonya, wondering if we should develop a plan on how others may contribute for example if Zoe or I stumble accross a peice of pertinent information it would be nice to be able to contrubute it to the project. Perhaps it is as simple as adding a scentence, other project members will send useful information/data to Sonya, thoughts?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":5480,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-06-06 17:40:52 UTC","updated_at":"2017-06-06 17:40:52 UTC"},{"id":536,"user_id":117,"text":"<p>&nbsp;Legislative Library may not be your preservation platform. Include here a reference to SFU's IR <a href=\"http://summit.sfu.ca/\" target=\"_blank\">Summit</a> and <a href=\"http://dvn.library.ubc.ca/dvn/\" target=\"_blank\">Abacus</a> <span id=\"form1:networkAnnouncementsMessages\" class=\"iceOutTxt\">research data repository of the BC Research Librareis Data Services as possible options for long term preservation. </span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":5481,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-06-08 23:59:33 UTC","updated_at":"2017-06-08 23:59:33 UTC"},{"id":559,"user_id":4915,"text":"<p>blah blah blah</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":5957,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-07-06 15:38:03 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-06 15:38:03 UTC"},{"id":563,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Potential respository for project data could be the University of Lethbridge's IR: https://www.uleth.ca/dspace/</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":6042,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-08 17:59:15 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-08 17:59:15 UTC"},{"id":565,"user_id":4999,"text":"<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Collect</span></p>\r\n<p>USRI - numeric, text</p>\r\n<p>Survey - numeric</p>\r\n<p>Interviews - audio, text</p>\r\n<p>Focus Group - audio, text</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":6054,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-22 01:03:02 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-22 01:03:02 UTC"},{"id":579,"user_id":5055,"text":"<p>Kevin smells like fish.&nbsp; Just saying....</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":6241,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-08-28 19:33:50 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 19:33:50 UTC"},{"id":580,"user_id":5055,"text":"<p>Kevin smells like fish.&nbsp; Just saying....</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":6241,"archived_by":5055,"created_at":"2019-08-28 19:33:50 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 19:35:30 UTC"},{"id":581,"user_id":5055,"text":"<p>what kind of fish?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":6241,"archived_by":5055,"created_at":"2019-08-28 19:34:46 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 19:36:07 UTC"},{"id":582,"user_id":5055,"text":"<p>what kind of fish?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":6241,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-08-28 19:34:46 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 19:34:46 UTC"},{"id":603,"user_id":4880,"text":"<p>Bonjour Jos&eacute;e!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":6449,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-09-18 19:39:59 UTC","updated_at":"2017-09-18 19:39:59 UTC"},{"id":613,"user_id":116,"text":"<p>I need some assistance on items starting a vocabularies</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":6532,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-12-11 19:23:34 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-11 19:24:11 UTC"},{"id":676,"user_id":5269,"text":"<p>Interesting!&nbsp; I'm thinking no need for any end user licence but I don't really know anything about it.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":6965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-11-17 15:08:20 UTC","updated_at":"2017-11-17 15:08:20 UTC"},{"id":679,"user_id":5269,"text":"<p>I'm assuming whatever we use for storage will be free.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":6969,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-11-17 15:11:51 UTC","updated_at":"2017-11-17 15:11:51 UTC"},{"id":687,"user_id":4685,"text":"<p>At the moment, the only funding described in the budget for materials is Myers' RAID array. It would be beneficial to prepare some estimates for the Tortell group data storage requirements in future budgets.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":7080,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-12-03 22:53:50 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-03 22:53:50 UTC"},{"id":710,"user_id":5332,"text":"<p>What do you think they mean by \"what data will you share\"? Does this mean a list of the data fields we intend on sharing? Or?????</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":7299,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-11-22 07:05:51 UTC","updated_at":"2017-11-22 07:05:51 UTC"},{"id":771,"user_id":4150,"text":"<p>HI.&nbsp; Can you check to make sure I've not forgotten anything?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":7588,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-12-07 15:09:06 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-07 15:09:06 UTC"},{"id":773,"user_id":4402,"text":"<p>Maya, will you audio tape the focus groups? Is this description accurate?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":7707,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2017-12-21 13:53:16 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-21 13:53:16 UTC"},{"id":774,"user_id":5414,"text":"<p>the description is 100% accurate! I would like to video tape them too, if that's possible - at mcgill in the counselling centre, is there a room with video equipment? if not, then default is just audio recording with our notes.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":7707,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-01-04 18:22:04 UTC","updated_at":"2018-01-04 18:22:04 UTC"},{"id":777,"user_id":5414,"text":"<p>(Biru is this correct? for the data transparency stuff?)&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":7717,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-01-04 19:00:26 UTC","updated_at":"2018-01-04 19:00:26 UTC"},{"id":806,"user_id":251,"text":"<p>Can you please add your response from the activity?</p>\r\n<p>Air samples at Gordon Southam Observatory will be collected continuously from air intakes located at the four towers (North, South, East and West)</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":7816,"archived_by":251,"created_at":"2018-04-24 20:57:58 UTC","updated_at":"2018-04-24 21:04:45 UTC"},{"id":863,"user_id":5587,"text":"<p>The guidance note here recommends storing three copies of the data.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Nelly, Jude, Dee: What do you recommend for this? I think the WorkSpace can be our master copies. I could store a back up copy on my UBC laptop and we could purchase a dedicated hard drive that is stored at IH offices and regularly syncronized?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8348,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-08 00:23:16 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-08 00:23:16 UTC"},{"id":864,"user_id":5587,"text":"<p>This is a partnered study....</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8361,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-08 18:52:57 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-08 18:52:57 UTC"},{"id":868,"user_id":5632,"text":"<p>As overarching theme:&nbsp;Add info from FAIR Guiding Principles with respect to&nbsp;long-term&nbsp;care of data. Findability; Accessiblity, Interoperability, and Resuability. Supporting discovery through good data management. Source: nature.com/scientificdata DOI: 0.1038/sdata.2016.18</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8543,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-18 16:08:22 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-18 16:08:22 UTC"},{"id":869,"user_id":5632,"text":"<p>Source: https://www.unidata.ucar.edu/software/netcdf/docs/netcdf_introduction.html</p>\r\n<p>Source:&nbsp;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NetCDF The Net CDF format is an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_standard\" target=\"_blank\">open standard</a>. NetCDF Classic and 64-bit Offset Format are an international standard of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_Geospatial_Consortium\" target=\"_blank\">Open Geospatial Consortium</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NetCDF#cite_note-2\" target=\"_blank\">[2]</a></sup></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8544,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-18 14:49:53 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-18 14:49:53 UTC"},{"id":870,"user_id":5632,"text":"<p>Advise Open Science Framework for long-term re-use?</p>\r\n<p>Add info from FAIR Guiding Principles with respect to long-term care of data. Supporting discovery through good data management.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8544,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-18 15:03:24 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-18 16:01:33 UTC"},{"id":873,"user_id":5632,"text":"<p>Use SQL to map folder structure/to model data? How do we ensure version control? OSF allows for version control.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8545,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-18 18:59:37 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-18 18:59:37 UTC"},{"id":874,"user_id":5632,"text":"<p>Sensor Data<br />Data Collector type:&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;e.g. ROMV&nbsp;<br />Data format:<br />NetCDF (contains all files of this type from all sensors)<br />Data Type: Field Notes<br />Animal type?<br />Subfolders: Captured and tagged animals, mark and recapture populations estimations, class-based observations studies<br />Citizen scientist reports</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8545,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-26 19:14:17 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-30 14:43:41 UTC"},{"id":877,"user_id":5632,"text":"<p>I asked a question in the discussion forum about data ownership, and the response has more to do with licensing:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"I have never bothered to get specific licenses. After your request I took a look for the citizen scientists and my own contract. Their data is open data and I own the data I produce.<br />There is not procedure or contract in place that the students (incoming or leaving) have to sign. Do you think that it is necessary to have that written down somewhere?\"</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8548,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-26 19:17:58 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-26 19:17:58 UTC"},{"id":878,"user_id":5632,"text":"<p>For definitions of data steward vs data owner: <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2GmRd8B\" target=\"_blank\">https://bit.ly/2GmRd8B</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.techopedia.com/definition/29059/data-ownership\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.techopedia.com/definition/29059/data-ownership</a></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8549,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-25 14:26:20 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-25 14:26:20 UTC"},{"id":887,"user_id":5681,"text":"<p>Hello world</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8608,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-03-29 16:35:24 UTC","updated_at":"2018-03-29 16:35:24 UTC"},{"id":912,"user_id":5724,"text":"<p>Field variables for numeric and text are those which relate to prospective students and applicants to undergraduate studies. Due to requirement to be FIPPA compliant the data are cleansed/anonymized.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8872,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-04-11 18:35:45 UTC","updated_at":"2018-04-11 18:35:45 UTC"},{"id":913,"user_id":2771,"text":"<p>File types are an essential consideration in data storage.</p>\r\n<p>Be aware of propritery vs non-proprietary formats.</p>\r\n<p>When choosing how to save your files chose a format that is:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Non-proprietary</li>\r\n<li>Open, with documented standards</li>\r\n<li>Used by your community</li>\r\n<li>Encoded using standard character encoding</li>\r\n<li>Uncompressed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8907,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-13 17:02:29 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-13 17:02:29 UTC"},{"id":915,"user_id":2771,"text":"<p>It is recommended that you choose a file naming convention and stick with it. Make sure that everyone on your team is following the same rules for naming files. When deciding how to name your files remember the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Keep file names under 32 characters</li>\r\n<li>Classify broad types of files (transcript, photo, etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Avoid spaces and special characters</li>\r\n<li>Use underscores instead of periods or spaces</li>\r\n<li>Make sure that file names are descriptive outside of their folders (in case they are misplaced or change locations); i.e., the file name should include all necessary descriptive information</li>\r\n<li>Include dates and format them consistently (international standard for date notation is YYYY_MM_DD or YYYYMMDD)</li>\r\n<li>Include a version number to track multiple versions of a document</li>\r\n<li>Be consistent!</li>\r\n</ul>","archived":0,"answer_id":8908,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-13 17:38:30 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-13 17:38:30 UTC"},{"id":916,"user_id":2771,"text":"<p>Documentation - important to record information about the data as you collect it. Properly naming columns, describing any formulas used to create date, listing where and when data was collected, etc. will help re-use of data.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8909,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-13 17:10:51 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-13 17:10:51 UTC"},{"id":917,"user_id":2771,"text":"<p>can plan for long term storage, preservation, and backup by using data repositories such as Dryad or Dataverse.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8912,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-13 17:15:07 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-13 17:15:07 UTC"},{"id":918,"user_id":2771,"text":"<p>Plans to share data; scope of data</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8914,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-13 17:16:02 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-13 17:16:02 UTC"},{"id":919,"user_id":2771,"text":"<p>Sharing datasets - be thoughtful of how and where sharing. For sensitive data, avoid google, drop box, where storage is not an institutional space or supported by your institution. For Queen's, storage and sharing space available with Queen's OneDrive, QShare, providing encryption and password protection.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8914,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-13 17:19:34 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-13 17:19:34 UTC"},{"id":920,"user_id":2771,"text":"<p>Creative Commons</p>\r\n<p>Dataverse - has standard terms of use; default CC is CC open. These can be changed based on needs of your dataset.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dataverse also provides various levels of restrictions fro datasets and files.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8918,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-13 17:29:26 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-13 17:29:26 UTC"},{"id":921,"user_id":2771,"text":"<p>Secondary uses of sensitive data can be driven by ehtics boards and/or end-user licences/terms of data.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Datasets can also be resticting of files, creating subsets of data or public use versions of data.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8924,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-13 17:32:33 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-13 17:32:33 UTC"},{"id":922,"user_id":4506,"text":"<p>You should specify your date format convention. The best (really the only) way to go is YYYY-MM-DD. Dashes are a valid character in a file name, and using this convention will mean that if you sort your files alphabetically on your computer they will be in chronologiacal order</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8968,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-04-30 15:44:40 UTC","updated_at":"2018-04-30 15:44:40 UTC"},{"id":923,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>quantitatives provenant de fichier d'enregistrement SPSS</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8983,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-04-26 18:26:33 UTC","updated_at":"2018-04-26 18:26:33 UTC"},{"id":924,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>donn&eacute;es num&eacute;riques &eacute;quivalent &agrave; \"quantitatives\" et non pas &agrave; \"digital\"</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":8983,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-04-26 19:34:43 UTC","updated_at":"2018-04-26 19:34:43 UTC"},{"id":929,"user_id":5794,"text":"<p>Do we have a system for archiving old files? For example, the P-PAG folder has several folders of old content that is no longer relevant to our current group, and includes several documents of older versions of now finalized documents.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9028,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-10 16:23:28 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-10 16:23:28 UTC"},{"id":931,"user_id":5794,"text":"<p>Which naming convention is the most up to date one?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[NameofFile]_[Author]_[DayMonthYear]_[DraftVersion#]_[InitialsofPersonModifyingText].ext</p>\r\n<p>TITLE\"_DDMMMYY_INITIALS&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":9029,"archived_by":5794,"created_at":"2018-05-10 16:27:10 UTC","updated_at":"2018-06-14 20:54:02 UTC"},{"id":933,"user_id":5794,"text":"<p>Is this an appropriate statement?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9034,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-10 16:42:00 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-10 16:42:00 UTC"},{"id":948,"user_id":117,"text":"<p>Using external sources pending approval for direct interviews?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9223,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-23 18:00:48 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-23 18:00:48 UTC"},{"id":950,"user_id":5839,"text":"<p>Hi Erin. Please look into MP4 as proprietary.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>Danae</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9252,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-24 02:19:55 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 02:19:55 UTC"},{"id":951,"user_id":4437,"text":"<p>MP4 is good - listed by the library of congress as a sustainable digital fomat</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9252,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-24 16:39:15 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 16:39:15 UTC"},{"id":952,"user_id":4437,"text":"<p>Logical file stucture to use would be Interview1-datecreated/revised (so rename file if you update with a new version - this is probably not overly relevant to your work, but an example might be, revised date if you edited the transcript to add missing detail - not inaudible, for ex.)&nbsp; Structure your file names in a pattern</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9253,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-24 16:43:56 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 16:43:56 UTC"},{"id":953,"user_id":4437,"text":"<p>will use consistent file naming convention?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9255,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-24 16:48:50 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 16:48:50 UTC"},{"id":954,"user_id":4437,"text":"<p>You might also want to write a small paragraph that outlines how you will collect data (in MP4, using set file naming convention, saved in locations A and B) basically outline of some things in this form but accessible at a quick glance</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9255,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-24 16:51:07 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 16:51:07 UTC"},{"id":955,"user_id":4437,"text":"<p>Dataverse supports use restrictions, provides a back up copy and is a convenient way to disseminate you data.&nbsp; Dataverse will only support 2 GB of space. Read more&nbsp;http://guides.scholarsportal.info/dataverse</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9260,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-24 18:16:27 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 18:16:27 UTC"},{"id":956,"user_id":5839,"text":"<p>Erin.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9261,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-05-24 02:32:53 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-24 02:32:53 UTC"},{"id":989,"user_id":6091,"text":"<p>This is a list of data that has been required to perform find perform data analytics and find which features best describe donors.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9625,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-07-29 17:17:28 UTC","updated_at":"2018-07-29 17:17:28 UTC"},{"id":996,"user_id":5818,"text":"<p>Need both ion chrom. and colorimetry for comparsion to published literature.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9662,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-08-07 20:21:57 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-07 20:21:57 UTC"},{"id":1003,"user_id":6259,"text":"<p>Zenodo a free repository that will not incur charges when I am no longer a student</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9858,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-09-11 11:34:00 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-11 11:34:00 UTC"},{"id":1004,"user_id":6259,"text":"<p>I guess it's me...</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":9864,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-09-11 12:20:41 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-11 12:20:41 UTC"},{"id":1021,"user_id":6196,"text":"<p>Donn&eacute;es administratives</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10292,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-08-22 20:42:31 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-22 20:42:31 UTC"},{"id":1031,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>You mention using industry standards re: metadata in the previous section, may be good to include here as well and any additional information that you might have about those.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10472,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-01 18:39:22 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-01 18:39:22 UTC"},{"id":1033,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>See previous note</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10473,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-01 18:39:54 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-01 18:39:54 UTC"},{"id":1034,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>For this and the next question - typically you may need to give more clarification about exactly how the data are going to be stored - e.g., cloud based servers (which then can be remotely accessed by geographically disperesed collaborators), local servers (and then how will data be shared with collaborators), etc. Depending upon these details, can then further clarify details re backups (e.g., automated processes taken care of for you, manual, onsite/offsite copies, etc)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10474,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-01 18:45:08 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-01 18:45:08 UTC"},{"id":1036,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>FRDR is pretty new, so should assume that anyone reviewing this may not know much about it - might be good to give a brief description (see my slides and website) and the link</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10477,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-01 18:46:51 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-01 18:46:51 UTC"},{"id":1038,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>And may wish to specifically clarify&nbsp;that the data will be openly discoverable through FRDR's public portal.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10481,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-01 18:27:35 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-01 18:27:35 UTC"},{"id":1039,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>In this section it is good to highlight specific processes and people where able. If you aren't there yet then I might suggest that stating that a data management protocol will be developed and that within this reoles and responsibilities will be identified.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10482,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-01 18:31:47 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-01 18:31:47 UTC"},{"id":1040,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>Relating to the previous note, you can also say that for specific processes/tasks there will be both primary and secondary (coverage when needed and if changes occur) individuals identified.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10483,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-01 18:34:25 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-01 18:34:25 UTC"},{"id":1041,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>Could add that, as necessary, access restrictions and customized terms of use can be developed and included with the data when deposited with FRDR for long-term stewardship.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10487,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-01 18:37:21 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-01 18:37:21 UTC"},{"id":1043,"user_id":2934,"text":"<p>Hey Sharon - I think that the surveys will be exported into tabular format like a .csv file??</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10554,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-09-13 16:42:33 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-13 16:42:33 UTC"},{"id":1047,"user_id":2934,"text":"<p>Hi Sherry, I can't remeber if we are collecting surveys?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":10554,"archived_by":2934,"created_at":"2019-08-28 19:34:10 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-14 20:25:27 UTC"},{"id":1068,"user_id":6439,"text":"<p>Data collected from less accessible formats (ex. GIS, print reports form municipalities) can be coded into excel to be made more accessible for future use. We can probably also archive the government reports that are the source for water system information, and create a guide for accessing the files. GIS raw data sources should just be sourced so that the analysis could be replicated.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10671,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-29 14:28:31 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-29 14:28:31 UTC"},{"id":1069,"user_id":6439,"text":"<p>I've only established naming conventions for data that we currently have. Spatial and master/regression files TBD.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10672,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-29 15:10:11 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-29 15:10:11 UTC"},{"id":1070,"user_id":6439,"text":"<p>I can start developing these metadata now.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10673,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-29 15:22:27 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-29 15:22:27 UTC"},{"id":1071,"user_id":6439,"text":"<p>I will work on developing this, after reviewing metadata conventions for similar datasets.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10675,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-29 15:25:31 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-29 15:25:31 UTC"},{"id":1072,"user_id":6439,"text":"<p>The library should be able to provide perpetual storage for us, but will need to double check.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10676,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-29 15:28:22 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-29 15:28:22 UTC"},{"id":1073,"user_id":6439,"text":"<p>I should probably touch base with library staff in the next few months (as the data collection wraps up) to get their input on the DMP.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10680,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-29 15:31:01 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-29 15:31:01 UTC"},{"id":1084,"user_id":6451,"text":"<p>Will&nbsp;we collect other kinds of data?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10726,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-18 19:43:14 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-18 19:43:14 UTC"},{"id":1085,"user_id":6451,"text":"<p>Will we collect other kinds of data?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10726,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-10-22 20:54:56 UTC","updated_at":"2018-10-22 20:54:56 UTC"},{"id":1106,"user_id":6212,"text":"<p>Ne sont pas recommand&eacute;s par UK Data Service</p>\r\n<p>Formats recommand&eacute;s ou acceptables : .por, .dsv, .dta</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":11065,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-02-13 15:44:20 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-13 15:44:20 UTC"},{"id":1116,"user_id":6637,"text":"<p>I actually did this with my data, because of this class! My natural inclination would have been to leave things as is, but coding options numerically actually made my analysis a little easier!&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":11151,"archived_by":6637,"created_at":"2018-11-03 16:00:27 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-03 16:14:20 UTC"},{"id":1123,"user_id":6637,"text":"<p>I like ptotaos</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":11164,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-11-12 19:25:24 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-12 19:25:24 UTC"},{"id":1124,"user_id":6637,"text":"<p>tatopo</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":11164,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-11-13 16:21:07 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-13 16:21:07 UTC"},{"id":1125,"user_id":6637,"text":"<p>potato?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":11165,"archived_by":6637,"created_at":"2018-11-12 19:20:06 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-13 16:13:31 UTC"},{"id":1127,"user_id":6637,"text":"<p>dzdfz</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":11165,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-11-13 16:19:57 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-13 16:19:57 UTC"},{"id":1155,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>V&eacute;rifier si STI-UQTR charge&nbsp; pour stockage? combien?</p>\r\n<p>V&eacute;rifier si&nbsp;Dataverse =BCI charge&nbsp; pour stockage? combien?</p>\r\n<p>&agrave; ajouter dans directives UQTR</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":11445,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-11-23 16:01:09 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-23 16:03:23 UTC"},{"id":1211,"user_id":6762,"text":"<p>This is a test</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":11783,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-11-22 18:06:23 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-22 18:06:23 UTC"},{"id":1285,"user_id":6622,"text":"<p>Using 'TBD' interfers with 'Questions Answered' counter. Blanking out but does not appear to fix the problem. Any chance you could reload with 'TBD' filler?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":12127,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2018-12-05 22:09:18 UTC","updated_at":"2018-12-05 22:09:18 UTC"},{"id":1287,"user_id":6911,"text":"<p>Not sure if this captures what I should be saying at the start of the study. Given it is an emerging design - participatory action research - I may not know what the files will look like, depending on what is requested by the research advisory committee.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":12173,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-01-13 02:25:12 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-13 02:25:12 UTC"},{"id":1324,"user_id":7183,"text":"<p>Numeric (algae size), images (algae), Instrumentation data: YSI (temperature, salinity), ODYSSEY (PAR), Hobo pendant (temperature)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":12729,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-01-29 01:12:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-29 01:12:24 UTC"},{"id":1347,"user_id":7411,"text":"<p>Added .json to list of file types.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":12902,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-19 19:35:38 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-19 19:35:38 UTC"},{"id":1360,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Is there a plan here to contribute any of the data (e.g. location of diadromous fish) as a map? If so, we can include the spatial data type here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13113,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 18:17:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 18:17:08 UTC"},{"id":1361,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Is there a plan here to contribute any of the data (e.g. location of diadromous fish) as a map? If so, we can include the spatial data type here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13113,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 18:17:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 18:17:08 UTC"},{"id":1363,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Is there something missing/misrepresented in this list?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13116,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 18:32:51 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 18:32:51 UTC"},{"id":1364,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Is there a plan to photo document each of the fish species retained from herring bycatch surveys? This may increase the need for additional storage space. Also, will location data be processed as part of a CSV file, or stored as spatial data in a&nbsp;geodatabase or shapefile?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13119,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 18:49:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 18:49:42 UTC"},{"id":1370,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>What systems do you use to share your data between your students and colleagues?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13121,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 18:56:58 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 18:56:58 UTC"},{"id":1371,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>What systems do you use to share your data between your students and colleagues?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13121,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 18:56:59 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 18:56:59 UTC"},{"id":1372,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Does MUN have a system of long term data storage and archiving if SLGO were to no longer be able to house data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13122,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 18:59:21 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 18:59:21 UTC"},{"id":1374,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Anything to change or add here? What sort of steps do you normally take to let the research community know your data exists?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13126,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 19:19:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 19:19:54 UTC"},{"id":1375,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Is there someone else who manages your group data over the long term?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13127,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 19:26:23 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 19:26:23 UTC"},{"id":1376,"user_id":7773,"text":"<p>Will the&nbsp;determined&nbsp; presence and densities of other forage fish species be output in the form of a shapefile ot tabular dataset, or will it be a raster file?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13129,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-27 17:43:33 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-27 17:43:33 UTC"},{"id":1377,"user_id":7773,"text":"<p>Will the physical characteristics of deep-water spawning sites, including bathymetric features, depth, sediment size, temperature, salinity and conductivity data be tabular or raster?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13129,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-04 14:27:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-04 14:27:25 UTC"},{"id":1378,"user_id":7773,"text":"<p>What data formats do you expect to have? Please add to or modify this list.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13130,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-04 14:34:51 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-04 14:34:51 UTC"},{"id":1380,"user_id":7773,"text":"<p>Could you speak to the estimated storage space requirement?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13135,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-04 19:30:21 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-04 19:30:21 UTC"},{"id":1381,"user_id":7773,"text":"<p>Do you plan on sharing raw data files or post-processed data/products?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13140,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-04 19:36:17 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-04 19:36:17 UTC"},{"id":1382,"user_id":7773,"text":"<p>Outside of SLGOs role, who is responsibel in your group?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13142,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-04 19:37:52 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-04 19:37:52 UTC"},{"id":1390,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Waiting on standardized list from SLGO for this, but will also populate with some ideas for project specifics.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13167,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-28 17:31:18 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-28 17:31:18 UTC"},{"id":1392,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Will need clarification here on who has what roles for managing data within ACAP HA.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13177,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-28 19:05:47 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-28 19:05:47 UTC"},{"id":1393,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Is there any sensitive data in this project? It doesn't appear that anything would carry personally sensitive data from the initial outset.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":13179,"archived_by":7834,"created_at":"2019-02-28 19:09:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-28 19:12:23 UTC"},{"id":1397,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>This likely needs to be more case specific than the generalized line item here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13181,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-28 19:12:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-28 19:12:24 UTC"},{"id":1398,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>This likely needs to be more case specific than the generalized line item here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13181,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-02-28 19:12:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-02-28 19:12:24 UTC"},{"id":1399,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Is there an intention to share data from surveys in a map form (e.g. raster, shapefile, etc.)?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13184,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-01 14:17:34 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-01 14:17:34 UTC"},{"id":1400,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Will there be images taken as part of site descriptions/photos?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13184,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-01 14:51:09 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-01 14:51:09 UTC"},{"id":1401,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>What type of format will the videos be collected in? AVI, MOV? Best guess is currently identified.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13185,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-01 14:54:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-01 14:54:08 UTC"},{"id":1403,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>This will be better fleshed out once a standardized list of metadata needs is received from SLGO.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13187,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-01 15:14:17 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-01 15:14:17 UTC"},{"id":1404,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Please indicate whether this is an acurate representation of how the data management responsibilities will be broken out for the project.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13196,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-01 17:28:01 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-01 17:28:01 UTC"},{"id":1408,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>What file types will the orthimages be stored as? Also, will the DSM be stored as a raster, vector or text file? (e.g. ASCII, DEM, FLt)?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13222,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-05 13:52:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-05 14:07:35 UTC"},{"id":1409,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Note:&nbsp;This is not a finalized list. Metadata needs will be filled in more by folks from SLGO.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13224,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-05 14:14:22 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-05 14:14:22 UTC"},{"id":1410,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Can you please confirm how much space you anticipate needing for storage of DSMs and orthoimagery?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13226,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-05 14:37:22 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-05 14:37:22 UTC"},{"id":1411,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Does NAACAP have any other plans for long term preservation of the data at the end of the porject?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13229,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-05 14:50:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-05 14:50:07 UTC"},{"id":1412,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>What format would DSMs be saved under?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13230,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-05 14:52:35 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-05 14:52:35 UTC"},{"id":1413,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Please make any changes according to how NAACAP's internal structure and oversight of the project is actually being carried out. This was a best guess based on the project proposal.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13233,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-05 15:07:36 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-05 15:07:36 UTC"},{"id":1423,"user_id":7773,"text":"<p>Could you specify any other data products/types?</p>\r\n<p>Will the data produced from analyses be in a tabular (CSV/Excel) or numeric from?</p>\r\n<p>There is mention of qualitiaive data as well. Will that be in the form of written reports or analyzed trend data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13296,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-06 15:02:45 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-06 15:02:45 UTC"},{"id":1424,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>Please confirm what and/or if you will be collecting audio files and how these files might be stored, or whether all data is planned to be post processed to a word document (e.g. TXT)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13313,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-06 14:39:57 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-06 14:39:57 UTC"},{"id":1425,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>We are waiting on a generic list of metadata needs from the external data provider to finish completing this section. If there are other things you can see are missing or need to be changed here, please add them.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13315,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-06 15:10:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-06 15:10:44 UTC"},{"id":1426,"user_id":7834,"text":"<ul>\r\n<li>Is there an electronic questionnaire being used to collect the information or is it mostly paper-based? Do you have plans to house the information internally, or elsewhere (i.e. cloud-based storage, online database, library, etc)</li>\r\n</ul>","archived":0,"answer_id":13320,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-06 16:54:45 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-06 16:54:45 UTC"},{"id":1428,"user_id":7834,"text":"<p>What will happen in this case if Dwan is no longer the project coordinator? How would FFAW/Unifor ensure the project is still completed in this case?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13326,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-06 17:48:46 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-06 17:48:46 UTC"},{"id":1458,"user_id":7983,"text":"<p>What are we doing?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13490,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-11 18:02:53 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-11 18:02:53 UTC"},{"id":1463,"user_id":8036,"text":"<p>tabular data</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13503,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-15 17:57:41 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-15 17:57:41 UTC"},{"id":1464,"user_id":8036,"text":"<p>spatial data</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13503,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-15 17:58:37 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-15 17:58:37 UTC"},{"id":1489,"user_id":8162,"text":"<p>Thoughts? (this is a test)</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":13877,"archived_by":8162,"created_at":"2019-03-27 19:58:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-27 19:59:34 UTC"},{"id":1490,"user_id":8162,"text":"<p><a href=\"https://dwc.tdwg.org/terms/\" target=\"_blank\">Darwin Core Terms</a></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13879,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-28 13:56:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-28 13:56:07 UTC"},{"id":1491,"user_id":8163,"text":"<p>Is a 6-month back-up schedule frequent enough?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13884,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-04-02 19:02:48 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-02 19:02:48 UTC"},{"id":1492,"user_id":8162,"text":"<p>I think the 6-month schedule is fine, though possibly a 3-month schedule if they up their data collection volume.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13884,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-04-03 02:43:14 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-03 02:43:14 UTC"},{"id":1493,"user_id":8163,"text":"<p>Check funding agencies for information pertaining to this question.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13886,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-04-02 19:22:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-02 19:22:08 UTC"},{"id":1494,"user_id":8163,"text":"<p>Examine the properties of these repositories to ensure that they align with the conditions of the researcher and funding institution.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13886,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-04-02 19:48:11 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-02 19:48:11 UTC"},{"id":1495,"user_id":8163,"text":"<p>Waiting for a response to this question.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":13889,"archived_by":8163,"created_at":"2019-03-28 15:29:58 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-02 19:52:21 UTC"},{"id":1496,"user_id":8163,"text":"<p>Check features of the repository chosen to ensure that they use identifiers and that they link the data to the publications.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13890,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-04-02 19:54:37 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-02 19:55:44 UTC"},{"id":1497,"user_id":8163,"text":"<p>Check information from funding agency to see what costs they cover.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13893,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-28 14:08:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-28 14:08:07 UTC"},{"id":1498,"user_id":8163,"text":"<p>Check information from funding agency to see what costs they cover.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":13893,"archived_by":8163,"created_at":"2019-03-28 14:08:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-28 15:24:31 UTC"},{"id":1499,"user_id":8162,"text":"<p>Could potentially be sensitive - depends on answers to questions re: making corrections/account necessity.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13894,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-28 15:04:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-28 15:04:54 UTC"},{"id":1500,"user_id":8163,"text":"<p>Check intellectual property rights</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13896,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-28 14:05:19 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-28 14:05:19 UTC"},{"id":1503,"user_id":8171,"text":"<p>My idea is: To manually change all the CSV files to Excel files for ease of use.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":13898,"archived_by":8171,"created_at":"2019-03-30 23:32:17 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-30 23:33:53 UTC"},{"id":1504,"user_id":8171,"text":"<p>My idea is: To manually change all the CSV files to Excel files for ease of use.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":13898,"archived_by":8171,"created_at":"2019-03-30 23:32:18 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-30 23:33:30 UTC"},{"id":1509,"user_id":8171,"text":"<p>OneDrive unlimited $12.8/month per user&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dropbox first year 3TB, $17.5/month 3 users, unlimited $27.5/month 3 users</p>\r\n<p>My perception is SharePoint used OneDrive as cloud storage because SharePoint Online is sold together with OneDrive. I suggest we use Dropbox as a backup.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":13904,"archived_by":8167,"created_at":"2019-03-31 02:29:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-02 11:49:19 UTC"},{"id":1510,"user_id":8171,"text":"<p>sync.com 3TB $10/month per user, stored in Canada</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13904,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-31 02:38:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-31 02:38:44 UTC"},{"id":1520,"user_id":3510,"text":"<p>D&eacute;tailler comment seront analys&eacute;es les photos hors du mapping</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":13919,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-03-29 03:55:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-29 03:55:42 UTC"},{"id":1532,"user_id":8379,"text":"<p>note1</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14049,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-04-23 17:25:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-23 17:25:25 UTC"},{"id":1533,"user_id":8379,"text":"<p>note2</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14050,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-04-23 17:25:59 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-23 17:25:59 UTC"},{"id":1551,"user_id":8471,"text":"<p>test</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14139,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-05-03 17:34:22 UTC","updated_at":"2019-05-03 17:34:22 UTC"},{"id":1572,"user_id":8622,"text":"<p>Need to define deposit 2 in more detail - accesses, reporduction, storage, etc</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14412,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-05-21 16:48:12 UTC","updated_at":"2019-05-21 16:48:12 UTC"},{"id":1583,"user_id":6757,"text":"<p><a href=\"http://data-archive.ac.uk/create-manage/format/formats\" target=\"_blank\">UK Data Archive</a>&nbsp;ne marche plus.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14520,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-05-29 14:56:06 UTC","updated_at":"2019-05-29 14:56:06 UTC"},{"id":1617,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Ok !&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14875,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:49:46 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:49:46 UTC"},{"id":1618,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Ok !&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":14875,"archived_by":8957,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:49:47 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-07 19:17:08 UTC"},{"id":1620,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Bonne id&eacute;e :)&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14876,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:51:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:51:54 UTC"},{"id":1621,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Bonne id&eacute;e :)&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14876,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:51:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:51:55 UTC"},{"id":1625,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>En r&eacute;seau ferm&eacute; ? Sinon ok pour le reste</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14881,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:14:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:14:29 UTC"},{"id":1626,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>En r&eacute;seau ferm&eacute; ? Sinon ok pour le reste</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14881,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:14:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:14:29 UTC"},{"id":1627,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Dropbox c'est pas assex s&eacute;curitaire... Jacinthe ?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14882,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:29:39 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:29:39 UTC"},{"id":1628,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Dropbox c'est pas assex s&eacute;curitaire... Jacinthe ?&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":14882,"archived_by":8957,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:29:39 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-07 19:22:19 UTC"},{"id":1629,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>au sein de l'&eacute;quipe constitu&eacute; de co-chercheur(e)s, d'assistant(e)s et d'une coordonnatrice. Qu'en penses-tu ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14885,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:33:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:33:44 UTC"},{"id":1630,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>au sein de l'&eacute;quipe constitu&eacute; de co-chercheur(e)s, d'assistant(e)s et d'une coordonnatrice. Qu'en penses-tu ?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pour les donn&eacute;es d&eacute;finitives je ne sais pas.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14885,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:33:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:34:59 UTC"},{"id":1631,"user_id":8779,"text":"<p>J'ai apport&eacute; les pr&eacute;cisions.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14885,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-04 15:14:37 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-04 15:15:24 UTC"},{"id":1632,"user_id":9011,"text":"<p>Certaines des informations me paraissent contradictoires</p>\r\n<p>Il est dit ici que &laquo;Les donn&eacute;es brutes et trait&eacute;es seront partag&eacute;es uniquement au sein de l'&eacute;quipe de recherche ..&raquo;</p>\r\n<p>N&eacute;anmoins, dans la section &laquo;Conformit&eacute; aux lois...&raquo;, on mentionne &laquo;Le consentement sera recueilli aupr&egrave;s des participants et ceux-ci seront avis&eacute;s que d'autres personnes autres que les co-chercheur(e)s pourront utiliser leurs donn&eacute;es compl&egrave;tement anonymes pour d'autres analyses reli&eacute;es au projet ou pour l'&eacute;laboration de projets futurs&raquo;; de m&ecirc;me que &laquo;...il sera possible de r&eacute;utiliser les donn&eacute;es puisque les participants y auront consentis avant de participer j&agrave; la collecte de donn&eacute;es. Cette r&eacute;utilisation doit &ecirc;tre approuv&eacute;e par la chercheure principale.&raquo;</p>\r\n<p>Y aura-t-il ou non partage des donn&eacute;es pour des projets futurs? Si oui, sous quelle forme?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14885,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-17 18:49:51 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-17 19:00:11 UTC"},{"id":1633,"user_id":8957,"text":"<p>Nous avons modifier pour que ce soit coh&eacute;rent. Merci!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14885,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-08-08 14:58:51 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-08 14:58:51 UTC"},{"id":1634,"user_id":9011,"text":"<p>Je comprends qu'il n'y aura donc pas d'accessibilit&eacute; aux donn&eacute;es en dehors des r&eacute;sultats pr&eacute;sent&eacute;s dans les publications.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14887,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-17 18:52:11 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-17 18:52:11 UTC"},{"id":1635,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Je les nommerai tous !&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14889,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:39:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:39:24 UTC"},{"id":1636,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Je les nommerai tous !&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14889,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:39:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:39:24 UTC"},{"id":1637,"user_id":8779,"text":"<p>C'est fait!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14889,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-04 15:25:03 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-04 15:25:03 UTC"},{"id":1639,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Yes ! C'est exactement &ccedil;a !&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14891,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:40:28 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:40:28 UTC"},{"id":1640,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Yes ! C'est exactement &ccedil;a !&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14891,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:40:28 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:40:28 UTC"},{"id":1641,"user_id":9011,"text":"<p>Il faudrait sp&eacute;cifier la forme sous laquelle les donn&eacute;es pourraient &ecirc;tre partag&eacute;es (en conformit&eacute; avec la section &laquo;Paratage et r&eacute;utilisation&raquo; cela semble &ecirc;tre des donn&eacute;es d&eacute;finitives).</p>\r\n<p>Dans le cas o&ugrave; on envisage une utilisation secondaire des donn&eacute;es, il faudrait pr&eacute;ciser&nbsp;cette phrase &laquo;Les donn&eacute;es seront archiv&eacute;es pendant 7 ans apr&egrave;s la derni&egrave;re publication scientifique.&raquo; afin de savoir si c'est la derni&egrave;re publication en lien avec le projet initial ou celle en lien avec les autres projets.</p>\r\n<p>Enfin, en situation d'utilisation secondaire des donn&eacute;es, la p&eacute;riode de conservation de 7 ans peut &ecirc;tre revue &agrave; la hausse et les donn&eacute;es peuvent &ecirc;tre conserv&eacute;es pendant plus longtemps surtout si elles sont anonymes et que le risque de r&eacute;identification est pratiquement nulle.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14891,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-17 19:20:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-17 19:20:44 UTC"},{"id":1643,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Oui toutes ces conditions sont inscrites dans le formulaire d'information et de consentement. Si jamais tu en as besoin, fais moi signe !&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14892,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:42:19 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:42:19 UTC"},{"id":1644,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Oui toutes ces conditions sont inscrites dans le formulaire d'information et de consentement. Si jamais tu en as besoin, fais moi signe !&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14892,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:42:19 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:42:19 UTC"},{"id":1646,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Encore une fois, je pense FIC dans lequel les personnes s'engagent &agrave; participer &agrave; la recherche et &agrave; donc produire des donn&eacute;es qui appartiendront aux chercheurs. Pour le reste, je ne sais pas.... Jacinthe ?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14893,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:45:28 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:45:28 UTC"},{"id":1647,"user_id":8567,"text":"<p>Encore une fois, je pense FIC dans lequel les personnes s'engagent &agrave; participer &agrave; la recherche et &agrave; donc produire des donn&eacute;es qui appartiendront aux chercheurs. Pour le reste, je ne sais pas.... Jacinthe ?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":14893,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-07-03 21:45:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-03 21:45:29 UTC"},{"id":1654,"user_id":5271,"text":"<p>Avoid using proprietary software when possible (.csv rather than .xlsx), avoid using compressed formats when possible (.tiff rather than .jpeg)</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":15008,"archived_by":5271,"created_at":"2019-06-20 21:15:59 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-21 19:07:39 UTC"},{"id":1655,"user_id":5271,"text":"<p>-We probably won't need to worry about storage requirements at this point, as far as I can tell OSF doesn't have any storage limits. However, each file uploaded cannot exceed 5GB.</p>\r\n<p>-We do need to think about length of storage, which is dependent on what's happening to the projects after the class is over. The data should be backed up at the end of each class and stored appropriately as OSF is not a data repository.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15013,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-06-20 22:04:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-20 22:04:25 UTC"},{"id":1656,"user_id":5271,"text":"<p>-Are we storing our data anywhere else? Dataverse, etc.? If we don't already follow the 3-2-1 rule we should think about ways to reduce the risk of data loss.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15014,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-06-20 22:08:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-20 22:08:07 UTC"},{"id":1657,"user_id":5271,"text":"<p>Are we doing anything for long-term preservation?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15016,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-06-20 22:26:05 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-20 22:26:05 UTC"},{"id":1747,"user_id":9106,"text":"<p>test de l'annotation</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15402,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-08-08 06:58:38 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-08 06:58:38 UTC"},{"id":1754,"user_id":9156,"text":"<p>Que faire si on perd les formulaires de consentement qui contiennent le num&eacute;ro associ&eacute;?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15516,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-08-06 18:25:06 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-06 18:25:06 UTC"},{"id":1855,"user_id":9502,"text":"<p>in \"guidance\" tab more specific guidelines (McMaster specific) might be available in context of institutional level</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16288,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-09-13 15:58:48 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-13 15:58:48 UTC"},{"id":1856,"user_id":9502,"text":"<p>in \"guidance\" tab more specific guidelines (McMaster specific) might be available in context of institutional level</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16288,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-09-13 15:58:48 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-13 15:58:48 UTC"},{"id":1937,"user_id":9881,"text":"<p>Can the transcripts be shared? If they don`t have identification, can they be accessed by asking you permission? In this case, I think you can share this data but with limited access.&nbsp;<br />Do you know the format of your analyzed and final data?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16693,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:03:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:03:42 UTC"},{"id":1938,"user_id":9881,"text":"<p>Can the transcripts be shared? If they don`t have identification, can they be accessed by asking you permission? In this case, I think you can share this data but with limited access.&nbsp;<br />Do you know the format of your analyzed and final data?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16693,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:03:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:03:42 UTC"},{"id":1939,"user_id":9881,"text":"<p>In your case, I think an end-user license could be a good idea in order to share your transcript data.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16694,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:07:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:07:25 UTC"},{"id":1940,"user_id":9881,"text":"<p>In your case, I think an end-user license could be a good idea in order to share your transcript data.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16694,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:07:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:07:25 UTC"},{"id":1941,"user_id":9881,"text":"<p>You are probably publishing a paper about your research. I understand that this is a step that will let the research community know that your data exists. You may don't want to share it, but you can let people know that it exists.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16695,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:20:35 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:20:35 UTC"},{"id":1942,"user_id":9881,"text":"<p>You are probably publishing a paper about your research. I understand that this is a step that will let the research community know that your data exists. You may don't want to share it, but you can let people know that it exists.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16695,"archived_