i, placerat vel condimentum sit amet, convallis eget ex. Integer consequat ut nulla et egestas.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16772,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-09-30 16:37:41 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-30 16:37:41 UTC"},{"id":1990,"user_id":9645,"text":"<p>Excel is definitely accessible at present, since it can be opened by open-source programs.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 00:15:40 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 00:15:40 UTC"},{"id":1993,"user_id":9645,"text":"<p>what cloud in particular, and do you know that the service is secure?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16971,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 01:13:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 01:13:29 UTC"},{"id":1996,"user_id":9645,"text":"<p>the anonymized data can be shared, but not personally identifying data, right?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16973,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 01:18:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 01:18:25 UTC"},{"id":1997,"user_id":9645,"text":"<p>May want to ensure that you save as .xls, and not as .xlsx, as long as your data doesn't require specific .xlsx features?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16974,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 01:20:34 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 01:20:34 UTC"},{"id":1998,"user_id":9645,"text":"<p>The \"analyzed data\" and \"final data\" sections under Guidance, I think, give you the option for talking about extra things. E.g., if you have a huge dataset, you can still share a graph of it; and your \"final data\" is all the stuff you include in your final report.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16975,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 13:32:01 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 13:32:01 UTC"},{"id":1999,"user_id":9645,"text":"<p>I'd think there is a framework that already exists for handling sensitive patient data. Maybe place a reference to it here?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16981,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 12:42:15 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 12:42:15 UTC"},{"id":2000,"user_id":9645,"text":"<p>This probably needs to involve the university, they need to have a policy in place.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16983,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 01:11:09 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 01:11:09 UTC"},{"id":2001,"user_id":9706,"text":"<p>Though you did mention the instrument you will use, I think it would be ideal to highlight what data this specific instrument is going to collect - I am assuming it is used to collected soil characteristics from samples but then again, I am not sure so maybe adding this bit of information would be informative.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16984,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 15:53:11 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 15:53:11 UTC"},{"id":2002,"user_id":9706,"text":"<p>Can this data be reused? I assume it can be shared and there will be long-term access to the data but explaining if it will be shared and stored for long-term access is something you could add to this question.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16985,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 15:55:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 15:55:49 UTC"},{"id":2003,"user_id":9706,"text":"<p>Excellent convention for organizing the data!&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16986,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-29 22:18:32 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 22:18:32 UTC"},{"id":2004,"user_id":9706,"text":"<p>If this is the only documentation required, then the information you have provided is sufficient.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16987,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-29 22:19:33 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 22:19:33 UTC"},{"id":2005,"user_id":9706,"text":"<p>Will all data be captured, recorded and saved the same way and on the same google drive folder or will there be additional folders or stoage units where data will be saved?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16988,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-29 22:22:06 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 22:22:06 UTC"},{"id":2006,"user_id":9706,"text":"<p>Sounds like a good stoage and backup plan.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16990,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-29 22:25:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 22:25:44 UTC"},{"id":2007,"user_id":9706,"text":"<p>When data has been modified or collaborated on once it has been removed from the soil respiration chambers, is there a naming convention or something similar that you or your research team look to use to keep all data up to date and informative - maybe you can add this as well.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16991,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-29 22:27:28 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 22:27:28 UTC"},{"id":2009,"user_id":9706,"text":"<p>Will you provide access to the project for other students?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":16992,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-29 22:28:23 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-29 22:28:23 UTC"},{"id":2025,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>I think that this is substantive and likely comprehensive of the data you are accessing, but what about data outputs? There is a mixture of GIS-type data, but no mention of what that data will be synthesized into. E.g., will thematic boundary information be created by analyzing the RSdata for built environments and then joined with road data to develop some sort of temporal analysis of boundary changes? Also, have you considered the landsat data from the usgs?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17136,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:42:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:42:08 UTC"},{"id":2027,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>I have limited working familiarity with the Europa RS data, but I believe these are often outputted as jpegs or similar formats.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17137,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:44:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:44:20 UTC"},{"id":2029,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>How will the raw and processed data be managed? Often multiple iterations of data outputs are generated before a final modelling output is felt or determined to be correct? Will it be the same versioning as the data name?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17138,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:46:02 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:46:02 UTC"},{"id":2030,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>Not knowing anything about your study, will there be documentation to outline what the objective of the project is and why the selected data is necessary?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Will the metadata include the steps that outline how the data was prepared and cleaned for analysis, the specific tools and methods used to conduct the analysis, and what challenges might be encountered if trying to replicate your results? Will it also identify which attributes within each dataset were used, the RS imagery bands used, and the programs to conduct the analysis?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17139,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:50:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:50:43 UTC"},{"id":2031,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>May be worthwhile to address this question.</p>\r\n<p>Will files be stored in GitHub to ensure completness of documentation? Will a short white paper be written on the methods of the data prep and analysis? Etc.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17140,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:53:11 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:53:11 UTC"},{"id":2034,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>How large is the data set? Depending on the amount of imagery you are using, I would guess this to be in the low GB range.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17142,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:54:53 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:54:53 UTC"},{"id":2035,"user_id":9881,"text":"<p>I have no idea about the size of the data. I began to collect the data this week, so maybe in the following weeks, I will have an idea.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17142,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:37:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:37:16 UTC"},{"id":2036,"user_id":9881,"text":"<p>I have no idea about the size of the data. I began to collect the data this week, so maybe in the following weeks, I will have an idea.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17142,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:37:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:37:16 UTC"},{"id":2037,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>You have identified an offsite copy, multiple copies of the data, and different mediums which is good. Perhaps a copy stored on an external HD or the external backup drives of the computers would be appropriate to minimize the potential for data loss.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17143,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:57:13 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:57:13 UTC"},{"id":2039,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>Since you are not working with confidential data, this is likely sufficient and there is minimal concern about sending information across emails. Should collaborators wish to edit or otherwise modify the project data, would it need to be changed on your computers, or would they have access to the remote copy and be able to make changes from there? Similarily, how would they contribute to the data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17144,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 15:59:46 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 15:59:46 UTC"},{"id":2040,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>Depending on the size of your data, you may exceed the account size of GitHub (1 GB), if this is the case, how long will that data be stored (5 years was mentioned) and who will pay those account fees? How will a original copy of the data be kept - on the researcher's personal computer, the supervisors, or somewhere else?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17145,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:02:31 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:02:31 UTC"},{"id":2041,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>It may be worth noting that your file formats are already likely preservation friendly. I believe shapefiles can be read by most non-ESRI programs include open software packages like R.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17146,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:04:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:04:43 UTC"},{"id":2042,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>In this consideration, is it your right to share the raw or processed outputs of data that you yourself have not collected? There may be usage restrictions depending on who formally owns the data. While as academics we often have broad access to otherwise very expensive data, we often do not have the right to share copies of the origina datasets. Might be worth looking into the EULA's for the datasets mentioned.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17147,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:07:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:07:49 UTC"},{"id":2044,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>This seems reasonable and sufficient.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17149,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:10:52 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:10:52 UTC"},{"id":2045,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>What is the timeframe associated with the responsibilities? Five years was mentioned, after the completion of grad or phd work, who then manages the data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17150,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:12:37 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:12:37 UTC"},{"id":2046,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>Might be worth noting that the metadata mentioned in early sections, as well as the overview documentation, would be very helpful in ensuring a smooth transition to a different primary or different researcher.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17151,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:14:09 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:14:09 UTC"},{"id":2047,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>This seems reasonable and sufficient.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17152,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:14:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:14:49 UTC"},{"id":2048,"user_id":9636,"text":"<p>In some respects, this may go back to the issue of who owns the data and given any generated outputs from that data, who is the owner of the IP? Is it the data owner, is it you as the reseachers, or is the institution which is paying all of the fees? Or some other 3rd-party?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17154,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-25 16:16:34 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-25 16:16:34 UTC"},{"id":2067,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>Do you need to have the version date in the file name? This could become cumbersom, and it would be better to use V1, V2, etc. (think if you are building a file over several days). Keep in mind too that the the date will be recorded when you save it.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17181,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 22:52:47 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 22:52:47 UTC"},{"id":2068,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>Do you need to have the version date in the file name? This could become cumbersom, and it would be better to use V1, V2, etc. (think if you are building a file over several days). Keep in mind too that the the date will be recorded when you save it.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17181,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 22:52:47 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 22:52:47 UTC"},{"id":2069,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>Will there be a data dictionary?</p>\r\n<p>As the data is manipulated, you will also want to keep notes on decisions made (ie., if variables are defined, recoded, user-made, etc.)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17182,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 22:54:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 22:54:42 UTC"},{"id":2070,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>Will there be a data dictionary?</p>\r\n<p>As the data is manipulated, you will also want to keep notes on decisions made (ie., if variables are defined, recoded, user-made, etc.)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17182,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 22:54:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 22:54:42 UTC"},{"id":2075,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>We will be working with a file server which will hold the original data file and versions. The computer that is used to manipulate the data will have a firewall, antivirus, disk encryption, and browser security.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17186,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 22:58:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 22:58:55 UTC"},{"id":2076,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>We will be working with a file server which will hold the original data file and versions. The computer that is used to manipulate the data will have a firewall, antivirus, disk encryption, and browser security.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":17186,"archived_by":9729,"created_at":"2019-10-24 22:58:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-30 20:54:45 UTC"},{"id":2077,"user_id":9958,"text":"<p>Maybe a bit more specific, how will the data be stored on these computers (subdirectory/folder etc.).</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":17186,"archived_by":9729,"created_at":"2019-10-27 16:01:23 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-30 20:54:45 UTC"},{"id":2081,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>See previous note regarding holding the data on a server. Like you note, this will only be accessible by the researchrs.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17187,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:00:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:00:43 UTC"},{"id":2082,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>See previous note regarding holding the data on a server. Like you note, this will only be accessible by the researchrs.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":17187,"archived_by":9729,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:00:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-30 20:34:02 UTC"},{"id":2086,"user_id":9958,"text":"<p>I don't know if this it too much to ask, but how will the data be destroyed? Are there specific guidelines/criteria that need to be followed to ensure that data is completely deleted?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17188,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 16:05:09 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 16:05:09 UTC"},{"id":2087,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>I\"m not sure how this fits with the previous response where you indicated it would not be preserved. Based on our ethics permission, we must destroy the data at the end of the project.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17189,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:04:09 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:04:09 UTC"},{"id":2088,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>I\"m not sure how this fits with the previous response where you indicated it would not be preserved. Based on our ethics permission, we must destroy the data at the end of the project.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17189,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:04:09 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:04:09 UTC"},{"id":2089,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>One option might be to indicate data can be shared (with PI's permissoin), but all personal identification will be stripped from the (residential location, work location, etc.)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17190,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:06:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:06:29 UTC"},{"id":2090,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>One option might be to indicate data can be shared (with PI's permissoin), but all personal identification will be stripped from the (residential location, work location, etc.)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17190,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:06:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:06:29 UTC"},{"id":2091,"user_id":9958,"text":"<p>Are there multiple journal articles that the data will be featured in? Or will there be one that this is intended for?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17192,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 16:09:17 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 16:09:17 UTC"},{"id":2093,"user_id":9958,"text":"<p>Will there be a specific team member that will be assigned to this in the future (i.e. future graduate student?)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17193,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 16:13:02 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 16:13:02 UTC"},{"id":2095,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>You can also indicate that the PI will identify other members of the research team to handle data administration.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17194,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:08:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:08:16 UTC"},{"id":2096,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>You can also indicate that the PI will identify other members of the research team to handle data administration.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17194,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:08:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:08:16 UTC"},{"id":2098,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>There will be no paper based surveys (at least in this phase). All data will be stored on a server as noted. You should note here that confidential information will not be released.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17196,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:10:45 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:10:45 UTC"},{"id":2099,"user_id":10013,"text":"<p>There will be no paper based surveys (at least in this phase). All data will be stored on a server as noted. You should note here that confidential information will not be released.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17196,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-24 23:10:45 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 23:10:45 UTC"},{"id":2112,"user_id":5130,"text":"<p>This looks good.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17273,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 15:48:51 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 15:48:51 UTC"},{"id":2113,"user_id":5130,"text":"<p>This looks good.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17273,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 15:48:51 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 15:48:51 UTC"},{"id":2114,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>Looks good, you have many different types of data listed which is great.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17273,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:26:58 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:26:58 UTC"},{"id":2115,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>Maybe describe the format that was used in the session 7 notes? Once you have the files divided by years how do you pan to name each file that is saved in this folder? (may or may not apply to the kind of data you work with)</p>\r\n<p>For example: files will be named as followed: Name_Project Descriptor_Version_Date Created</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17275,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:34:38 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:34:38 UTC"},{"id":2116,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>Looks good, only if applicable I would also add then a note on how the data itself can be easily interpreted by a reader. data may be eaasy for you to interpret and read but more complexe data may use terms and be structured in such a way that someone who was unfamiliar with your data may struggle.</p>\r\n<p>If there is a way to prevent this please explain.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17276,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:38:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:38:44 UTC"},{"id":2117,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>Updated in which way? how will your documentation change with updates and how does this ensure consistancy?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17277,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:40:12 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:40:12 UTC"},{"id":2122,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>If you are cloning or forking data how will you combine data contributed by collaborators into the data files that you are updating/creating?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17281,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:46:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:46:55 UTC"},{"id":2123,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>I would maybe clarify what type of data each of the mentioned are. For example, would your R code be considered your raw data or is ti your processed data? etc.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17284,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:50:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:50:20 UTC"},{"id":2124,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>will your data be published? may want to check if your data will also have licenses associated with where it is published.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17285,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:52:18 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:52:18 UTC"},{"id":2125,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>will there be abything published at the end of your analysis on the data you have aquired?</p>\r\n<p>Will you be sharing your findings at the end of your project?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17286,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:56:01 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:56:01 UTC"},{"id":2126,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>will there be any requirement for training individuals in the projec team in order for them to use your work and interpret the data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17287,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 13:58:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 13:58:07 UTC"},{"id":2127,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>any personal expenses involved? USB sticks, hard drives for data storage?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17289,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 14:00:10 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 14:00:10 UTC"},{"id":2128,"user_id":9672,"text":"<p>are there any legal restrictions put in place by the providers of the data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17292,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-28 14:02:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-28 14:02:55 UTC"},{"id":2137,"user_id":9729,"text":"<p>Can you please include some details on file naming (not versions)? Like how you will name the files.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17312,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 04:29:45 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 04:29:45 UTC"},{"id":2138,"user_id":9729,"text":"<p>Is there any confidential data? If yes, would that be good idea to store them in personal drives or in cloud?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17316,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 04:35:05 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 04:35:05 UTC"},{"id":2139,"user_id":9729,"text":"<p>That's a really great plan. But how you will manage all these versions without creating confusions?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17321,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 04:39:31 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 04:39:31 UTC"},{"id":2140,"user_id":9729,"text":"<p>Do users need permission to reuse the data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17323,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 04:40:50 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 04:40:50 UTC"},{"id":2141,"user_id":9729,"text":"<p>Who will assign roles?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17324,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-27 04:42:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-27 04:42:54 UTC"},{"id":2152,"user_id":9635,"text":"<p>What are the data sources and the projects? Are they related to a paper?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17440,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 15:52:04 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 15:52:04 UTC"},{"id":2153,"user_id":9635,"text":"<p>What are the data sources and the projects? Are they related to a paper?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17440,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 15:52:04 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 15:52:04 UTC"},{"id":2154,"user_id":9635,"text":"<p>Might want to include underscores for the naming and avoid wordy descriptions. Eg. Reanalysis_LTS.R</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17442,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 15:54:39 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 15:54:39 UTC"},{"id":2155,"user_id":9635,"text":"<p>*changed Gituhb to Github.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>*changed requrired to required</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17443,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 15:56:39 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 15:56:39 UTC"},{"id":2158,"user_id":9635,"text":"<p>Approximately how many gigabyes? How big are the data that goes in the network? If it's collected every year/time period how big are the collected files?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17446,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 16:09:26 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 16:09:26 UTC"},{"id":2163,"user_id":9635,"text":"<p>What forms will be the data in? Eg. shape file, csv</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":17450,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-10-23 16:18:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 16:18:20 UTC"},{"id":2264,"user_id":10146,"text":"<p>I cannot find A Way Home's Google Drive storage capabilities, and the file sizes are not available to me.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18010,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-01-16 15:18:19 UTC","updated_at":"2020-01-16 15:18:19 UTC"},{"id":2266,"user_id":10146,"text":"<p>I'm not sure if we should include the data captured by the YAP tool.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18013,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-01-16 17:29:52 UTC","updated_at":"2020-01-16 17:29:52 UTC"},{"id":2267,"user_id":10146,"text":"<p>Will need to consult York Library about this and the importance of it.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18015,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-01-17 19:39:05 UTC","updated_at":"2020-01-17 19:39:05 UTC"},{"id":2268,"user_id":10146,"text":"<p>This may change, I'm not sure what the current standing is on this issue.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18019,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-01-17 20:09:43 UTC","updated_at":"2020-01-17 20:09:43 UTC"},{"id":2283,"user_id":10177,"text":"<p>Need to complete this question after meeting with Cameron</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18067,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-11-11 22:25:01 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-11 22:25:01 UTC"},{"id":2284,"user_id":10177,"text":"<p>Need to complete this question after meeting with Cameron</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18067,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-11-11 22:25:02 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-11 22:25:02 UTC"},{"id":2289,"user_id":10230,"text":"<p>Does anyone have the specific name of the XML format we were discussing? Portland something-or-other?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18184,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-11-26 22:49:39 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-26 22:49:39 UTC"},{"id":2290,"user_id":10230,"text":"<p>Does anyone have the specific name of the XML format we were discussing? Portland something-or-other?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18184,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-11-26 22:49:41 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-26 22:49:41 UTC"},{"id":2291,"user_id":10230,"text":"<p>Sharon? Can you help us please? We're out of our depth on this one!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18189,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-11-26 23:05:00 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-26 23:05:00 UTC"},{"id":2292,"user_id":10230,"text":"<p>Sharon? Can you help us please? We're out of our depth on this one!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18189,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2019-11-26 23:05:00 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-26 23:05:00 UTC"},{"id":2414,"user_id":10844,"text":"<p>Ownership: <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do we own the data as the data are created by volunteers or through the crowdsourcing platform (Paid)?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Image Copyright: Do we have permission to share the image extracted from Youtube.</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":18741,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-02-12 22:42:52 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-12 22:42:52 UTC"},{"id":2473,"user_id":11225,"text":"<p>ne sont pas des formats recommand&eacute;s par UK Data Service. Il faudrait utiliser des fichiers .por, .dsv.dta</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19054,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-02-13 15:42:37 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-13 15:42:37 UTC"},{"id":2474,"user_id":11225,"text":"<p>on parle du contr&ocirc;le des versions ici</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19055,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-02-13 16:12:20 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-13 16:12:20 UTC"},{"id":2504,"user_id":3451,"text":"<p>Erin don't forget this is your section - fill it out by Dec.10</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19221,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-02-21 17:39:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 17:39:53 UTC"},{"id":2541,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>Should add in the transcription (text) data as well. If there there are any data being created via analytic software, or code that is written, you can include that here too.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19370,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 17:04:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 17:04:13 UTC"},{"id":2542,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>If adding the text (transription) data then can indicate the format here. You mentioned MSWord, which makes sense to work with, but for the longer term preservation those should be converted to. a non-proprieatary format, such as a basic .txt file.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19371,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 17:15:49 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 17:15:49 UTC"},{"id":2543,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>We spoke about this one already on the call and think that you are on the right track here. A couple of suggestions, helpful to speak to the file versioning in a bit more detail (e.g., Raw, Master, Analytic - all as applicable) and also to have a date stamp.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19372,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 17:20:57 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 17:20:57 UTC"},{"id":2544,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>This is where I additiaonlly recommend speaking to the development and implementation of a file naming convention protocol and crosswalk document - that will allow anyone to easily inderstand your file naming conventions and locate fles of interest across context and versions.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19373,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 17:22:47 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 17:22:47 UTC"},{"id":2545,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>Similar to above, you could additionally speak to having a data collection protocol which includes a reference to the file naming documentation. Part of the data collection protocol can include when and how files are named, and also a file verification checking process.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19374,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 17:25:17 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 17:25:17 UTC"},{"id":2546,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>At this stage I think it is fine to say that beyond the in-house file naming conventions you are also consulting with local metadata experts on campus to identify any established metadata standards that might optimally support your project.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19375,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 17:26:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 17:26:53 UTC"},{"id":2550,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>We spoke a bit about this on the call, so this is just more to help remind and provide information. Google Drive (or Compute Canada's cloud environment if that ends up happening) is a solution for supporting the active phases of the research, but not for supporting the &nbsp;long term preservation, discovery, sharing and reuse of data. Goes back to the trusted digital repository and DOI's conversation that we had.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once it is determined what suports will be in place for sharing data with collaborators you can certainly indicate that. For the long term sharing of data I think it is ok to say that there are no plans to destroy any of the data and that you will look to deposit the processed data (and maybe the raw?) into a trusted digital repository such as e.g., Dataverse, ERC, FRDR, for long term preservation, discovery and acess, and that you will work with experts in the DIgital Initiatives area of the Library to help guide you during this process.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19381,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 17:59:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 17:59:58 UTC"},{"id":2551,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>Similar to previous - can indicate that you will work with Library folks to help guide. I think likely though that you are looking at having an open CC-BY license from the sounds of things. See URL below for more information:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/ca/</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19382,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 18:03:14 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 18:03:14 UTC"},{"id":2552,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>Can revise this re: data repository, DOIs, etc. I can help refine it later with you if you'd like.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19383,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-01 18:04:09 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-01 18:04:09 UTC"},{"id":2586,"user_id":6244,"text":"<p>Need to be filled.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19632,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-22 10:37:48 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-22 10:37:48 UTC"},{"id":2588,"user_id":6244,"text":"<p>Are there other types data that will be collected?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19635,"archived_by":6244,"created_at":"2020-04-13 15:59:26 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-23 02:54:53 UTC"},{"id":2594,"user_id":3451,"text":"<p>test</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19689,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-17 15:39:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-17 15:39:53 UTC"},{"id":2595,"user_id":9778,"text":"<p>I wanted to highlight the temp data; you've done an excellent job describing how you will organize, process, and store your video/tag data, but I didn't see any details about the temperature data in the \"data documentation and metadata\" section.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19690,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-09 15:54:08 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 15:54:08 UTC"},{"id":2596,"user_id":9778,"text":"<p>I've highlighted sections that we need to work on, such as the mechanism for sharing data.&nbsp; At this time, we do not have a central data storage location for Module E data, but some possibilities include Google Drive, Dropbox, Network-Attached storage (Sue Ziegler), or a MUN-hosted FTP site.&nbsp; Progress to identify the best resources is on-going (SJ).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Otherwise, great answer, Ben!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19692,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-09 15:42:56 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 15:42:56 UTC"},{"id":2597,"user_id":9778,"text":"<p>Once we identify the best respository(-ies) for your data, we'll need to update this field with any costs anciticipate during data upload and archive in the repository.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19693,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-09 15:44:25 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 15:44:25 UTC"},{"id":2598,"user_id":9778,"text":"<p>This looks GREAT, thank you for staying on top of file organization!&nbsp; I had more questions about the naming conventions, but you've anticipated that and already answered it in your next metadata question.</p>\r\n<p>Note: instrumentation documention for many repositories is LONG and comprehensive, so we'll want to be sure we have as much information about your equipment retained as we can.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19695,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-09 15:48:46 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 15:50:26 UTC"},{"id":2600,"user_id":9778,"text":"<p>Is your R code something you've created, or will you be using someone else's code?&nbsp; If the former, will we want to document and share that code as well?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19697,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-09 15:51:30 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 15:51:30 UTC"},{"id":2602,"user_id":9778,"text":"<p>We will need to discuss within your research group and Module E to determine what resources are available for collaborating in the short to medium-term.&nbsp; Please feel free to bug me about this as much as you need to.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19700,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-09 15:56:30 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 15:56:30 UTC"},{"id":2603,"user_id":9778,"text":"<p>Ben, is your work coordinated with the Nunatsiavut Government science office?&nbsp; I'm not yet clear on agreements between OFI and NG in terms of IP/knowledge and sharing, but let's flag this for follow up.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19701,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-09 16:00:36 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 16:00:36 UTC"},{"id":2604,"user_id":9778,"text":"<p>Thanks for getting started on this, Mary!&nbsp; If you could also edit the plan details to include a few sentence \"elevator-pitch\" style project description, it would definitely help the reader put your dataset descriptions and the rest of your responses into better context.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19706,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-09 16:05:47 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 16:05:47 UTC"},{"id":2630,"user_id":12460,"text":"<p>Ici, il faut confirmer le format sous lequel les donn&eacute;es vid&eacute;os seront enregistr&eacute;es.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19808,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-04-28 11:17:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 16:08:13 UTC"},{"id":2632,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>Pr&eacute;ciser: la base de donnn&eacute;es sera mise &agrave; jour r&eacute;guli&egrave;rement - est-ce de fa&ccedil;on quotidienne? hebodomadaire ? mensuelle? ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19809,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-05-22 02:58:59 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 02:58:59 UTC"},{"id":2634,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>@ Jo&euml;l pr&eacute;ciser document = dictionnaire de variables?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19810,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:28:38 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-11 12:14:50 UTC"},{"id":2635,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>@Jo&euml;l, Pr&eacute;ciser : d'instaurer les syst&egrave;mes ? Tu veux dire les porc&eacute;dures?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pr&eacute;ciser : la r&eacute;daction de documents qui d&eacute;taillent le processus d&eacute;cisionnel ainsi que les diff&eacute;rentes d&eacute;marches de recherche - tu veux dire proc&egrave;s verbal ? Il faudrait &ecirc;tre pr&eacute;cis et tenter de ne pas ajouter bcp de t&acirc;ches...</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19811,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:22:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:07:11 UTC"},{"id":2637,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>@ Jo&euml;l - Sauvegarde sur mon ordinateur - estce vraiment pratique et r&eacute;aliste? cela pourrait &ecirc;tre autre disque externe ou ton ordinateur ?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19814,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:30:02 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:08:18 UTC"},{"id":2638,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>@Jo&euml;l pr&eacute;ciser le nom du document ?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19815,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:26:37 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:09:07 UTC"},{"id":2640,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>@Jo&euml;l - juste avant on a indiqu&eacute; disque externe et ordinateur VDrapeau?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19816,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:31:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:11:32 UTC"},{"id":2641,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>Conservation combien de temps? 5 ans (pour nous) puis apr&egrave;s banque sant&eacute; durable PULSAR?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19816,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:32:39 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:12:35 UTC"},{"id":2642,"user_id":12460,"text":"<p>Point &agrave; voir avec PULSAR</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19817,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-04-28 12:04:54 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 16:05:35 UTC"},{"id":2643,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>Pr&eacute;ciser : les normes relatives &agrave; la confidentialit&eacute;, au respect de la vie priv&eacute;e ainsi qu'&agrave; la propri&eacute;t&eacute; intellectuelle...en conformit&eacute; avec le cadre de gestion PULSAR</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19818,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:11:47 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:15:20 UTC"},{"id":2644,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>@Jo&euml;l - Pr&eacute;ciser apr&egrave;s combien de temps ? Il me semble que l,on avait dit 5 ans?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19821,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:14:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:19:18 UTC"},{"id":2645,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>Un protocole de transfert de connaissances ? je ne suis pas certaine car il me semble que le plan de gestion des donn&eacute;es devrait pr&eacute;voir cela...</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19822,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:19:29 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:20:51 UTC"},{"id":2646,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>Bonne question!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Je dirais un PPR &agrave; 25% ? + temps consultation et ressource PULSAR?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19823,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:17:44 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 03:17:44 UTC"},{"id":2647,"user_id":12461,"text":"<p>@ Jo&euml;l nous aurons des donn&eacute;es sensibles - par ex. courriel et num de t&eacute;l&eacute;phone (pour les questions &eacute;chologiques). merci de pr&eacute;ciser les autres.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19824,"archived_by":12460,"created_at":"2020-05-22 03:35:57 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-22 13:34:54 UTC"},{"id":2657,"user_id":12140,"text":"<p>Sourayan is this appropriate?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":19940,"archived_by":12140,"created_at":"2020-05-08 20:36:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-08 20:37:20 UTC"},{"id":2658,"user_id":12915,"text":"<p>for example&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19960,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-02 20:25:51 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-02 20:25:51 UTC"},{"id":2678,"user_id":5700,"text":"<p>To be answered.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":20104,"archived_by":5700,"created_at":"2020-06-01 13:46:01 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-01 13:52:02 UTC"},{"id":2680,"user_id":5700,"text":"<p>To be answered.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":20106,"archived_by":5700,"created_at":"2020-06-01 13:46:48 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-01 13:49:51 UTC"},{"id":2681,"user_id":5700,"text":"<p>A little piece about how consistency in the creation of logs and syntax files would be managed (template? standardized format?) would help make this section a little more robust.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":20107,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-01 14:35:11 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-01 14:35:11 UTC"},{"id":2682,"user_id":5700,"text":"<p>To be answered.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":20108,"archived_by":5700,"created_at":"2020-06-01 13:50:45 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-01 13:52:46 UTC"},{"id":2683,"user_id":5700,"text":"<p>A little detail about what those tasks might look like would be helpful - what does following the data management plan look like?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":20117,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-01 14:23:48 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-01 14:23:48 UTC"},{"id":2729,"user_id":13722,"text":"<p>Unless the site locations are sensitive...</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":20417,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-12 20:00:23 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-12 20:00:23 UTC"},{"id":2730,"user_id":13722,"text":"<p>The collected data is not sensitive, however, we would have to check with the landowners if they mind that the gps locations of the sample sites are shared. If not, the coordinates linked to the cores can be removed; the data would still be valuable just not spatially.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":20421,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-12 19:15:17 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-12 19:15:17 UTC"},{"id":2742,"user_id":14573,"text":"<p>I'm not really sure of the best way to do this - what do you think?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":20512,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-06-15 13:32:52 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 13:32:52 UTC"},{"id":2792,"user_id":4897,"text":"<p><strong>Denote dates in YYYYMMDD format</strong></p>\r\n<p>BECAUSE: Computers sort YYYYMMDD in chronological order.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Use a short unique identifier (e.g. Project Name or Grant #)</strong></p>\r\n<p>DO: CHHM</p>\r\n<p>DON&rsquo;T: Centre for Hip Health and Mobility</p>\r\n<p>BECAUSE: Short filenames prevent the need for side scrolling and column adjustment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Include a summary of content (e.g. Questionnaire or GrantProposal) as part of the file name<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>DO: FileNm_<strong>Guidelines</strong>_20180409_v01.docx</p>\r\n<p>DON&rsquo;T: FileNm_20180409.docx</p>\r\n<p>BECAUSE: Files will be easier to find.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Use _ as delimiters. Avoid these special characters: &amp; , * % # * ( ) ! @$ ^ ~ &lsquo; { } [ ] ? &lt; &gt; &ndash;</strong></p>\r\n<p>DO: FileNm<strong>_</strong>Guidelines<strong>_</strong>20140409<strong>_</strong>v01.docx</p>\r\n<p>DON&rsquo;T: FileNm Guidelines 2014 04 09 v01.docx</p>\r\n<p>BECAUSE: Different computer systems handle&nbsp;special characters differently &ndash; filing order, etc.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Keep track of document versions either sequentially (e.g. v01, v02,) or with a unique date and time ( e.g. 20140403_1800)</strong></p>\r\n<p>DO: FileNm_Guidelines_20140409_<strong>v01</strong>.docx</p>\r\n<p>DON&rsquo;T: FileNm_Guidelines_20140409_<strong>Review</strong>.docx AND FileNm_Guidelines_20140409_<strong>Investigation</strong>.docx</p>\r\n<p>BECAUSE: Two years from now, you won&rsquo;t remember what you meant.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Make folder hierarchies as simple as possible</strong></p>\r\n<p>DO: F:/<strong>&nbsp;Env/LIBR/</strong>DataMgmt_FileFormats_20140409_v01.docx</p>\r\n<p>DON&rsquo;T: F:/<strong>Environment/Library/Woodward/Data/Education/Materials/Draft/2014/04/</strong>-DataMgmt_FileFormats_20140409_v01.docx</p>\r\n<p>BECAUSE: Complex folder hierarchies are harder to navigate and offer more opportunities for filing errors. System back-ups may take longer.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":20877,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-07-09 18:04:40 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-09 18:04:40 UTC"},{"id":2795,"user_id":4897,"text":"<ul>\r\n<li>Title</li>\r\n<li>Creator: names and addresses of data creator(s)</li>\r\n<li>Identifier: can be a permanent identifier or an internal project number.</li>\r\n<li>Funder</li>\r\n<li>Rights: Intellectual property or licensing rights for the data.</li>\r\n<li>Access Information</li>\r\n<li>Language</li>\r\n<li>Dates</li>\r\n<li>Project description</li>\r\n<li>Methodology: how data was generated.</li>\r\n<li>Data Structure: including relationships between files.</li>\r\n<li>Variable names or other data level documentation (if not self evident or embedded in the file).</li>\r\n<li>Data Citation: Preferred format for citing data.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Documentation can be included in a README.txt file (or other relevant file name) in the folder with the data files.The README.txt file should accompany the data if files are moved or deposited in a repository. Be sure the README file includes such information as file folder heirarchy or other external context of the data.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tempate 2</p>\r\n<pre class=\"bp-text bp-text-plain hljs bp-is-scrollable\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"bp-text-code txt\">This DATSETNAMEreadme.txt file was generated on YYYY-MM-DD by NAME\r\n&lt;help text is included in angle brackets, and can be deleted before saving&gt;\r\n\r\n\r\nGENERAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\n1. Title of Dataset: \r\n\r\n2. Author Information\r\n\tA. Principal Investigator Contact Information\r\n\t\tName: \r\n\t\tInstitution: \r\n\t\tAddress: \r\n\t\tEmail: \r\n\r\n\tB. Associate or Co-investigator Contact Information\r\n\t\tName: \r\n\t\tInstitution: \r\n\t\tAddress: \r\n\t\tEmail: \r\n\r\n\tC. Alternate Contact Information\r\n\t\tName: \r\n\t\tInstitution: \r\n\t\tAddress: \r\n\t\tEmail: \r\n\r\n3. Date of data collection (single date, range, approximate date) &lt;suggested format YYYY-MM-DD&gt;: \r\n\r\n4. Geographic location of data collection &lt;latitude, longiute, or city/region, State, Country, as appropriate&gt;: \r\n\r\n5. Information about funding sources that supported the collection of the data: \r\n\r\n\r\nSHARING/ACCESS INFORMATION\r\n\r\n1. Licenses/restrictions placed on the data: \r\n\r\n2. Links to publications that cite or use the data: \r\n\r\n3. Links to other publicly accessible locations of the data: \r\n\r\n4. Links/relationships to ancillary data sets: \r\n\r\n5. Was data derived from another source? yes/no\r\n\tA. If yes, list source(s): \r\n\r\n6. Recommended citation for this dataset: \r\n\r\n\r\nDATA &amp; FILE OVERVIEW\r\n\r\n1. File List: \r\n&lt;list all files (or folders, as appropriate for dataset organization) contained in the dataset, with a brief description&gt;\r\n\r\n2. Relationship between files, if important: \r\n\r\n3. Additional related data collected that was not included in the current data package: \r\n\r\n4. Are there multiple versions of the dataset? yes/no\r\n\tA. If yes, name of file(s) that was updated: \r\n\t\ti. Why was the file updated? \r\n\t\tii. When was the file updated? \r\n\r\n\r\nMETHODOLOGICAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\n1. Description of methods used for collection/generation of data: \r\n&lt;Include links or references to publications or other documentation containing experimental design or protocols used in data collection&gt;\r\n\r\n2. Methods for processing the data: \r\n&lt;describe how the submitted data were generated from the raw or collected data&gt;\r\n\r\n3. Instrument- or software-specific information needed to interpret the data: \r\n&lt;include full name and version of software, and any necessary packages or libraries needed to run scripts&gt;\r\n\r\n4. Standards and calibration information, if appropriate: \r\n\r\n5. Environmental/experimental conditions: \r\n\r\n6. Describe any quality-assurance procedures performed on the data: \r\n\r\n7. People involved with sample collection, processing, analysis and/or submission: \r\n\r\n\r\nDATA-SPECIFIC INFORMATION FOR: [FILENAME]\r\n&lt;repeat this section for each dataset, folder or file, as appropriate&gt;\r\n\r\n1. Number of variables: \r\n\r\n2. Number of cases/rows: \r\n\r\n3. Variable List: \r\n&lt;list variable name(s), description(s), unit(s)and value labels as appropriate for each&gt;\r\n\r\n4. Missing data codes: \r\n&lt;list code/symbol and definition&gt;n\r\n\r\n5. Specialized formats or other abbreviations used: </code></pre>","archived":0,"answer_id":20878,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-07-15 22:15:50 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-15 22:18:47 UTC"},{"id":2796,"user_id":4897,"text":"<p>average size of one hour of audio?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":20881,"archived_by":4897,"created_at":"2020-07-09 18:08:17 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-15 22:12:11 UTC"},{"id":2809,"user_id":15835,"text":"<p>The link to the Encryption re: U of A doesn't work.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":21017,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-07-22 17:51:09 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-22 17:51:09 UTC"},{"id":2815,"user_id":15927,"text":"<p>https://archives.uqam.ca/gestion-documents-administratifs/archives-environnement/8-gestion-documents-administratifs/18-guide-classification-uniforme.html</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":21076,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-01-14 15:17:44 UTC","updated_at":"2021-01-14 15:17:44 UTC"},{"id":2838,"user_id":16377,"text":"<p>Direct access to the Ubuntu virtual machine where the AIS data is collected, processed, and stored will be reserved for those who have been trained on system and program specifics, and have access to the University of Victoria's network. Those outside of this trianing, and network, will be able to request any data required through trained persons who will send the data to them in a spatial or table format.</p>\r\n<p>Any spatial or statistical products created from the data will become available once the research is complete, and will be accompanied by detailed descriptions how the products were created, along with any assumptions made.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":21221,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-09-10 02:57:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-10 02:57:53 UTC"},{"id":2839,"user_id":16382,"text":"<p>Data size?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":21236,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-08-11 16:27:41 UTC","updated_at":"2020-08-11 16:27:41 UTC"},{"id":2840,"user_id":16382,"text":"<p>Q: Standard procedure for data stored in U of G repository?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":21236,"archived_by":16382,"created_at":"2020-08-11 16:57:06 UTC","updated_at":"2020-08-11 16:59:52 UTC"},{"id":2841,"user_id":16382,"text":"<p>Q: Standard procedure for data stored in U of G repository?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":21237,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-08-11 17:00:03 UTC","updated_at":"2020-08-11 17:00:03 UTC"},{"id":2842,"user_id":16382,"text":"<p>Q:Any restrictions due to the nature of the grant?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Specifically what grant?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":21239,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-08-11 17:07:34 UTC","updated_at":"2020-08-11 17:10:10 UTC"},{"id":2843,"user_id":16382,"text":"<p>Q:Restrictions on sharing?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":21241,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-08-11 17:13:03 UTC","updated_at":"2020-08-11 17:13:03 UTC"},{"id":2930,"user_id":3451,"text":"<p>tet</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":22185,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-10-21 14:10:29 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-21 14:10:29 UTC"},{"id":3057,"user_id":15975,"text":"<p>J'invente, mais il ne serait pas mal de le faire pour de vrai...</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23424,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-11-09 05:47:48 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-09 05:47:48 UTC"},{"id":3058,"user_id":15975,"text":"<p>J'invente, mais il ne serait pas mal de le faire pour de vrai...</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23424,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-11-09 05:48:07 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-09 05:48:07 UTC"},{"id":3059,"user_id":15975,"text":"<p>&Agrave; terme, faut-il peut-&ecirc;tre consid&eacute;rer quelque chose comme&nbsp;<span class=\"spellmod\" title=\"data verse, data-verse, d'adverse, d'averse, adverse, d'adverses, traverse, travers&eacute;, d'averses\">dataverse?</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"spellmod\" title=\"data verse, data-verse, d'adverse, d'averse, adverse, d'adverses, traverse, travers&eacute;, d'averses\">https://dataverse.scholarsportal.info/dataverse/uvic</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23431,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-11-09 06:09:24 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-09 06:09:24 UTC"},{"id":3060,"user_id":15975,"text":"<p>Encore, j'invente...</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23434,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-11-09 06:45:23 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-09 06:45:23 UTC"},{"id":3068,"user_id":18468,"text":"<p>We need more information here!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23587,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-11-26 19:47:46 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-26 19:47:46 UTC"},{"id":3078,"user_id":18614,"text":"<p>The UK data service doesn't recommend \"binary formats of GIS and CAD packages.\" Is .qgz a binary of this type?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23696,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-12 01:57:57 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-12 01:57:57 UTC"},{"id":3081,"user_id":18468,"text":"<p>Metadata are stored separately from the .shp and .tif files - we should try to follow international standards (e.g. ISO 19115. Geographic Information Metadata) here. The metadata can be edited in QGIS and exported as QMetadata (.qmd), but this is a bad choice for long-term use. We should consider how to formalize metadata.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23698,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-16 23:41:03 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-16 23:41:03 UTC"},{"id":3092,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Deb are we storing interview/focus group data here?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23847,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 13:29:42 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 13:29:42 UTC"},{"id":3093,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Ideally, probably .csv or xls files?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23848,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 13:34:37 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 13:34:37 UTC"},{"id":3097,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Deb will any of the final spreadsheets used to make the visualizations (Nodes and Edges sheets) be uploaded to the repository?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23850,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 13:47:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 13:47:33 UTC"},{"id":3098,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Deb do you have any preferences surrounding how we document?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23851,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 13:53:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 13:53:33 UTC"},{"id":3101,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Am I wrong in assuming that we wouldn't need more than 10GB for a project like this?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23853,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 13:55:47 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 13:55:47 UTC"},{"id":3102,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Deb, how do you usually go about backing-up project data when you're working?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23854,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 13:57:21 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 13:57:21 UTC"},{"id":3103,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Good question. Are we going to be working in and out of Dataverse, or will we just be uploading data to it and then working with it on our own machines or sharing through Dropbox?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23855,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 14:02:52 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 14:02:52 UTC"},{"id":3104,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Deakin is more of a question of what goes where. Are we storing Work Package 1 data there as a back-up and are we storing Work Package 2 data at the UofA?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23856,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 14:01:10 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 14:01:10 UTC"},{"id":3105,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Not sure about the final file format or whether we will be removing non-anonymized datasets from earlier in the work from the repository.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23857,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 14:08:06 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 14:08:06 UTC"},{"id":3106,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Other than the file format, I think this is accurate.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23858,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 14:10:14 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 14:10:14 UTC"},{"id":3107,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Deb, do you have any thoughts on this?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23859,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 14:10:54 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 14:10:54 UTC"},{"id":3108,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Do you have any thoughts on this Deb?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23860,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 14:12:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 14:12:58 UTC"},{"id":3110,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Given the relatively short span of time between receiving the data and using it for Work Package 1, this shouldn't be too much of an issue.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23862,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 14:19:21 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 14:19:21 UTC"},{"id":3112,"user_id":18741,"text":"<p>Deb, this is where a greenhorn like me would really like to have your insights. I imagine talking with James might help in answering this question as well.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":23864,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2020-12-07 14:38:37 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-07 14:38:37 UTC"},{"id":3160,"user_id":19517,"text":"<p>Not sure what naming convention you'll be using for youth interviews.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":24565,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-02-19 18:52:07 UTC","updated_at":"2021-02-19 18:52:07 UTC"},{"id":3161,"user_id":2812,"text":"<p>test</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19151,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-02 18:12:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-02 18:12:50 UTC"},{"id":3162,"user_id":3451,"text":"<p>Louise - please elaborate.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":24924,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-04 16:56:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-04 16:56:01 UTC"},{"id":3163,"user_id":3473,"text":"<p>Note, interviewees will be asked about any learning objects/artifacts. Unfortunately, this data will not be shared in the transcript if it refers to an institution-specific tutorial that would identify the speaker.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25236,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-10 20:51:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-10 20:51:12 UTC"},{"id":3164,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is a comment/question.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":25310,"archived_by":20435,"created_at":"2021-03-16 17:51:18 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-16 23:01:49 UTC"},{"id":3165,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>Is there a handy chart for proprietary to open source file formats?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25311,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-16 18:06:30 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-16 18:06:30 UTC"},{"id":3166,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>Would an answer like this be acceptable?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25313,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-16 18:24:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-16 18:24:47 UTC"},{"id":3167,"user_id":6077,"text":"<p>We have to speak about the data we are collecting - essentially the questions we are asking in the survey.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":25527,"archived_by":20524,"created_at":"2021-03-24 03:42:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-27 14:44:39 UTC"},{"id":3168,"user_id":6077,"text":"<p>We only need to speak about the fiel formats - don't need to mention password protection or Qualtrics.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25528,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-24 03:43:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-24 03:43:47 UTC"},{"id":3169,"user_id":4554,"text":"<p>Version ctrl is most effectively done with software. Since OSF is being used, I would also consider describing its use here as well.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We should consider changing the question to include software.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25312,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-26 23:28:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-26 23:28:01 UTC"},{"id":3170,"user_id":4554,"text":"<p>i wouldn't necessarily call these handy charts, but LAC's local digital format registry has good tables (see 3 and 4) and good descriptions of formats: http://www.councilofnsarchives.ca/sites/default/files/LAC%20File%20Format%20Guidelines%20for%20Preservation%20and%20Long-term%20v1_2010-12_0.pdf&nbsp;</p>\n<p>LoC is good too: https://www.loc.gov/preservation/resources/rfs/RFS%202020-2021.pdf</p>\n<p>The UK Data Service's table is cleaner but not as extensive: https://www.ukdataservice.ac.uk/manage-data/format/recommended-formats</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25311,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-26 23:35:19 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-26 23:35:19 UTC"},{"id":3171,"user_id":4554,"text":"<p>Yes.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I would also include a description of the the training documentation, and specify that the consent forms will be kept.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The question isn't limited to documentation that will be shared publicly. The consent forms will need to be kept to understand the conditions around data sharing and reuse, which could vary for each participant depending on how the form is shaped.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Training documentation might explain issues encountered with the data or assumptions that need to be made.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25313,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-26 23:41:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-26 23:41:47 UTC"},{"id":3172,"user_id":4554,"text":"<p>For this question here i would think about the workflow the data goes through and how much curation is going to be applied to the data that will be shared. For e.g. is it just the quantitative data, or are qualitative data going to be output from the database as well? Are data going to be coded or standardized? You describe below that there will be anonymization procedures, so that implies some kind of processing. Are you only going to share the segments of the data underlying findings presented in publications, or are you going to share the entire database?, etc...</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25322,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-26 23:51:34 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-26 23:51:34 UTC"},{"id":3173,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Does it look like you can download the data? Would that mean you could re-use the data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25748,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-30 16:33:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-30 16:33:47 UTC"},{"id":3174,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Would you want to write a codebook that would tell others what data was included in each section? Or what the variables would mean?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Did they include a codebook in the dataset?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25759,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-30 16:35:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-30 16:35:12 UTC"},{"id":3175,"user_id":20556,"text":"<p>test124</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25760,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-03-30 17:51:41 UTC","updated_at":"2021-03-30 17:51:41 UTC"},{"id":3176,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Great catch - without a codebook, data sets can be misinterpreted or just unreadable.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25967,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:24:00 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:24:00 UTC"},{"id":3177,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Sensitive data could also refer to protect species or protected land that requires controlled access to information. But good observations there.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25742,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:25:42 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:25:42 UTC"},{"id":3178,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Expanding on that could be to have a set schedule for collection that is maintained as well as a schedule for deposit into the repository.</p>\n<p>Consistency could depend on the codebook, which as you've already mentioned, doesn't appear to be present.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25749,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:27:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:27:50 UTC"},{"id":3179,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>This project also looks like it's a long-term project. How long has it been going? What do you think that means for the storage needs?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25751,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:28:35 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:28:35 UTC"},{"id":3180,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Maybe a bit more elaboration here. Who would need to access the whole dataset (principal investigator, graduate assistants etc.?) or who would have restricted access? Restricted access could also mean the current researchers could not go back and change the old data sets but could only add new ones.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25756,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:30:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:30:12 UTC"},{"id":3181,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>NSSDCA is a great archival option! For large data sets from Canadian institutions we also have the Federated Research Data Repository.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25780,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:37:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:37:20 UTC"},{"id":3182,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>This is a really good option, intranets are secure and can allow for different levels of access.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25745,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:40:00 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:40:00 UTC"},{"id":3183,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Yes, data registries and repositories are excellent ways to make your data visible - especially is the metadata is coded well and tagged appropriately.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25754,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:41:00 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:41:00 UTC"},{"id":3184,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Will this be recorded as excel files? Word files?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":25721,"archived_by":4993,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:42:54 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:43:08 UTC"},{"id":3185,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Having a workflow that includes multiple eyes looking over something is really valuable. Especially if you have your naming conventions firmly established.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25726,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:44:16 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:44:16 UTC"},{"id":3186,"user_id":4993,"text":"<p>Having something offsite is valuable as well. Very appropriate in a pandemic when you suddenly lose access to a location.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25731,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-01 16:45:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-01 16:45:31 UTC"},{"id":3187,"user_id":20617,"text":"<p>Should I write anything about data sensitivity here?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":26447,"archived_by":20628,"created_at":"2021-04-09 15:25:11 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-14 12:30:57 UTC"},{"id":3188,"user_id":20617,"text":"<p>Lisa I think the focus group discussion will be video. In that case I can remove 'audio' from the answer to this question.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":26449,"archived_by":20628,"created_at":"2021-04-09 15:27:36 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-14 12:31:48 UTC"},{"id":3189,"user_id":20617,"text":"<p>Lisa do you think 10 GB is the right answer?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":26452,"archived_by":20617,"created_at":"2021-04-09 15:32:55 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-14 14:32:55 UTC"},{"id":3190,"user_id":20629,"text":"<p>Potential: Pictures, and secondary data including text descriptions, photos, Excel spreadsheets, charts, graphs and diagrams.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26523,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-09 20:08:54 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-09 20:08:54 UTC"},{"id":3191,"user_id":20629,"text":"<p>Potential: Secondary data including text descriptions, photos, Excel spreadsheets, charts, graphs and diagrams.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26524,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-09 20:14:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-09 20:14:37 UTC"},{"id":3192,"user_id":20629,"text":"<p>Anything missing? I'm open to suggestions. Thanks.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26547,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-09 21:54:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-09 21:54:10 UTC"},{"id":3193,"user_id":20628,"text":"<p>Madhu - is this data that will be included in the storage? If so, it will be transcripts of audiorecordings of the focus groups. We won't store the videos of the group.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":26449,"archived_by":20617,"created_at":"2021-04-14 12:32:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-14 14:31:13 UTC"},{"id":3194,"user_id":20628,"text":"<p>I have absolutely no idea but I feel like 10GB is too much so I have halved it. If we are not storing video recordings of the focus groups, it won't be as much space that is needed.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":26452,"archived_by":20617,"created_at":"2021-04-14 12:34:04 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-14 14:33:56 UTC"},{"id":3195,"user_id":8768,"text":"<p>Only the relevent experimental data will be shared with the industrial partner by PI. Data aquired from 3rd party and industrial partner will only be shared with mutual conscent.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Non shareble data will be stored and kept protected with PI - Dr. Dutta&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26844,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-16 16:35:52 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-20 16:57:14 UTC"},{"id":3196,"user_id":8768,"text":"<p>n/a</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26856,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-16 16:53:55 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-16 16:53:55 UTC"},{"id":3197,"user_id":8768,"text":"<p>n/a</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26856,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-16 16:59:38 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-16 16:59:38 UTC"},{"id":3198,"user_id":20653,"text":"<p>How I defined/distinguish between the different data types:</p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">\n<li>Numeric - data quantified into numbers and recorded in physical or digital files</li>\n<li>Image - data used to graphically or pictorially represent information and often recorded in physical or digital files</li>\n<li>Audio - &nbsp;auditory data often recorded using digital auditory processes and files</li>\n<li>Video - continuous visual signals that are recorded digitally</li>\n<li>Text - data that is qualitatively expressed with written words in physical or digital files</li>\n<li>Tabular data - data expressed in a table format containing quantitative and/or qualitative information about a subject(s) and recorded in physical or digital files</li>\n<li>Modeling - data used to describe relationships or attributes of entities and can be physical or digital files</li>\n<li>Spatial - data about an object represented in a digital geospatial file&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Instrumentation - data of the processes the investigator(s) use to collect other forms of data can be physical or digitally recorded</li>\n</ul>","archived":0,"answer_id":26883,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-17 14:26:49 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-17 14:26:49 UTC"},{"id":3199,"user_id":20701,"text":"<p>What does \"link to\" refer to?</p>\n<p>Will we be creating tabular data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27193,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-29 19:16:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-29 20:00:13 UTC"},{"id":3200,"user_id":20701,"text":"<p>Will we be collecting data as XML?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27194,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-29 20:01:42 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-29 20:01:42 UTC"},{"id":3201,"user_id":20701,"text":"<p>Would this be for all documentation or just where the data is presented? Also, how much and what types of documentation will there be?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27195,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-29 20:32:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-29 20:32:31 UTC"},{"id":3202,"user_id":20701,"text":"<p>Will we be using a metadata standard? The resource only provided information about metadata standards for XML.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27282,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-29 20:48:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-30 13:52:36 UTC"},{"id":3203,"user_id":20701,"text":"<p>Would CSV ensure file integrity?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27200,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-04-30 14:10:02 UTC","updated_at":"2021-04-30 14:10:02 UTC"},{"id":3204,"user_id":18033,"text":"<p>Yes I think it's fair to say that we'll create tabular data.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Link to</em> probably refers to when researchers don't actually collect their own data, but use data that has already been collected by someone else and made available for use in a data repository.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27193,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-03 17:17:55 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-03 17:17:55 UTC"},{"id":3205,"user_id":18033,"text":"<p>I don't think so, but when we connect with the Opinio rep we can confirm.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27194,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-03 17:19:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-03 17:19:15 UTC"},{"id":3206,"user_id":18033,"text":"<p>Fantastic! I love this!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27280,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-03 17:20:07 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-03 17:20:07 UTC"},{"id":3207,"user_id":18033,"text":"<p>We probably won't use one, so we can leave this blank.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27282,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-03 18:04:13 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-03 18:04:13 UTC"},{"id":3208,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is an instil comment.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":27474,"archived_by":20435,"created_at":"2021-05-04 23:23:03 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-04 23:23:17 UTC"},{"id":3209,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is an insightful comment.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27474,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-04 23:23:26 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-04 23:23:26 UTC"},{"id":3210,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>@Andrea - I could add a *lot more* here, but my sense is that this isn't required.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27342,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-09 22:03:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-09 22:03:50 UTC"},{"id":3211,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>I really have no idea how to estimate this. A guide would be helpful (every hour of audio recording in mp3 etc). For the purposes of an example, I am not going to hunt down that information.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27350,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-09 22:32:04 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-09 22:32:04 UTC"},{"id":3212,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>Hi Andrea. Is there a resource that lists what are preservation friendly formats for Word, Excel, and mp3 files?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":27358,"archived_by":20732,"created_at":"2021-05-09 22:40:36 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-18 15:57:41 UTC"},{"id":3213,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>Beyond deleting this, I truly don't know what steps are involved. Is there an REB guideline to consult?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27360,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-09 22:42:19 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-09 22:42:19 UTC"},{"id":3214,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>Andrea: need guidelines to know what to write here b/c I don't understand how repositories like DataVerse work. Is the suggestion that everything will be in Dataverse, but under different level of protections? What's the language?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27372,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-09 23:23:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 22:05:42 UTC"},{"id":3215,"user_id":18033,"text":"<p>Great questions. Documentation applies to collected data that has been unprocessed; in other words, the data files that we will export from Opinio. Our documentation would be very important if we were going to make our unprocessed data available to other researchers in a data repository, as we would want to make sure that they interpret our data correctly.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We will still definitely want to work documentation into our own project. I'm not sure how much and what types there will be, but the categories you've noted are excellent! We'll start with those.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27195,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 16:56:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 16:56:43 UTC"},{"id":3216,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>I would agree with these additional data types. Please add them.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26523,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 18:48:00 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 18:48:00 UTC"},{"id":3217,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>Think ahead to your thesis: what do you think your supplementary material you will be publishing with it (or any article). Would it include secondary data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26524,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 18:50:35 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 18:50:35 UTC"},{"id":3218,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>As per my comments in Data Collection Q2, consider what documentation would be required to understand/reuse any final products included in your thesis? Not clear here what your final products are.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":26547,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 18:52:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 18:52:37 UTC"},{"id":3219,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>This is discussing naming conventions you may be using to consistently track and manage all products. E.g. can you recognize files are the consent forms from the file names?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27870,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 18:54:11 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 18:57:01 UTC"},{"id":3220,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>This resource may be helpful for indigenous naming/metadata in your research description: https://indigenouslis.ca/the-use-our-words-toolkit/</p>\n<p>Also, this is the schema for GIS data: https://www.fgdc.gov/metadata/csdgm/organization.html</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27871,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 19:05:56 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 19:05:56 UTC"},{"id":3221,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>Instead of Sociological abstracts (which isn't a schema), consider this one: https://www.icpsr.umich.edu/web/ICPSR/thesaurus/index . Subject thesaurus.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27345,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 22:48:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 22:48:12 UTC"},{"id":3222,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>Just need an estimate range for this: see this calculator https://www.colincrawley.com/audio-file-size-calculator/ as example for 1 recording then x by the number of interviews. Likely the audio would be the biggest file size other than Nvivo files.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27350,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 23:07:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 23:07:12 UTC"},{"id":3223,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>Here's what I would recommend:</p>\n<p>.docx = .pdf, .rtf&nbsp;</p>\n<p>.xlsx = .csv</p>\n<p>.mp3 = already an open, preservation format</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":27358,"archived_by":20732,"created_at":"2021-05-11 23:11:51 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-18 15:57:28 UTC"},{"id":3224,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>Best to give the date here that you gave the REB.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27359,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 23:12:28 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 23:12:28 UTC"},{"id":3225,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>I wish re: REB guideline.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It will depend on the medium. For network stored files, I am not sure what processes IST would take to truly 'wipe' backup files that they make.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27360,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 23:15:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 23:15:25 UTC"},{"id":3226,"user_id":4823,"text":"<p>I think what is required here is the REB you applied to for your research, the ID for approval. If your co-I needed ethics approval at their institution, it should also be stated here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27363,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-11 23:18:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-11 23:18:20 UTC"},{"id":3227,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is an insightful comment.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27979,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-17 17:20:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-17 17:20:10 UTC"},{"id":3228,"user_id":5957,"text":"<p>Please use the following files in BaseCamp: OFI Mod E - Ecosystem Indicators:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>README_template.docx</li>\n<li>Dara_Dictonary_template.xlsx</li>\n</ul>","archived":0,"answer_id":27985,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-18 11:23:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-18 11:23:10 UTC"},{"id":3229,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>I'm afraid that's a level of technical language I don't understand fully. As we move forward with this, researchers will need a guide that's super easy to calculate with. Otherwise, people will estimate this poorly. I've done a rough sketch here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27350,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-18 15:31:07 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-18 15:52:46 UTC"},{"id":3230,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>Researchers will need to have a readily accessible link to a document that shows what is preservation ready.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27358,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-18 15:58:04 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-18 15:58:04 UTC"},{"id":3231,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>Ok. I'll leave this blank then, for now. Researchers will need an easily linked document outlining what these processes are from IST, to copy and paste (or, if the system can automate this, once it knows our university, even better).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27360,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-18 15:59:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-18 15:59:45 UTC"},{"id":3232,"user_id":20732,"text":"<p>Need to align standards with research paradigm (ie, Lincoln &amp; Guba is not exhaustive on paradigms used for qualitative research)<br /><br />This required pulling together different pieces not already clearly in one place.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27343,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-18 17:29:56 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-18 17:29:56 UTC"},{"id":3233,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>bb</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":28029,"archived_by":20810,"created_at":"2021-05-26 10:01:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-26 10:02:06 UTC"},{"id":3234,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>Do I need to elaborate about the purpose of data collection.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28029,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-26 19:07:08 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-26 19:07:08 UTC"},{"id":3235,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>I'm confused about it, our transcripts and coding will be longitudinally</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28058,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-26 19:33:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-26 19:33:47 UTC"},{"id":3236,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>I guess we need to change the tentative dates (June- February 2021)??</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28059,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-26 19:37:54 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-26 19:37:54 UTC"},{"id":3237,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>Should we include the document like protocol, interview guides along with our response?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28082,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-26 23:32:32 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-26 23:32:32 UTC"},{"id":3238,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>how should I include the versions for different softwares? Should I use the latest versions for all of them ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28083,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-26 23:39:03 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-26 23:40:22 UTC"},{"id":3239,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>I'm little confused about this one.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28084,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-26 23:41:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-26 23:41:10 UTC"},{"id":3240,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>I just gathered this information through our discussions and meetings so far. Please let me know how I should edit this section.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28085,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 00:22:56 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 00:22:56 UTC"},{"id":3241,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>We are going to use all these formats during our process of data collection and analysis....??</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28087,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 00:26:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 00:26:25 UTC"},{"id":3242,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>Should we include our code book ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28088,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 00:31:44 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 00:31:44 UTC"},{"id":3243,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>This is perfect. No need to elaborate on purpose of data collection (since that is in the ethics application/protocol)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28029,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:49:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:49:17 UTC"},{"id":3244,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>Correct, but we are only meeting with participants at a single point in time (not following up with them over time)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28058,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:50:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:50:01 UTC"},{"id":3245,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>Good idea</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28059,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:50:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:50:15 UTC"},{"id":3246,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>I don't think so? I think a data management plan is more about the overall plan on how we are going to collect/store/analyze/maintain the data. And the screening tools/interview guides are kept as part of the data collection tools. But this might be a good question for one of the Dal Librarians. Are we supposed to attach data collection items to the DMP?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28082,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:52:35 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:52:35 UTC"},{"id":3247,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>Yes, just latest version of each.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28083,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:53:03 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:53:03 UTC"},{"id":3248,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>I think the following:</p>\n<p>word documents for transcripts (.doc)</p>\n<p>Audio files for interviews (.m4a)</p>\n<p>Nvivo for analyis (.nvp)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28084,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:54:38 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:54:38 UTC"},{"id":3249,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>This is great. I wonder if we should also have a master excel sheet where we keep track of the different versions of REB amendments and list what changes we made?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Similar sheet could be maintained for data - when we change something, we record in the master sheet so it is clearly documented?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>(I see this mentioned below that you have a log book for changes - great idea!!)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28085,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:56:30 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:58:32 UTC"},{"id":3250,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>I removed a couple and added nvivo and audio&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28087,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:57:22 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:57:22 UTC"},{"id":3251,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>We won't have it developed as of yet, but a good idea to mention it here&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28088,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 10:57:54 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 10:57:54 UTC"},{"id":3252,"user_id":20809,"text":"<p>This one is focused on the trustworthiness of qualitative data. I've added a few</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28089,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 11:02:06 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 11:02:06 UTC"},{"id":3253,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>Should I mention about zoom and audio recorders as wee?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28096,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 15:04:11 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 15:04:11 UTC"},{"id":3254,"user_id":20821,"text":"<p>.vtt can this be converted to another file type? or should it be? Maybe convert to .txt?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28127,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 18:30:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 18:30:50 UTC"},{"id":3255,"user_id":20821,"text":"<p>ask Allison about this</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28129,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 20:04:41 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 20:04:41 UTC"},{"id":3256,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>Should I include all the team members here ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28160,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-27 23:56:42 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-27 23:56:42 UTC"},{"id":3257,"user_id":20810,"text":"<p>I guess it will open access ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28167,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-05-28 15:29:46 UTC","updated_at":"2021-05-28 15:29:46 UTC"},{"id":3258,"user_id":10307,"text":"<p>Aucun choix quant au format original des donn&eacute;es re&ccedil;ues.</p>\n<p>Des logiciels, tel que FME Quick Translator permettent le changement de format des donn&eacute;es.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28462,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-07 18:15:18 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 18:15:18 UTC"},{"id":3259,"user_id":10307,"text":"<p>Des m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es internes seront ajout&eacute;es lorsque n&eacute;cessaire pour une meilleure compr&eacute;hension des collections.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":28463,"archived_by":10307,"created_at":"2021-06-07 18:21:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 18:55:23 UTC"},{"id":3260,"user_id":10307,"text":"<p>La description de nos collections int&eacute;gr&eacute;es dans G&eacute;oindex est bas&eacute;e sur la norme ISO 19115 Profil nord-am&eacute;ricain.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28465,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-07 18:59:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 18:59:59 UTC"},{"id":3261,"user_id":20801,"text":"<p>Title is tentative.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28490,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-08 21:21:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-08 21:21:25 UTC"},{"id":3262,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is an insightful comment.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28590,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-08 21:23:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-08 21:23:59 UTC"},{"id":3263,"user_id":20843,"text":"<p>There is also the option of having a designated laptop/camera/phone etc. that is password encrypted, but that might get complicated with the 'trans-Atlantic aspect of the project.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28606,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-09 15:16:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-09 15:16:31 UTC"},{"id":3264,"user_id":20843,"text":"<p>Not too sure (maybe 500 GBs?)- This will really depend if we have a lot of video or audio recordings.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28607,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-09 15:19:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-09 15:19:10 UTC"},{"id":3265,"user_id":20843,"text":"<p>Added dropbox - but we can definitely change this if we wanted to move to a more advanced and secure software</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28608,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-09 15:23:35 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-09 15:23:35 UTC"},{"id":3266,"user_id":20745,"text":"<p>&agrave; ajouter plus d'info</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28694,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-10 14:08:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 14:08:15 UTC"},{"id":3267,"user_id":20745,"text":"<p>ISO 19115 (&agrave; v&eacute;rifier)</p>\n<p>V&eacute;rifier si on inclus les list P01, P02 .... (pour BODC)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28699,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-10 14:24:44 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 14:26:22 UTC"},{"id":3268,"user_id":20745,"text":"<p>a</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":28700,"archived_by":20745,"created_at":"2021-06-10 15:01:52 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 15:02:02 UTC"},{"id":3269,"user_id":20745,"text":"<p>- garder l'id&eacute;e &agrave; avoir un troisi&egrave;me copie (backup).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- comment l'&eacute;quipe interne Amundsen peut acceder, modifier, collaborer sur les donn&eacute;es.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28702,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-10 17:28:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 17:36:40 UTC"},{"id":3270,"user_id":20745,"text":"<p>Donn&eacute;es CTD du Laurier. &Agrave; consid&eacute;rer vu que Amundsen l'utilise pour le calibrage des instrument des mouillages.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>NB: Amundsen ne les publie pas, mais seulement les a en stockage.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28458,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-16 14:04:03 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-16 14:04:03 UTC"},{"id":3271,"user_id":9156,"text":"<p>we must re-draft this. here are the guidance.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15531,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-16 15:39:58 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-16 15:39:58 UTC"},{"id":3272,"user_id":9156,"text":"<p>same here</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-16 15:40:07 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-16 15:40:07 UTC"},{"id":3273,"user_id":10989,"text":"<p>@ben what is this?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28966,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-16 15:51:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-16 15:51:59 UTC"},{"id":3274,"user_id":20908,"text":"<p>I have gong through each section (except the last two) and added a few words making the English flow a little more. Not yet had a chance to look at the last two sections, however. About to go into meetings until we meet at 1.30pm UK time. I think we're looking good! Best wishes, Steve</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-17 07:39:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-17 07:39:31 UTC"},{"id":3275,"user_id":20931,"text":"<p>What do we write here? We are confused. </p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29318,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-18 15:28:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-18 15:47:35 UTC"},{"id":3276,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Indiquer que ce sont des enregistrements audio</p>\n<p>Utiliser cette information dans le 2 pages &agrave; remettre</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15514,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 11:29:14 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:00:29 UTC"},{"id":3277,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>J'enl&egrave;verais ce qui est en gras, c'est d&eacute;j&agrave; tr&egrave;s clair dans le premier paragraphe.</p>\n<p>Je vois deux options pour la partie apr&egrave;s le gras : apporter des pr&eacute;cisions (de quel type de format il s'agit lorsqu'il est question de raw data, de coded data, etc.?) ou l'enlever.</p>\n<p>Autre possibilit&eacute; : si dans le projet export&eacute; par NVivo il y a d'autres formats que ceux pr&eacute;cis&eacute;s au d&eacute;but, les ajouter ici puis d&eacute;placer ceux deux paragraphes dans la section \"partage et r&eacute;utilisation\" &agrave; la question 1.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15515,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 11:29:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 11:29:24 UTC"},{"id":3278,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Ajouter lien vers la convention UBC.</p>\n<p>J'enl&egrave;verais ce que j'ai mis entre ** sinon il faut expliquer ce qu'est Valeria et ce serait mieux plus loin.</p>\n<p>Ajouter que les r&egrave;gles de nommage et d'organisation seront partag&eacute;es &agrave; l'ensemble de l'&eacute;quipe.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15516,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 11:34:30 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 11:34:30 UTC"},{"id":3279,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>D&eacute;finir PI et RPI.</p>\n<p>Ajouter ref. au README qui servira &agrave; d&eacute;finir les variables et qui est mentionn&eacute; dans la section 1 question 3.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15517,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 11:49:06 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 11:49:06 UTC"},{"id":3280,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Since the data will be in Dataverse, you can add the DDI (Data Documentation Initiative) schema (https://ddialliance.org/) which is used by Dataverse</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15519,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 11:54:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 18:23:20 UTC"},{"id":3281,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Add a short description of what is VALERIA and the link (https://valeria.science/).</p>\n<p>Specify that it is the UL Dataverse.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15520,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 11:58:26 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 11:58:26 UTC"},{"id":3282,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>A summary of this information would be useful in the 2 pager (just to say that the information shared is secured)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15518,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:01:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:01:47 UTC"},{"id":3283,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>If the 3-2-1 rule is mentionned, you have to explain what it means (you can also remove the reference, all the other pertinent information follows).</p>\n<p>I would delete the mention (X:Drive) and U:, it's not understandable for someone outside what it means.</p>\n<p>What I put between ** I would transfert it in the next question</p>\n<p>RPI and PI should be define (and everywhere else they appears)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15521,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:10:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:45:45 UTC"},{"id":3284,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>I would delete the part in bold.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15522,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:12:41 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:12:41 UTC"},{"id":3285,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>All of it should be in the 2 pager.</p>\n<p>Specify UL DATAVERSE.</p>\n<p>The format should be in the next question.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15523,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:27:13 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:27:13 UTC"},{"id":3286,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>If possible, add link to the UK guidelines?</p>\n<p>You could just say that you will use means and software to anonymise data, but more information is ok too.</p>\n<p>If possible, add that all petinent informations about data (what will be necessary to understand it) will be collected and will stay attach to the data until the deposit.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15524,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:33:55 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:33:55 UTC"},{"id":3287,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>In the two pager</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15525,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:34:49 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:34:49 UTC"},{"id":3288,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>If possible add a link to the description of the licence.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28964,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:35:23 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:35:23 UTC"},{"id":3289,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>In the two pager.</p>\n<p>Speficy UL DATAVERSE.</p>\n<p>The metadata of DATAVERSE is harversted by repositories including the Federated Research Data Repository (FRDR), a point of access to discover canadian data (https://www.frdr-dfdr.ca/)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15526,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:39:48 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:39:48 UTC"},{"id":3290,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>In the two pager</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15527,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:47:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:47:05 UTC"},{"id":3291,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>In the two pager</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15528,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 12:47:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 12:47:31 UTC"},{"id":3292,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Dataverse is paid by the library.</p>\n<p>I often see 10% of someone salary for data management during the project.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15529,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 13:03:52 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 13:03:52 UTC"},{"id":3293,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>You can add that the research was approuved by ethics comitee, that participants will signed informed consent and mention somewhere DGPR.</p>\n<p>For UL, technically, data is own by the university but I don't think it matters here...</p>\n<p>In the two pager.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 13:11:53 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 13:11:53 UTC"},{"id":3294,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>All this information should be at the previous question.</p>\n<p>Here, you can just say that no sensible data will be shared so there won't be secondary use of them, The sensible data will be destroyed after X years.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":15531,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-22 13:15:44 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-22 13:15:44 UTC"},{"id":3295,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p>Will video or audio be recorded?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29405,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-23 21:35:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-23 21:35:05 UTC"},{"id":3296,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is an insightful comment.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29410,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-24 17:26:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-24 17:26:24 UTC"},{"id":3297,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>I would suggest that here you use something like:</p>\n<p>Throm_ProjectName_Topic/Aspect_Typeoffile_YYYY_MM_DD</p>\n<p>Throm_LengthofStay_DaysbyCondition_rawdata_2018_05_21</p>\n<p>Throm_LengthofStay_DaysbyCondition_Deidentifieddata_2018_05_21</p>\n<p>(Obviously if you decide the aspects of the name convention they will make more sense)</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":29521,"archived_by":2916,"created_at":"2021-06-29 15:59:30 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-30 14:12:46 UTC"},{"id":3298,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>I suspect this will not be super large based on the file formats you have. But you will want to provide at least a rough estimate of how much data there will be overall, and then in each subproject plan you can give an estimate for that plan.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29503,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-29 18:05:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-29 18:05:25 UTC"},{"id":3299,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>I would suggest that you plan to move the data to MUN OneDrive once it is available so that everyone can access it all in one place. The NLCHI data will likely have to stay at Eastern health locations.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You may also plan to move to CHIA, based on future discussions with Don Bryant</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29504,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-29 18:07:07 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-29 18:07:07 UTC"},{"id":3300,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>In the specific DMPs for each subproject, you would put which specific data you are using for this subproject.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29495,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-30 14:11:28 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-30 14:11:28 UTC"},{"id":3301,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>Needs to be answered. This will take some discussion on your part to decide how you are going to do this. Who will be responsible?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29527,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-30 14:17:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-30 14:17:15 UTC"},{"id":3302,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>This metadata is basic citation metadata that many repositories collect. It describes how to access the data and what the data covers, when and how it was collected, etc.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29529,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-30 14:18:13 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-30 14:18:13 UTC"},{"id":3303,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>Suggestion:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>OneDrive (once it is available) Indicate who will have what kind of access (read only, edit, etc.)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29523,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-30 14:23:02 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-30 14:23:02 UTC"},{"id":3304,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>List specific responsibilities that each team member will hold.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29522,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-06-30 17:41:57 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-30 17:41:57 UTC"},{"id":3305,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>James' comment: we can talk about this one a bit more, and I have some examples and resources that I can provide which may be hepful</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":29771,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-08 15:07:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-08 15:07:31 UTC"},{"id":3306,"user_id":20858,"text":"<p>please add about producer participants!</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":29927,"archived_by":20858,"created_at":"2021-07-09 19:36:36 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-29 15:58:59 UTC"},{"id":3307,"user_id":20858,"text":"<p>add how many times you think the producers will measure</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":29931,"archived_by":20858,"created_at":"2021-07-09 19:42:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-29 15:53:04 UTC"},{"id":3308,"user_id":20858,"text":"<p>right now it is google drive.../I'm not sure if the unviersity will like this but we can try.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":29933,"archived_by":20858,"created_at":"2021-07-09 19:43:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-29 15:54:19 UTC"},{"id":3309,"user_id":20858,"text":"<p>we need to specify how it is backed up. (ie. hard drive, one drive, google</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":29934,"archived_by":20858,"created_at":"2021-07-09 19:44:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-29 15:58:44 UTC"},{"id":3310,"user_id":20858,"text":"<p>feel free to refine. this is rather generic</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":29935,"archived_by":20858,"created_at":"2021-07-09 19:44:58 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-29 15:55:55 UTC"},{"id":3311,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Hey Bob!&nbsp; We have project initiating data, right?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30000,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-13 20:27:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-13 20:27:15 UTC"},{"id":3312,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is an insightful comment.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30024,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-14 18:26:57 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-14 18:26:57 UTC"},{"id":3313,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Do we have project initiating data?!!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30258,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-19 01:19:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-19 01:19:15 UTC"},{"id":3314,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Anything to add?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30259,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-19 01:21:06 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-19 01:21:06 UTC"},{"id":3315,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Do we actually have any project initiating data?!!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30267,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-19 13:29:19 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-19 13:29:19 UTC"},{"id":3316,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Do we have any project initiating data?!!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30271,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-19 13:53:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-19 13:53:24 UTC"},{"id":3317,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Do we have project initiating data?!!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30274,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-19 14:30:00 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-19 14:30:00 UTC"},{"id":3318,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Do we have this data type??</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30278,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-20 13:33:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-20 13:33:10 UTC"},{"id":3319,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Do we have any project initiating data?!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30281,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-20 18:31:53 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-20 18:31:53 UTC"},{"id":3320,"user_id":13643,"text":"<p>Do we have any project initiating data?!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30284,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-20 19:25:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-20 19:25:59 UTC"},{"id":3321,"user_id":20977,"text":"<p>The research technician accesses, modifies and contributes data <strong>only</strong> to the I:drive version. The copies on our desktop computers and the external hard drive are updated by automatic backups occur every Friday afternoon.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30312,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-22 13:20:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-22 13:20:37 UTC"},{"id":3322,"user_id":20977,"text":"<p>Crop injury and weed control data are collected by the research technician, according to this Excel schedule, dry weight data are collected by the summer students under the supervision of the technician, and yield data are&nbsp; collected by created by the technician and summer students. Data are collected by hand, on prepared data collected sheets that are generated by ARM. The data are then entered into each .dat file in ARM.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30312,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-22 13:26:26 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-22 13:26:26 UTC"},{"id":3323,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30486,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-28 22:27:21 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-28 22:27:21 UTC"},{"id":3324,"user_id":20854,"text":"<p>Test feedback.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30487,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-07-29 03:06:02 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-29 03:06:02 UTC"},{"id":3325,"user_id":21000,"text":"<p>Not sure about LOC</p>\n<p><input id=\"idg-io-safe-browsing-enabled\" type=\"hidden\" /></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30549,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-03 00:53:42 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-03 00:53:42 UTC"},{"id":3326,"user_id":21000,"text":"<p>Not sure here. We don't hold copyright to most of the materials that will be shared. Do we need as we include materials to get the copyright owners to indicate what type of license their data should have?</p>\n<p>Should the interviews be free under CC?</p>\n<p><input id=\"idg-io-safe-browsing-enabled\" type=\"hidden\" /></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30558,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-03 02:09:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-03 02:09:17 UTC"},{"id":3327,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>this is an insightful comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30567,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-03 17:04:30 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-03 17:04:30 UTC"},{"id":3328,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30568,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-03 17:08:07 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-03 17:08:07 UTC"},{"id":3329,"user_id":21000,"text":"<p>Not sure what to write here</p>\n<p><input id=\"idg-io-safe-browsing-enabled\" type=\"hidden\" /></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30572,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-04 01:51:14 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-04 01:51:14 UTC"},{"id":3330,"user_id":21005,"text":"<p>It sounds like licensing (even it you want the data public domain) is becoming more encouraged and common, but not strictly necessary yet, so I put NA. I may have to read up on this a bit more though.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30648,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-05 18:51:38 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-05 18:51:38 UTC"},{"id":3331,"user_id":21005,"text":"<p>I should probably insert actual coordinates of of the sites.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30547,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-05 19:40:03 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-05 19:40:03 UTC"},{"id":3332,"user_id":21005,"text":"<p>I am not certain of the difference between \"metadata\" and \"documentation\" mentioned above.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30662,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-05 19:50:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-05 19:50:01 UTC"},{"id":3333,"user_id":20966,"text":"<p>For data produced by GEOS-Chem, this is done automatically. For other data, I will need to add the metadata as part of the file creation, but this is not difficult.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30398,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-09 18:17:02 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-09 18:17:02 UTC"},{"id":3334,"user_id":20966,"text":"<p>What I describe for the GEOS-Chem output either is done automatically, or follows the default folder names.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30399,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-09 18:18:29 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-09 18:18:29 UTC"},{"id":3335,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>- Look into how POmax is measured using the GXT</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":30829,"archived_by":21070,"created_at":"2021-08-11 16:53:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-16 15:39:13 UTC"},{"id":3336,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>- Double check that both the 20% and the 80% GNG was used. If not, what was used?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":30829,"archived_by":21070,"created_at":"2021-08-11 17:03:39 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-11 17:36:58 UTC"},{"id":3337,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>Are we actually collecting HR during AEmod?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":30829,"archived_by":21070,"created_at":"2021-08-11 17:19:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-11 17:36:51 UTC"},{"id":3338,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>Double check the saliva sample collection times</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":30829,"archived_by":21070,"created_at":"2021-08-11 17:24:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-16 15:39:10 UTC"},{"id":3339,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>Double check that the 5th cortisol sample collection time is correct.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30829,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-16 15:46:53 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-16 15:46:53 UTC"},{"id":3340,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>I am not sure how Opinio data can be exported. I assume .csv?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":30830,"archived_by":21070,"created_at":"2021-08-16 15:47:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-16 15:51:57 UTC"},{"id":3341,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>I assume that data collected via MATLAB can be exported into XLM format, and that that is the format in which the data will be stored, but I am not sure.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30830,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-16 15:53:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-16 15:53:25 UTC"},{"id":3342,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>The DalCAB file formatting is based off the DalCAB data that Stephanie already shared with me.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The GXT and cortisol file formatting is something that I drafted.</p>\n<p>The Stroop and fNIRS and MIST file formatting will need to be checked (I do to have access to the data for the first couple of participants).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I don't know exactly how Opinio data is exported (do you export the data for each participant individually or can you export the data for multiple participants at once?). I figured that it would make sense for you to draft a file format for the Opinio data.</p>\n<p>If you think that it makes sense to change any of the formatting, then that is fine with me!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30831,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-16 16:06:11 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-16 16:06:11 UTC"},{"id":3343,"user_id":21070,"text":"<p>Note to self: The GXT stuff needs some work. I do not fully understand/ I forget all of the details regarding how that works. I need to review the forms in the lab.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30873,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-16 20:21:44 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-16 20:21:44 UTC"},{"id":3344,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>There are a few questions in these charts that will need to be answered. (for example, when you go to individual sites, you can list the names of the spaces you visited).&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30992,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-20 16:22:34 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-20 16:22:34 UTC"},{"id":3345,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>This is just a suggestion of how you might want to name your files. you can obviously change this to something that suits your needs.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30994,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-20 16:29:16 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-20 16:29:16 UTC"},{"id":3346,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>You will need to put in an estimate of the cost of hard drives and laptops if you plan on buying these for students. you may also want to consider to cost of cameras if you are buying cameras.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30997,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-23 13:28:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-23 13:28:24 UTC"},{"id":3347,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>You will need to estimate costs for laptops and hard drives here.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31004,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-23 15:19:22 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-23 15:19:22 UTC"},{"id":3348,"user_id":21086,"text":"<p>Talk to Bryan about this - not sure if there should be some identifying data to give context - e.g., co-researcher D, a Catholic chaplain</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31033,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-25 15:13:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-25 15:13:24 UTC"},{"id":3349,"user_id":21086,"text":"<p>Ask Bryan if this is applicable.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31036,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-08-25 15:14:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-25 15:14:59 UTC"},{"id":3350,"user_id":20615,"text":"<p>Je ne suis pas certaine de la r&eacute;ponse.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31356,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-15 19:16:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-15 19:16:25 UTC"},{"id":3351,"user_id":20615,"text":"<p>asbjshbc</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31358,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-15 20:02:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-15 20:02:01 UTC"},{"id":3352,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is an insightful comment.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31378,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-16 17:30:13 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-16 17:30:13 UTC"},{"id":3353,"user_id":20615,"text":"<p>jahdfv</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31394,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-17 14:52:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-17 14:52:20 UTC"},{"id":3354,"user_id":21146,"text":"<p>Just a note - which data type are numeric variables that are treated as text variables (ie. site ID #, ecoregion #, mesh filter size in &mu;m, etc.)?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31417,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-18 21:09:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-18 21:13:08 UTC"},{"id":3355,"user_id":21226,"text":"<p>Le nombre de participants et le volume des donn&eacute;es demeure &agrave; estimer</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31584,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 16:18:14 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 16:18:14 UTC"},{"id":3356,"user_id":21226,"text":"<p>Pour Github, il y a des pr&eacute;occupations d'h&eacute;bergement. On va devoir penser aux m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es ...</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31587,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 16:19:54 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 16:19:54 UTC"},{"id":3357,"user_id":21226,"text":"<p>Il faut estimer les besoins en termes d'espaces</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31589,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 16:22:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 16:22:40 UTC"},{"id":3358,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>not using one as of yet but will look into doing so</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31636,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 21:06:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 21:06:20 UTC"},{"id":3359,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>Methods and research objectives will be outlined in protocols for each institution and these protocols should be referenced in the collected data.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31633,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 21:06:30 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 21:06:30 UTC"},{"id":3360,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>Not sure how the DNA sequences will be sent and received - potentially as a Database</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31619,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 21:06:39 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 21:06:39 UTC"},{"id":3361,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>swabs/tissue needs to be linked appropriately to numeric and text data collected for each frog. This will allow future linking to the resultant DNA sequence</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31616,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 21:06:44 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 21:06:44 UTC"},{"id":3362,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>I do not know how much storage space will be required for the DNA sequences once they are returned nor who will be responsible for storing these (my school or the Toronto Zoo). Need to look into this.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Ask if Laurentian will store my data or not.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31642,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 21:32:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 21:32:24 UTC"},{"id":3363,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>Data storage and sharing is complicated by the privacy constraints of working with zoo data. Luckily most zoo data is stored on their ZIMS network and I can simply pull copies of it off to work with locally and clean locally, but I am not sure if they will require the cleaned data to be stored at the zoo or in a private database when finished. Will have to inquire.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Many collaborators means raw data is backed up in many places but I need a plan for backing up my cleaned data as well.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31643,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-22 21:41:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 21:41:25 UTC"},{"id":3364,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>Not sure if I can anonymize data from zoo animals - even using their Global Animal Number will allow tracking back to the original zoo and this may be important to keep track of anyways. Not sure if this should be anonymized.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31651,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-23 02:17:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-23 02:17:59 UTC"},{"id":3365,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>Not sure how much of the zoo animal data I will be allowed to share due to zoo privacy / confidentiality matters. This might even depend on the results (i.e. if my study conclusions cast the zoos in a poor light they should allow publishing/sharing of final results but may not allow raw data to be released)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31652,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-23 03:00:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-23 03:00:50 UTC"},{"id":3366,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>Again, not sure if the zoos will allow completely open data</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31653,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-23 03:07:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-23 03:07:50 UTC"},{"id":3367,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>data mined from ZIMS will have copyright and privacy concerns.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31616,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-24 16:32:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-24 16:32:17 UTC"},{"id":3368,"user_id":21018,"text":"<p>What are the audio file format?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30962,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-28 15:22:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-28 15:22:10 UTC"},{"id":3369,"user_id":21018,"text":"<p>Output of Altius files?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30962,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-28 15:23:57 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-28 15:23:57 UTC"},{"id":3370,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is an insightful comment.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31937,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-09-28 21:31:38 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-28 21:31:38 UTC"},{"id":3371,"user_id":21018,"text":"<p>Not sure?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32107,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-04 14:47:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 14:47:20 UTC"},{"id":3372,"user_id":21018,"text":"<p>This was a guess.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32109,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:15:23 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:15:23 UTC"},{"id":3373,"user_id":21018,"text":"<p>Thoughts?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32117,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:38:34 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:38:34 UTC"},{"id":3374,"user_id":21018,"text":"<p>Ideas of journals to publish in?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32120,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:40:26 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:40:26 UTC"},{"id":3375,"user_id":21018,"text":"<p>Do we want to use UM's Dataverse?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32115,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:42:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:42:45 UTC"},{"id":3376,"user_id":21018,"text":"<p>Is this correct?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32130,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-04 16:18:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 16:18:05 UTC"},{"id":3377,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>this is a comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32256,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-05 16:30:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-05 16:30:01 UTC"},{"id":3378,"user_id":21290,"text":"<p>Maybe there should be? E.g. Creative Commons Attribution (allows the distribution, reuse, expansion of data providing credit is given to original creators).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32434,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 01:05:41 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 01:05:41 UTC"},{"id":3379,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>My lab traditionally stores sequences on Sharcnet but I am pushing to make the sequences public through GenBank.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31650,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 02:46:02 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 02:46:02 UTC"},{"id":3380,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>Since most long-term preservation of data is being provided by other institutions (zoos or BC ministry) the associated costs will fall primarily on them and are not significantly altered by addition of my project data.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32442,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 03:51:36 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 03:51:36 UTC"},{"id":3381,"user_id":21150,"text":"<ul class=\"list-unstyled\">\n<li>\n<div class=\"display-readonly-textarea-content\">\n<p>Since most long-term preservation of data is being provided by other institutions (zoos or BC ministry) the associated costs will fall primarily on them and are not significantly altered by addition of my project data.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>","archived":0,"answer_id":32444,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 03:52:08 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 03:52:08 UTC"},{"id":3382,"user_id":21150,"text":"<p>loss of PI is a legitimate concern for this project as my principal supervisor was let go during the mass firings at Laurentian U this year. On account of this, there has already been significant discussion but he is committed to supervising the completion of the project - a \"backup\" supervisor at a partner institution has been identified as a last resort.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32446,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 03:59:22 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 03:59:22 UTC"},{"id":3383,"user_id":21293,"text":"<p>The audio recordings I have from a previous study using the recorders I have are in .WMA format, similar to .MP3&nbsp; WMA is acronym for Windows Media Audio.&nbsp; The study was done in 2014 so I have to guess the file format has evolved since then.&nbsp; If you use your iphone using the voice memo it supposedly stores them as .m4a files that you have to convert to MP3 or WAV formats.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":30962,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 18:44:16 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 18:46:02 UTC"},{"id":3384,"user_id":21293,"text":"<p>Can we add examples of what we mean?</p>\n<p>Also, I would prefer we spell out the month and add the year on the file naming convention.&nbsp; For example: 10 Sept 2021</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":31655,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 18:48:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 18:49:26 UTC"},{"id":3385,"user_id":21293,"text":"<p>We will need to ensure we clarify the units of measure used in the study.</p>\n<p>We will need a coding guide for the data we collect</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32105,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 18:53:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 18:53:47 UTC"},{"id":3386,"user_id":21293,"text":"<p>I&nbsp; only get as far as \"meta data is data about data\" and then I glaze over trying to read the explanations provided in the links...I wonder if there is a specialist that can advise us about how such a thing applies to our particular study? &nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32107,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 19:00:09 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 19:09:56 UTC"},{"id":3387,"user_id":21293,"text":"<p>It would appear, by clicking on the link in the guidance on this topic, that items on people's local laptops are being backed up and stored on dataverse (somehow).&nbsp; Having a \"cloud\" backup that is secure but only visible to the team would be good.&nbsp; We need to find out how this works...can it be like OneDrive and just constantly synching the files?&nbsp; Is it okay if the files contain participant personal information (Dataverse is on servers on our campus I think).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32108,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 19:05:38 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 19:06:00 UTC"},{"id":3388,"user_id":21293,"text":"<p>Under U of MB IP policy, the owner of the copywrite for works written or created by a University member (co-PI and graduate students) is that member. It is unclear if in this case a third party (i.e. Decor) has been granted any rights to the intellectual property developed under the study, even though they are funding it.&nbsp; Such an agreement would have had to been made in writing.&nbsp; I do not anticipate there is any monetization of the findings involved here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32117,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 19:20:27 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 19:20:27 UTC"},{"id":3389,"user_id":21293,"text":"<p>International Journal of Occupational Safety and Ergonomics</p>\n<p>The Journals of Gerontology</p>\n<p>Journal for Housing the Elderly</p>\n<p>Generations (American Society for Aging)</p>\n<p>The Gerontologist</p>\n<p>Building Research and Information (BRI)</p>\n<p>Journal of Architectural Planning Research</p>\n<p>Journal of Environmental Psychology</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32120,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 19:33:51 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 19:33:51 UTC"},{"id":3390,"user_id":21293,"text":"<p>I sure hope so because we didn't budget for it!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32130,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-07 19:53:58 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-07 19:53:58 UTC"},{"id":3391,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>helpful</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32571,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-08 17:30:38 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-08 17:30:38 UTC"},{"id":3392,"user_id":5957,"text":"<p>You can mention that you will use the Module E metadata template here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32901,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-19 18:14:46 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-19 18:14:46 UTC"},{"id":3393,"user_id":5957,"text":"<p>This is one thing that should be discussed with the data providers during the data collection. I recommend CC BY 4.0 licence, which requires others to cite you but gives them the freedom to use the data as they see fit.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32902,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-19 18:18:41 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-19 18:18:41 UTC"},{"id":3394,"user_id":21311,"text":"<p>Data registry?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32905,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-20 01:21:02 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 01:21:02 UTC"},{"id":3395,"user_id":21311,"text":"<p>do we have sensitive data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32908,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-20 01:29:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 01:29:45 UTC"},{"id":3396,"user_id":21311,"text":"<p>frequency: weekly or monthly?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":32806,"archived_by":21311,"created_at":"2021-10-20 02:11:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 15:51:28 UTC"},{"id":3397,"user_id":21335,"text":"<p>Most of our data will be Excel based. I think we should include .csv files. I am not sure about xml, because these are \"browser files\". Depending on the age of the browser, you may cannot read them.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":32804,"archived_by":21311,"created_at":"2021-10-20 15:14:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 15:44:14 UTC"},{"id":3398,"user_id":21335,"text":"<p>What about the numerical data from image analysis?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32803,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-20 15:15:26 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 15:15:26 UTC"},{"id":3399,"user_id":21335,"text":"<p>Weekly! We will measure the body weight weekly and update the file asap. But I would not print the collection tables (to save paper and ink; be more green). I would rather save the new file with the modification date at the end. We will create tons of files but in this way, we can track everything.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32806,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-20 15:20:34 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 15:20:34 UTC"},{"id":3400,"user_id":21335,"text":"<p>Wait, not ALL data. We will perform CT measurements and these images are HUGE. When we acquire the data, we will store them on an external hard drive. I am not sure if we can store these images on McGill Dataverse.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32910,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-20 15:22:44 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 15:22:44 UTC"},{"id":3401,"user_id":21335,"text":"<p>What is the difference between analysed and final data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32906,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-20 15:28:11 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 15:28:11 UTC"},{"id":3402,"user_id":21335,"text":"<p>Yes, we can use a data registry. I have used before Mendeley Data. Further, we can publish our data in the journal \"Data in Brief\" which can link our data to Mendeley Data.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32905,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-20 15:31:30 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-20 15:31:30 UTC"},{"id":3403,"user_id":21290,"text":"<p>revise!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":32406,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-25 15:08:14 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-25 15:08:14 UTC"},{"id":3404,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>question?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33027,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-10-25 21:28:28 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-25 21:28:28 UTC"},{"id":3405,"user_id":21427,"text":"<p>Pas de r&eacute;ponse aujourd'hui. Nous pourrons remplir cette section dans quelques mois.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33205,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-02 13:25:23 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-02 13:25:23 UTC"},{"id":3406,"user_id":21428,"text":"<p>Cela d&eacute;pend de la dur&eacute;e du projet et des besoins pour l'acc&egrave;s &agrave; long terme aux donn&eacute;es.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33209,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-02 13:59:18 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-02 13:59:26 UTC"},{"id":3407,"user_id":21454,"text":"<p>C'est ce que je propose pour le moment, mais &ccedil;a reste &agrave; v&eacute;rifier avec Vincent T.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33448,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 17:11:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 17:11:47 UTC"},{"id":3408,"user_id":21454,"text":"<p>C'est ce que je propose pour le moment, mais &ccedil;a reste &agrave; v&eacute;rifier avec Vincent T.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":33448,"archived_by":21454,"created_at":"2021-11-04 17:11:49 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 17:12:18 UTC"},{"id":3409,"user_id":21454,"text":"<p>Je n'ai aucune id&eacute;e de ce que &ccedil;a peut repr&eacute;senter &agrave; ce jour.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33455,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 17:23:19 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 17:23:19 UTC"},{"id":3410,"user_id":21454,"text":"<p>Voir avec Vincent T. qui a mentionn&eacute; quelque chose &agrave; ce sujet lors de la pr&eacute;sentation de la GDR.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33456,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 17:24:41 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 17:24:41 UTC"},{"id":3411,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Do we have a metadata standard that we can use? If not, for simplicity, I suggest we leave this blank for now and make do with my explanation above?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33467,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:27:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-09 12:23:09 UTC"},{"id":3412,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Is this correct? I assume the University backs up the OneDrive? Also, are you ok with what I have suggested here with additional back-up to external harddrive on a weekly basis? I am open to suggestions.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33423,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:31:00 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:31:00 UTC"},{"id":3413,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>How can this slack communication best be stored long term (even after completion of project?) in a way that is accessible? We have many important conversations in there, that would be worth saving long term.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33424,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:45:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:45:37 UTC"},{"id":3414,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Linda, I need your input on this. Not sure what you would like to do with the data once project is over? Are you ok with the suggested?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33451,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:47:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:47:05 UTC"},{"id":3415,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>How about data/findings that are patentable?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33458,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:48:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:48:50 UTC"},{"id":3416,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Thinking this is something we can decide later. Will need help with this.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33459,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:49:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:49:24 UTC"},{"id":3417,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>I think we might need more information here?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33461,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:50:33 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:50:33 UTC"},{"id":3418,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>I think we might need more details here?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33463,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:51:00 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:51:00 UTC"},{"id":3419,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Thinking resources for this will be part of my salary as project manager, but it will probably be more as this also include payment for storage solutions during the project, long term storage and maintenance, etc. Not sure about dollar amount. Will need help with this section</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33468,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:53:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:53:42 UTC"},{"id":3420,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Not sure if I have covered everything we need to here?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33464,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:54:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:54:12 UTC"},{"id":3421,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Do we reference the research agreement with AMNS here, or something else? Will need help with this section.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33465,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:55:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:55:59 UTC"},{"id":3422,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Will need assistance with this section. Do we refer to research agreement with AMNS?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33466,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-04 19:56:58 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 19:56:58 UTC"},{"id":3423,"user_id":21357,"text":"<p>Linda, with this organization, where should <strong>draft theses</strong> be stored? Does it make most sense to store these in the separate Project folders?&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":33315,"archived_by":21357,"created_at":"2021-11-05 19:14:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-23 12:59:32 UTC"},{"id":3424,"user_id":21471,"text":"<p>However, further details of the data are not disclosed for now as per the confidentiality agreement between Syncrude and U of A.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33535,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-08 18:40:23 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-08 18:40:23 UTC"},{"id":3425,"user_id":10076,"text":"<p>Normalement je ne mentionnerais pas les donn&eacute;es administratives, mais comme il s'agit d'un aspect de l'utilisation de l'infrastructure par des tiers, il me semble que c'est important.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33651,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-10 15:40:02 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-10 15:40:02 UTC"},{"id":3426,"user_id":4150,"text":"<p>Heidi, could you take on this section since I made it sound so bad.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33981,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-23 14:36:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-23 14:36:25 UTC"},{"id":3427,"user_id":4150,"text":"<p>Yikes!&nbsp; Reid, can you help me find the right one?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34003,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-23 14:49:09 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-23 14:49:09 UTC"},{"id":3428,"user_id":21189,"text":"<p>NEEDS MORE WORK</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33955,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-23 16:17:55 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-23 16:17:55 UTC"},{"id":3429,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>A question to keep in mind will be how long you want to maintain the data yourself as well. As REDCap infrastructure and cost is worked out, we may want to consider how long you need access to the project data in REDCap for your own purposes and/or if other storage is appropriate. -RS</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33882,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-25 19:49:09 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 19:49:09 UTC"},{"id":3430,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Once we have access to REDCap, we can revisit this question to look at export formats and features and see what procedures you may want to create/follow.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33883,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-25 19:52:04 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 19:52:04 UTC"},{"id":3431,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Depending on agreements with any Indigenous communities, there may be a need to work out to give them access and control their data (and it may need to be excluded from data deposits if the communities do not wish to have it shared openly).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33884,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-25 19:55:54 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 19:55:54 UTC"},{"id":3432,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Ellen is working on a budget, and AU IT is setting up REDCap infrastructure. IDEA Lab this round will be a bit of a pilot for figuring out how REDCap use will need to be charged to researchers.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33892,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-25 19:58:22 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 19:58:22 UTC"},{"id":3433,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Sample consent form language is available in this document:</p>\n<pre><a href=\"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4107178\">https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4107178</a><br /><br />We can also discuss with Gail in the ethics office when you submit your ethics application.</pre>","archived":0,"answer_id":33894,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-25 20:00:51 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 20:00:51 UTC"},{"id":3434,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Consent form and potentially agreements with Indigenous community collaborators?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33895,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-25 20:02:35 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 20:02:35 UTC"},{"id":3435,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>this is an insightful comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":25310,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-11-25 20:09:55 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 20:09:55 UTC"},{"id":3436,"user_id":21190,"text":"<p>\"Further discussion between members of the research team are still needed to decide how public to make <strong>this</strong> data<strong>.</strong> <strong>The</strong> intent of adding them to this repository is to ensure that, at the very least, other researchers interested in <strong>conducting</strong> similar studies will be able to follow the process underwent to collect, analyze, and share our data.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":34333,"archived_by":21190,"created_at":"2021-11-29 03:25:55 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-02 08:12:55 UTC"},{"id":3437,"user_id":21190,"text":"<p>Some specifications for data sharing have not yet been determined, as publishing policies vary from journal to journal, and ethics approval to share data to a data repository has not yet been <strong>granted</strong>.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":34337,"archived_by":21190,"created_at":"2021-11-29 03:29:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-02 08:13:41 UTC"},{"id":3438,"user_id":21190,"text":"<p>The&nbsp;<strong>principal</strong> investigator will be responsible for data management throughout the project and upon completion, with support from the research supervisor (Dr. Jane Yardley).</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":34339,"archived_by":21190,"created_at":"2021-11-29 03:31:56 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-02 08:14:07 UTC"},{"id":3439,"user_id":21347,"text":"<p>Do we want to use Git for version control? Git tracks the changes you make to files, so you have a record of what has been done, and you can revert to specific versions if you ever need to.</p>\n<p>I don&rsquo;t know if everyone got the training for it, but it could be useful mostly for file management and coding.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33469,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-06 21:26:42 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-06 21:26:42 UTC"},{"id":3440,"user_id":21347,"text":"<p><em>Some suggestions for electronic lab notebooks that should be used in the group? A lot of organic chemistry research groups in our department use Findmolecule for ELN and lab inventory</em></p>\n<p><em>I don&rsquo;t know what is used in analytical/environmental chemistry research.</em></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":33471,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-06 21:33:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-06 21:33:01 UTC"},{"id":3441,"user_id":21552,"text":"<p>Not sure if R/SPSS scripts will be included in this, or instrumentation data (what exactly is this?)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34596,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-07 20:58:04 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-07 20:58:04 UTC"},{"id":3442,"user_id":21552,"text":"<p>- check to see if there are vocabulary that is consistent for files across the discipline</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34601,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-07 21:39:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-07 21:39:45 UTC"},{"id":3443,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>This is a comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34683,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-13 18:24:58 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-13 18:24:58 UTC"},{"id":3444,"user_id":21626,"text":"<p>https://www.re3data.org/repository/r3d100010328</p>\n<p>maybe here?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34750,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-17 21:13:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-17 21:13:37 UTC"},{"id":3445,"user_id":4692,"text":"<p>Other anticipated files? CSVs? Word docs?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34833,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-22 18:18:36 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-22 18:18:36 UTC"},{"id":3446,"user_id":4692,"text":"<p>This can all be edited and is what I am suggesting based on the Metadata Template from Ithaka. If there is preference for another file naming convention, let's discuss and update this section.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34834,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-22 18:19:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-22 18:29:57 UTC"},{"id":3447,"user_id":4692,"text":"<p>Do we need a shared folder on the T-drive to back up all data? Or we could use one of our home drives? Alternatively, we could temporarily store raw data files on a secondary cloud source like OSF? We need a location to back up files.&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":34836,"archived_by":4692,"created_at":"2021-12-22 18:40:32 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-22 18:53:14 UTC"},{"id":3448,"user_id":4692,"text":"<p>Do we need a shared folder on the T-drive to back up all data? Or we could use one of our home drives? Alternatively, we could temporarily store data files on a secondary cloud source like OSF? We need a location to back up files.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34838,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-22 18:53:06 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-22 19:20:51 UTC"},{"id":3449,"user_id":4692,"text":"<p>We need to clarify how we will manage files (see second bullet point) if each of us is interviewing on our own. And will need to establish a workflow for handling and managing files. May be a good idea to assign a data manager (see the Responsibilities section below) who can oversee the data management for the project (create readme file, ensure data is being backed up, etc.)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34836,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-22 18:57:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-22 19:26:39 UTC"},{"id":3450,"user_id":4692,"text":"<p>How long will we store the files? It looks like files will go to Ithaka. Perhaps they have guidance on file retention.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>What is the long term storage plan for these files?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34839,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-22 19:12:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-22 19:13:04 UTC"},{"id":3451,"user_id":4692,"text":"<p>Will we be storing long term? Need to clarify with Ithaka if they have guidance on this. Can be decided once we have more information.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34841,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-22 19:24:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-22 19:24:12 UTC"},{"id":3452,"user_id":4692,"text":"<p>Similar to comment above. Do we want one person managing the project's data? Or we could assign roles?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34842,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2021-12-22 19:28:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-12-22 19:28:01 UTC"},{"id":3453,"user_id":21506,"text":"<p>AWS data privacy: https://aws.amazon.com/compliance/pipeda/&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\"As AWS does not have visibility into or knowledge of what customers are uploading onto its network, including whether or not that data is deemed subject to PIPEDA regulations, customers are responsible for their own PIPEDA compliance.\"</p>\n<p>PIPEDA</p>\n<p>https://www.priv.gc.ca/en/privacy-topics/privacy-laws-in-canada/the-personal-information-protection-and-electronic-documents-act-pipeda/&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34727,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-07 20:06:07 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-07 20:06:07 UTC"},{"id":3454,"user_id":8051,"text":"<p>alternative for the Archives Unleashed Cloud, should FRDR be mentioned here?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27963,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-17 18:35:30 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-17 19:03:18 UTC"},{"id":3455,"user_id":8051,"text":"<p>Can this be more explicit, what exactly are the naming conventions, are the Archives Unleashed naming conventions still going to be used? How is versioning being handled?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27964,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-17 19:15:25 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-17 19:15:25 UTC"},{"id":3456,"user_id":8051,"text":"<div data-canvas-width=\"31.856538995508373\">also include something like \"A description of the project, which will include a description of how the data was collected\"</div>","archived":0,"answer_id":27965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-17 19:18:53 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-25 08:17:06 UTC"},{"id":3457,"user_id":8051,"text":"<p>mention the length of time of data storage?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34685,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-17 19:23:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-17 19:23:26 UTC"},{"id":3458,"user_id":8051,"text":"<p>how often will local drive be backed up? After every session, once a week?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34686,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-17 19:24:41 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-25 08:21:07 UTC"},{"id":3459,"user_id":8051,"text":"<p>alternative for Archives Unleashed Cloud?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34687,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-17 19:25:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-17 19:25:33 UTC"},{"id":3460,"user_id":21713,"text":"<p>Bill needs to fill this out</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":35359,"archived_by":21713,"created_at":"2022-01-17 21:09:15 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-17 21:10:20 UTC"},{"id":3461,"user_id":21713,"text":"<p>Ask Bill about how SMDHU factors into this</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35362,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-17 21:20:22 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-17 21:20:22 UTC"},{"id":3462,"user_id":9702,"text":"<p>Added - thanks!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27963,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-24 18:36:42 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-24 18:36:42 UTC"},{"id":3463,"user_id":8051,"text":"<p>How will large files be shared?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34687,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-25 08:22:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-25 08:22:26 UTC"},{"id":3464,"user_id":8051,"text":"<p>Could use greater detail</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34697,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-25 08:26:05 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-25 08:26:21 UTC"},{"id":3465,"user_id":9702,"text":"<p>Yes... I am wondering, how much does this documentation go in the DMP, or if it belongs elsewhere, where is that, and should I be linking to there from here? I do have the original project proposal in DSpace: http://dx.doi.org/10.25316/IR-15160</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-25 21:30:18 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-25 21:30:18 UTC"},{"id":3466,"user_id":9702,"text":"<p>We also have the public-facing collection level description: https://archive-it.org/collections/13709</p>\n<p>Badly formatted in that platform</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-25 21:32:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-25 21:32:31 UTC"},{"id":3467,"user_id":9702,"text":"<p>updated 25 Jan</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34684,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-25 21:35:22 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-25 21:35:22 UTC"},{"id":3468,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>Probably best not to go through UW for back-up storage, since we would want these practices to extend beyond my post-doc.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35540,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-27 14:45:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-27 14:45:33 UTC"},{"id":3469,"user_id":21506,"text":"<p><strong>Connie, Dr. Marti please add here.</strong></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34733,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-30 00:17:47 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-30 00:17:47 UTC"},{"id":3470,"user_id":20811,"text":"<p>Bonjour! Je pense que les enqu&ecirc;tes seront export&eacute;es dans un format tabulaire comme un fichier .csv ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":28030,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-31 17:31:13 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-31 17:31:13 UTC"},{"id":3471,"user_id":9702,"text":"<p>I have a question about best practice for refreshing local drive storage.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34685,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-31 19:05:57 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-31 19:05:57 UTC"},{"id":3472,"user_id":9702,"text":"<p>It has been more like twice a year. Ideally I think it would be at the end of each month.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34686,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-31 19:08:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-31 19:08:09 UTC"},{"id":3473,"user_id":21773,"text":"<p>I have never heard of this before. If this is going to be a requirement at Western, suggest providing some workshops or templates for faculty members... I looked a few up and they were really cryptic and outside of my field. This one will be the biggest change for most of us.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35689,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-31 19:57:55 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-31 19:57:55 UTC"},{"id":3474,"user_id":21773,"text":"<p>This and many other fields are duplicate info with fields in WREM. Suggest consolidating that if this is going to be implemented, so that we are not answering similar questions in two places. This one has a much more detailed examination of data storage issues, so perhaps could replace these fields in WREM?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35683,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-31 19:59:19 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-31 19:59:19 UTC"},{"id":3475,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p>Remove or edit any statements that do not apply to your project.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":35698,"archived_by":11002,"created_at":"2022-01-31 20:36:53 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 18:45:50 UTC"},{"id":3476,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p><em>RPARR B.1.4; B.2.1</em></p>\n<p><em>GCREB 10. Methodology; 14. Collection of Personal Information</em></p>\n<p><em>Multi-college 9. Methodology; 15. Collection and Protection of Personal Information</em></p>\n<p>If you will be collecting any identifiers or potentially identifying information about human participants, remember to provide the justification in your application for research ethics approval.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35705,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-31 20:38:54 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 19:01:39 UTC"},{"id":3477,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p><em>GCREB 10. Methodology; 17. Transmission or Movement of Data</em></p>\n<p><em>Multi-college 9. Methodology; 17. Moving and Transmission of Data</em></p>\n<p><em>Note: Some of this might change once I.T. has a chance to look into our institutional settings.</em></p>\n<p>This template includes information on the most common online/remote data collection methods for research involving human participants - surveys and interviews/focus groups.</p>\n<p>Include descriptions of any other data collection methods you plan to use.</p>\n<p>Remove or edit any statements that do not apply to your project, e.g. premium features of Qualtrics if you are not using them. Adjust for any settings you choose to use in Microsoft Teams or Webex, e.g. any steps you might take to authenticate people joining your meeting or steps to kick out uninvited participants if you are not using authentication.</p>\n<p>This information may be subject to change. Consult Georgian College I.T. Support or the Access and Privacy Office for more information.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35700,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-01-31 20:42:17 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-10 20:56:55 UTC"},{"id":3478,"user_id":21779,"text":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id=\"3ba0702c-b135-4384-9cca-dec6c4680be7\" class=\"widget general-html none  widget-none  widget-compact-all\">\n<div class=\"wrapped \">\n<div class=\"widget-body body body-none  body-compact-all\">\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"c862b13b-6ba7-4313-a2cc-78e63f354fa0\" class=\"widget general-rich-text none  widget-none  widget-compact-horizontal\">\n<div class=\"wrapped \">\n<div class=\"widget-body body body-none  body-compact-horizontal\">\n<div id=\"rich-text-c862b13b-6ba7-4313-a2cc-78e63f354fa0\" class=\"pb-rich-text\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","archived":0,"answer_id":35743,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-01 09:09:03 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-01 11:51:08 UTC"},{"id":3479,"user_id":1099,"text":"<p>The info at https://archive-it.org/collections/13709 is a good start. I'd build on this description and include a file with the following info:</p>\n<p>1). the background of how the project scope changed over time (i.e. expanded focus geographically, importance of capturing archive of Indigenous-related COVID news). This includes ramifications for what maybe didn't get collected in the early days in certain areas, but is collected later on.</p>\n<p>2) description of the process for inclusion (i.e. is there a daily keyword search done on certain news sites? is it library staff recommendations captured via Matter Most links)</p>\n<p>This isn't something I'd necessarily put in a DMP, other than signaling that the file with this info will be made available alongside the collection.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-01 18:19:23 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-01 18:19:23 UTC"},{"id":3480,"user_id":1099,"text":"<p>If VIU Library Data team is too general, we can specify which positions are included, i.e. \"The Library Data team is comprised of individuals who hold the positions of eResources Librarian, Collections Librarian, and Data Librarian.\"&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34696,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-01 18:29:10 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-01 18:29:10 UTC"},{"id":3481,"user_id":1099,"text":"<p>Mention that members of the team have TCPS2 CORE (https://tcps2core.ca/) training (if we all do) and be guided by that?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34695,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-01 18:38:11 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-01 18:38:11 UTC"},{"id":3482,"user_id":6745,"text":"<p>It would be good to have more detail on how you will document things for the team; things like codebooks or data dictionaries if data are coded, readme files if appropriate, how decisions about data management will be incorporated into team documentation, what documentation will be required internally for the team, vs. what needs to be provided with any shared data to help users interpret and reuse it correctly. You may not have answers to this yet, and maybe more details would be more appropriate for Phase II; bearing in mind that a DMP is intended to be a living document, and something you can revise as you work through these issues.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35472,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-02 17:02:17 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-02 17:02:17 UTC"},{"id":3483,"user_id":6745,"text":"<p>Regarding 2. it would be good to identify early in the project what the long-term storage solution will be for MR files, because there may be cost implications. External hard drives can be a line item in your funding application. I think long-term storage is a bit of a gap in the services the UofC offers for data management, to be honest. IT seems to focus more on supporting the active phase of research. I've asked the library and we aren't able to support this type of long-term data storage.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35475,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-02 17:34:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-04 21:14:26 UTC"},{"id":3484,"user_id":6745,"text":"<p>Also, spelling: it's principal investigator.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35475,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-02 18:49:05 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-02 18:49:05 UTC"},{"id":3485,"user_id":6745,"text":"<p>In restricted-access situations, you may want to consider developing in advance a data-sharing agreement template that can be ready in case you do receive requests to share data. The University of Waterloo Research Office has a some good guidance; I'm not aware of similar guidance at UofC but this could be adapted.&nbsp;<br />https://uwaterloo.ca/research/office-research-ethics/research-human-participants/pre-submission-and-training/human-research-guidelines-and-policies-alphabetical-list/data-sharing-or-transfer-agreements-what-are-they-and-when/elements-data-sharing-agreement-example&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35476,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-02 19:04:44 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-02 19:04:44 UTC"},{"id":3486,"user_id":6745,"text":"<p>If there are workflows or instructions for some of these things, they should be described under the Documentation section.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35477,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-02 19:17:00 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-02 19:17:00 UTC"},{"id":3487,"user_id":6745,"text":"<p>This would be where you price out the cost of your long-term data storage, if any.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35478,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-02 19:30:17 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-02 19:30:17 UTC"},{"id":3488,"user_id":6745,"text":"<p>The Data Curation Network has a primer on neuroimaging data curation that you may want to consult, and may help flesh out some of these procedures. <a class=\"underline mat-body-1 ng-star-inserted\" href=\"http://hdl.handle.net/11299/216582\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">http://hdl.handle.net/11299/216582</a></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35477,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-02 19:36:03 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-02 19:36:03 UTC"},{"id":3489,"user_id":6745,"text":"<p>If images are shared, is there potentially identifying information embedded in the metadata? If so this will need to be dealt with - the Data Curation Network primer I mentioned above has some suggestions around this. The Canadian Association of Radiologists also has some guidance on de-identifying medical images; see Other Resources listing at https://library.ucalgary.ca/c.php?g=395022&amp;p=5150380&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35480,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-02 19:38:56 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-02 19:38:56 UTC"},{"id":3490,"user_id":9702,"text":"<p>Thanks for this. So I'm getting that documentation as threaded above needs to be gathered into a file to guided future use of data outputs of the project. Would this file then best be deposited to DV as a supporting file to the dataset? and perhaps deposited also to the VIUSpace IR for the sake of redundancy and paranoia? And then this section of the DMP can link to one or both of those resources?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27965,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-07 17:45:00 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-07 17:45:00 UTC"},{"id":3491,"user_id":9702,"text":"<p>great idea, thanks.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34695,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-07 19:43:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-07 19:43:31 UTC"},{"id":3492,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35916,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-08 18:26:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-08 18:26:52 UTC"},{"id":3493,"user_id":14849,"text":"<p>Hey Jane - I think there will be a second document for the search history exports?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36038,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-15 14:18:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-15 14:19:53 UTC"},{"id":3494,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>No clue</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36044,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-15 20:10:47 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-15 20:10:47 UTC"},{"id":3495,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>I do not know</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36048,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-15 20:28:36 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-15 20:28:36 UTC"},{"id":3496,"user_id":21873,"text":"<p>What the heck is metadata? Is this a codebook?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36065,"archived_by":21874,"created_at":"2022-02-17 17:44:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 20:04:38 UTC"},{"id":3497,"user_id":21741,"text":"<p>BIDS: Gorgolewski et al. (2016) <em>Scientific Data. </em>DOI: 10.1038/sdata.2016.44</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35484,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 00:04:05 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 00:04:05 UTC"},{"id":3498,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>J'ai vu plus haut une r&eacute;f&eacute;rence &agrave; des partenaires priv&eacute;s, y a-t-il des ententes avec eux au sujet de la propri&eacute;t&eacute; intellectuelle?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vous pouvez aussi indiquer ici que vous allez avoir le soutien du Bureau de liaison Universit&eacute; Milieu et du Bureau du droit d'auteur pour toutes ces question.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36166,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 12:38:02 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 12:38:02 UTC"},{"id":3499,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Il est fort possible que vous n'utilisiez pas de renseignements personnels, mais les donn&eacute;es sensibles incluent &eacute;galement des donn&eacute;es strat&eacute;giques dont le partage pourrait nuire &agrave; l'environnement, l'industrie ou autre. Simplement, confirmer ici que vous n'en utiliserez aucune.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36164,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 12:42:07 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 12:42:07 UTC"},{"id":3500,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Si la question ci-dessous reste N/A, celle-ci le reste &eacute;galement.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36165,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 12:43:00 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 12:43:00 UTC"},{"id":3501,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Si possible, &eacute;vitez les acronymes (PI).</p>\n<p>La taille du projet serait &agrave; pr&eacute;ciser. On en d&eacute;duit qu'il y aura un gestionnaire de projet qui supervisera des gens ou des &eacute;quipes de gens, incluant des &eacute;tudiants.</p>\n<p>Ici, est-ce que nous devons en comprendre que les directives principales proviendraient du gestionnaire de projet et que la responsabilit&eacute; de l'application serait partag&eacute;s avec les PI ou tous ensemble d&eacute;cident des r&egrave;gles de gestion de donn&eacute;es?</p>\n<p>Qui s'occupera de former ceux qui se joindront au projet en cours de route?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36161,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 12:52:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 12:52:16 UTC"},{"id":3502,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Si possible, &eacute;viter les abr&eacute;viation (PI).</p>\n<p>Il ne manquerait que l'information si jamais le gestionnaire de projet doit s'absenter, qui prend la rel&egrave;ve?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36162,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 12:53:36 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 12:53:36 UTC"},{"id":3503,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Si vous connaissez les co&ucirc;ts de stockage, vous pouvez l'indiquer ici.</p>\n<p>Vous pouvez &eacute;galement d&eacute;j&agrave; pr&eacute;voir un pourcentage de temps (PI ou autre) pour s'occuper de la gestion des donn&eacute;es (ex. 5%).</p>\n<p>Dans certains cas plus rares, il y a des embauches sp&eacute;cifiques pour la gestion des donn&eacute;es de recherche.</p>\n<p>Indiquer que cette question reste encore &agrave; &ecirc;tre valid&eacute;e et discut&eacute;e avec les PI est &eacute;galement&nbsp;acceptable &agrave; cette &eacute;tape.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36163,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 13:00:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 13:00:16 UTC"},{"id":3504,"user_id":21851,"text":"<p>Question is clear.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36095,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 14:22:11 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 14:22:11 UTC"},{"id":3505,"user_id":21851,"text":"<p>No comments. The example provides a clear description of what is required.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36099,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 14:25:22 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 14:25:22 UTC"},{"id":3506,"user_id":21851,"text":"<p>Perhaps an addition or link to a template for these files would be helpful for those doing this for the first time?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36100,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:01:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:01:09 UTC"},{"id":3507,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Il s'agit effectivement d'un bon moyen de communiquer l'information, mais si les donn&eacute;es ne sont pas accessibles (via un d&eacute;p&ocirc;t ou un autre moyen), que devront faire ceux qui voudront les consulter?</p>\n<p>Si votre projet met en place un site web, ce peut aussi &ecirc;tre une fa&ccedil;on de communiquer l'information.</p>\n<p>Si &eacute;ventuellement les donn&eacute;es sont mises dans un d&eacute;p&ocirc;t, celui-ci offrira certainement des moyens pour augmenter la visibilit&eacute; des donn&eacute;es (DOI, moissonnage, etc.). Cela ne signifie pas n&eacute;cessairement de rendre vos donn&eacute;es ouvertes, mais elles pourraient &ecirc;tre retrouvables si elles sont d&eacute;pos&eacute;es.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36160,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:02:08 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:02:08 UTC"},{"id":3508,"user_id":21851,"text":"<p>Value in linking this to what it says in the ethics protocol? Or verify that these sharing techniques are approved by ethics?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36104,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:07:36 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:07:36 UTC"},{"id":3509,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Cette section (partage et r&eacute;utilisation) concerne principalement le partage des donn&eacute;es avec des personnes qui ne font pas partie du projet de recherche. Bien que toutes les versions des donn&eacute;es soient conserv&eacute;es pour le projet, ce ne seraient peut-&ecirc;tre pas toutes ces versions qui seraient partag&eacute;es.</p>\n<p>Je n'ai trouv&eacute; aucune information au sujet de d&eacute;p&ocirc;t &agrave; l'externe, ce sera &agrave; pr&eacute;ciser (si le d&eacute;p&ocirc;t et le partage sont impossibles, il faut le mentionner et le justifier, car l'exigence de d&eacute;p&ocirc;t des donn&eacute;es est de plus en plus courante chez les &eacute;diteurs, aussi bien pr&eacute;parer la r&eacute;ponse le plus t&ocirc;t possible). Il est &agrave; noter que d&eacute;p&ocirc;t n'&eacute;quivaut pas n&eacute;cessairement au partage.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36158,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:09:21 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:09:21 UTC"},{"id":3510,"user_id":21851,"text":"<p>Analyzed data is a presentation of the results, not a data file. This might be confusing for some.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36106,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:11:00 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:11:00 UTC"},{"id":3511,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>S'agit-il ici de publication des donn&eacute;es ou de publication des r&eacute;sultats de recherche (ex. : article)?</p>\n<p>Lorsque nous pensons archivage, nous pensons pr&eacute;servation &agrave; long terme des donn&eacute;es, est-ce ce qui est sous-entendu ici?</p>\n<p>J'ai vu plus loin que l'ensemble des types de donn&eacute;es sera conserv&eacute; (brute, analyse, compilation), les donn&eacute;es brutes seront donc conserv&eacute;es dans le format propri&eacute;taire s'il y a lieu? Est-ce que toutes les donn&eacute;es recueillies pourront utiliser ces formats comme formats finaux?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36157,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:21:17 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:21:17 UTC"},{"id":3512,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Cette section traite de la pr&eacute;servation long terme, qui exclut donc toute forme de suppression apr&egrave;s un certain nombre d'ann&eacute;es.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Lorsqu'il est mentionn&eacute; que chaque PI pourra conserver les donn&eacute;es, s'agit-il de l'ensemble des donn&eacute;es ou des donn&eacute;es qu'il/elle aura recueillies? Est-ce &agrave; dire que le gestionnaire de projet ne pr&eacute;voit pas de conserver &agrave; long terme? S'il y a une question de droit qui explique cette situation, l'inclure dans la section \"conformit&eacute; &eacute;thique et juridique\".</p>\n<p>Si possible, ne pas utiliser d'acronyme (PI)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36156,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:22:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:22:52 UTC"},{"id":3513,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>One Drive et Teams sont des outils tout &agrave; fait acceptables.</p>\n<p>Si vous avez besoin de plus d'espace, vous pourrez aller voir du c&ocirc;t&eacute; de VALERIA (https://valeria.science/accueil)&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36155,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:26:07 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:26:07 UTC"},{"id":3514,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Dans la mesure du possible, installer un mode de backup automatis&eacute; ou avoir une proc&eacute;dure &agrave; ce sujet (telle personne de telle &eacute;quipe fait un backup tel jour)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36154,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 15:38:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 15:38:26 UTC"},{"id":3515,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Cette question ne fait pas r&eacute;f&eacute;rence &agrave; la documentation d'accompagnement, mais plut&ocirc;t aux normes qui seront utilis&eacute;es pour d&eacute;crire les donn&eacute;es. Par exemple, si vous r&eacute;coltez des &eacute;chantillons et que vous suivez la norme ISO 19115, l'indiquer ici. Si vous avez pr&eacute;vu utiliser un d&eacute;p&ocirc;t, celui-ci utilise certainement un sch&eacute;ma de m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es que vous pourriez inscrire. Si vous qualifiez vos donn&eacute;es avec un vocabulaire contr&ocirc;l&eacute; (th&eacute;saurus, ontologie, etc.), c'est une autre information &agrave; inscrire.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36152,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 18:12:47 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 18:12:47 UTC"},{"id":3516,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Cette information serait plus appropri&eacute;e dans la section sur le stockage.</p>\n<p>Pour cette question, si vous avez plusieurs personnes qui travaillent sur une m&ecirc;me partie de projet, comment vous assurez-vous que les donn&eacute;es de l'un seront saisies de la m&ecirc;me fa&ccedil;on que les donn&eacute;es de l'autre?</p>\n<p>Comment vous assurez-vous que les donn&eacute;es d'une personne soient compr&eacute;hensibles? Advenant d'un impr&eacute;vu et que cette personne doit quitter, sera-t-il possible de comprendre ses donn&eacute;es et de poursuivre son travail?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36151,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 18:19:11 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 18:19:11 UTC"},{"id":3517,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Allez-vous utiliser des cahiers de terrain et/ou des cahier de laboratoire?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36150,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 18:20:14 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 18:20:14 UTC"},{"id":3518,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Avez-vous &eacute;galement des recommandations pour structurer vos dossiers? Si plusieurs personnes travaillent sur le projet avec des r&eacute;pertoires partag&eacute;s, ce peut &ecirc;tre utile.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36149,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 18:27:43 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 18:27:43 UTC"},{"id":3519,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>&Agrave; la question pr&eacute;c&eacute;dente, vous mentionnez des donn&eacute;es spatiales ainsi que des vid&eacute;os et de l'audio, mais il n'y a aucun format correspondant ici. Peut-&ecirc;tre sont-ils encore inconnus?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36148,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-23 20:07:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-23 20:07:59 UTC"},{"id":3520,"user_id":21898,"text":"<p>The university needs a standard policy on this and a repository for lab notebooks from a laboratory. &nbsp;The notebooks from a laboratory should be kept for a limited amount of time (10 years) after retirement of the PI and destroyed at the end of 10 years. &nbsp;This should be a repository of unindexed notebooks as PIs are not librarians. &nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36290,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-25 18:36:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-25 18:36:31 UTC"},{"id":3521,"user_id":21898,"text":"<p>When a PI retires there needs to be a system for the notebooks to be retained for X years before being destroyed. &nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36291,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-25 18:38:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-25 18:38:24 UTC"},{"id":3522,"user_id":21898,"text":"<p>If the major problem with data preservation is work on human subjects then the instructions need to contain examples of what does not require this type of curation. &nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36293,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-02-25 18:40:50 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-25 18:40:50 UTC"},{"id":3523,"user_id":21856,"text":"<p>On recueille des donn&eacute;es pour un long p&eacute;riode et on va les utiliser surement m&ecirc;me apr&egrave;s le projet de recherche. Or, il s'agit, au moins pour l'instant, analyses de documents textuels qui ne semblent pas occuper beaucoup d'espace de stockage. Les exercices H5P occuperaient peut-&ecirc;tre un peu plus, mais les sondages et leurs rapports ne semblent pas poser trop de probl&egrave;me non plus (PDF). Comment le calculer? Demander &agrave; Jonathan Dorey.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36299,"archived_by":21856,"created_at":"2022-02-25 20:27:27 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 15:33:52 UTC"},{"id":3524,"user_id":21856,"text":"<p>Nancy, est-ce que tu as toutes les donn&eacute;es sauvegard&eacute;es quelque part d'autre? Aussi dans ton ordinateur?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36300,"archived_by":21856,"created_at":"2022-02-25 20:29:51 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-16 13:17:36 UTC"},{"id":3525,"user_id":21856,"text":"<p>Est-ce que cela serait pr&eacute;f&eacute;rable de convertir ce qu'on a en MS Word &agrave; .rtf?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36345,"archived_by":21856,"created_at":"2022-02-28 13:37:29 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 15:39:27 UTC"},{"id":3526,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p><em>GCREB 10. Methodology; 17. Transmission or Movement of Data; 18. Others' Access to Data</em></p>\n<p><em>Multi-college 9. Methodology; 17. Moving and Transmission of Data</em></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36384,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-02 15:58:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 19:55:18 UTC"},{"id":3527,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p><em>GCREB </em><em>17. Transmission or Movement of Data</em></p>\n<p><em>Multi-college 17. Moving and Transmission of Data</em></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36385,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-02 15:59:23 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 19:52:31 UTC"},{"id":3528,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p>GCREB 19. Secondary Use of Data.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36386,"archived_by":11002,"created_at":"2022-03-02 16:00:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 19:56:22 UTC"},{"id":3529,"user_id":21918,"text":"<p>I use Qualtrics to collect most of my data. I'm not sure what file format that would be considered as. Qualtrics then provides format options for downloading data (e.g., csv, spss, excel).&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36409,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 02:36:11 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 02:38:06 UTC"},{"id":3530,"user_id":21918,"text":"<p>The example and comments in the Guidance section were really helpful.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36412,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 02:40:00 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 02:40:07 UTC"},{"id":3531,"user_id":21918,"text":"<p>I'm not really sure if the level of detail in my response is sufficient as I have never been asked to do this before. The information in the Guidance section was really helpful -- I would be curious to know if there are any online tools that can help researchers set up this type of documentation or various ways in which researchers can keep track of this type of information.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36413,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 02:42:36 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 02:46:31 UTC"},{"id":3532,"user_id":21918,"text":"<p>I wasn't sure what level of detail would be required here. For example, as I am reviewing my response, I'm wondering if I should say that I would, for example, use a shared google doc, to keep track of the documentation. I'm wondering what tools will make this process easier for researchers such as having using a tool that can link to codes or syntax or some sort of TOC or binder that keeps the components together.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36414,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 02:49:53 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 02:49:53 UTC"},{"id":3533,"user_id":21918,"text":"<p>Something that I find a bit confusing is how \"long-term preservation\" different from simply storing your data on the OSF at the end of a project? For example, most researchers in my area, social psychology, will include a de-identified data file on the OSF, but it's unclear how this might differ from preserved data.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36425,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 02:53:47 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 02:55:17 UTC"},{"id":3534,"user_id":21918,"text":"<p>This goes back to my last comment. By sharing a de-identified data file on the OSF, would that just be processed data? I should add that these files typically have variable names that are obvious, or an associated codebook to understand the variables within the data file.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36427,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 02:57:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 02:57:16 UTC"},{"id":3535,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>Whichever repository we decide on...&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36466,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 16:37:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 16:37:09 UTC"},{"id":3536,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>I think we'll need to wait on this answer until we know which repository and what their specific requirements are... ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36467,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 16:37:55 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 16:37:55 UTC"},{"id":3537,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>Wording from REB?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36468,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 16:39:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 16:39:33 UTC"},{"id":3538,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p><em>RPARR B.2.1</em></p>\n<p><em>GCREB 19. Secondary Use of Data</em></p>\n<p><em>Multi-college 18. Secondary Use of Data</em></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35704,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-03 19:39:32 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-03 19:39:32 UTC"},{"id":3539,"user_id":21618,"text":"<p>AWS suggestion: AWS Transcribe and bucket storage for original audio recordings (S3 input bucket) and transcribed interview (S3 output bucket). To conduct the case studies interviews, this project can use AWS Chime and AWS Transcribe a speech-to-text transcription service.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36565,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-07 21:29:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 03:14:31 UTC"},{"id":3540,"user_id":21618,"text":"<p><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/ebs/?c=s&amp;sec=srv\">AWS Elastic Block Store</a> would work well for this project.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36570,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-07 22:28:58 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-07 22:28:58 UTC"},{"id":3541,"user_id":20435,"text":"<p>comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36599,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-08 21:33:19 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-08 21:33:19 UTC"},{"id":3542,"user_id":21910,"text":"<p>Bob - you fill this in.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36623,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-09 15:48:38 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-09 15:48:38 UTC"},{"id":3543,"user_id":11002,"text":"<p><em>GCREB 10. Methodology.</em></p>\n<p><em>Multi-college 9. Methodology.</em></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36386,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-09 21:02:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-09 21:02:37 UTC"},{"id":3544,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>R&eacute;viser le texte de r&eacute;ponse.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36713,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-11 16:21:38 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-11 16:21:38 UTC"},{"id":3545,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>Texte de r&eacute;ponse &agrave; r&eacute;viser.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36714,"archived_by":21368,"created_at":"2022-03-11 16:43:02 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-11 16:43:12 UTC"},{"id":3546,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>Texte de r&eacute;ponse &agrave; r&eacute;viser</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36714,"archived_by":21368,"created_at":"2022-03-11 18:24:38 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-11 18:24:51 UTC"},{"id":3547,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You could strengthen this answer by explicitly highlighting that you will update your documentation as needed (and potentially identify which role(s) are responsible for doing so).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34548,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-12 00:45:32 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 00:45:32 UTC"},{"id":3548,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>The metadata section of this could be clarified a little. Are the bullets information to be included with a bit more description in the README file (e.g., 'mode of collection - self administered writing' is that a description of the the raw data (written by MOOC participants)?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34542,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-12 01:13:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 01:13:09 UTC"},{"id":3549,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>To address the second part of the question, you may want to explicitly state whether or not you need any specific software to read your file types or identify what will allow you to access or use your data long term and/or provide links to more info (it's helpful for reviewers or team members who may not be as familiar with the tools).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34543,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-12 01:23:19 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 01:23:19 UTC"},{"id":3550,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>I would suggest adding a couple more descriptive titles (like your \"Convention for Jupyter Notebook files\"), e.g., convention for MOOC data.&nbsp; A little more description is need to understand what topic_dis applies to (e.g., is topic the start of all dissemination files or a stand-in for whatever descriptive info you want people to use?).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34545,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-12 01:27:35 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 01:27:35 UTC"},{"id":3551,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>It's implied in your answer already, but you may want to state that the computing resources and support are made available through AU's IDEA Lab (a sentence that would provide a bit more context for a reader/reviewer).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34549,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-12 01:37:07 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 01:37:07 UTC"},{"id":3552,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You may want to update this as you go with a bit more context of what you used (amounts etc.) to make it easier to plan for future projects. (If you wanted to replicate your study, what would you need in this description?)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34551,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-12 01:43:51 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 01:43:51 UTC"},{"id":3553,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>If you use any particular Python libraries or packages you should identify them here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34719,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-12 01:45:01 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 01:45:01 UTC"},{"id":3554,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You may need to document any settings in your software (parameter values) to make your analysis as replicable as possible. I haven't used Comprehend, but other topic modeling algorithms have things like seeds and stop words that would affect outputs.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":34553,"archived_by":2671,"created_at":"2022-03-12 01:59:15 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 02:04:26 UTC"},{"id":3555,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Tri-Agency Policy asks for deposit of \"digital research data, metadata and code that directly support the research conclusions in journal publications and pre-prints that arise from agency-supported research\" so it is possible that you may want to deposit your Jupyter notebook files of code as well.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":34731,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-12 02:10:23 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-12 02:10:23 UTC"},{"id":3556,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>R&eacute;viser le texte de cette r&eacute;ponse</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36742,"archived_by":21368,"created_at":"2022-03-14 16:32:04 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 16:32:11 UTC"},{"id":3557,"user_id":21971,"text":"<p>Are there any issues with sharing the data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36778,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 19:27:43 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 19:27:43 UTC"},{"id":3558,"user_id":21971,"text":"<p>Do we have any other concerns here?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36783,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 19:29:58 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 19:30:55 UTC"},{"id":3559,"user_id":21971,"text":"<p>Nigel, please provide your office number here</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36785,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 19:33:10 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 19:33:10 UTC"},{"id":3560,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>ROBYN - is this an accurate answer?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36811,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 20:03:36 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 20:03:36 UTC"},{"id":3561,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>ROBYN - do we re-enter from the last question, or should the last answer be here instead?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36065,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 20:04:02 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 20:04:02 UTC"},{"id":3562,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>ROBYN:&nbsp; do you have suggestions for this question?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36813,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 20:14:18 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 20:14:18 UTC"},{"id":3563,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>ROBYN:&nbsp; I'm not sure what is best practice here?&nbsp; (KHARAH:&nbsp; suggestions?)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36815,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 20:18:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 20:18:16 UTC"},{"id":3564,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>ROBYN &amp; KHARAH - I'm not sure what repository costs typically are, and I'm not sure how much the external hard drive would cost...?&nbsp; Also, are there other costs I haven't included?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36816,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 20:20:51 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 20:20:51 UTC"},{"id":3565,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>ROBYN:&nbsp; we're not sure what to put in this question... ?&nbsp; Will this be included in the licence?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36818,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-14 20:22:44 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-14 20:22:44 UTC"},{"id":3566,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You may want to provide a link to the documentation from physionet and note that your own processes will be documented as laid out in the next question below. Assuming this is the correct set of documentation, it's been assigned a DOI, which would also be great to include: <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.13026/C2XW26\">https://doi.org/10.13026/C2XW26</a>.</p>\n<p>One additional piece to consider is putting a READme file in the top folder of your Sharepoint site with an overview of the project and brief explanation of what is in your files. There is a <a href=\"https://data.research.cornell.edu/content/readme\">template provided by Cornell</a> (it assumes you don't also have codebooks, so you could abbreviate it considerably if you have those). The idea being that if you were to go back to this group of files in couple of years (or if you were to deposit it elsewhere) you would be able to replicate what you have done or repurpose it.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36579,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 14:23:27 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 14:34:33 UTC"},{"id":3567,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>If there are defined roles for your project, you may want to include who will create (and update) the documentation as needed.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36580,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 14:23:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 14:23:37 UTC"},{"id":3568,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Unless I'm misunderstanding, I would put the information you've included here in the first and/or second question (about data types and formats).</p>\n<p>Does MIMIC-III organize or describe data based on any particular standard? From my very quick read on physionet, it looks like they've pulled data together to match the raw hospital data as closely as possible, and they've made their own data model. You could note you are using the health records as provided in the database that uses their data model (and then link to or state that you have access to that documentation--I assume you documentation about the information in the databases' tables, some of them may use controlled vocabularies e.g., WHO International Classification of Diseases). Any controlled vocabularies would be good to either note here, or state that they are included in the documentation of MIMIC-III.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36739,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 14:45:35 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 14:45:35 UTC"},{"id":3569,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>The only thing I would suggest here is adding how long you intend to keep the data or a plan to reassess its retention period after X number of years.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36581,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 14:48:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 14:48:33 UTC"},{"id":3570,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>This comment is more from a reviewer standpoint (so for future reference if submitting a DMP for review), but you may want to state how many copies you have and/or if they are stored remotely in different geographic locations (that speaks to risk of data loss). On that note, AU's SharePoint is backed up to AWS as well, I believe.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36582,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 14:51:18 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 14:51:18 UTC"},{"id":3571,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Because you have listed two different avenues, you may want to note how files in both locations will be reconciled (or if there is a need to reconcile them).</p>\n<p>You could also note if only particular team members are doing specific tasks.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36583,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 14:53:18 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 14:53:18 UTC"},{"id":3572,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>This would be long term access for team members, correct? You may want to note any conditions for access or use (you had to do a data access agreement to get credentials to use MIMIC-III, right? So if there are any conditions from that, they could be noted as relevant in the questions of this section.)</p>\n<p>Is the iceboxed version mentioned when discussing backups a long term solution as well? (I realize this may need to be updated as IDEA Lab works out how they want to deal with use of AWS resources long term).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36584,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 14:57:56 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 14:57:56 UTC"},{"id":3573,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>I am assuming you are not depositing this data in an outside repository, so you could note that data will stored with its documentation as outlined earlier in your plan (you are not necessarily creating a package for deposit in a repository).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36585,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:00:10 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:00:10 UTC"},{"id":3574,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>This is another space where you could note any necessary agreements you had to make to get access and that others would need to go through that process as well (i.e. you may not actually be able to share the data outside your team depending on the terms of your agreement).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36586,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:02:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:02:33 UTC"},{"id":3575,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>This one may not be applicable if you are not sharing your data outside of your team. If you deposit with a repository, they will typically ask you to assign a license that includes re-use terms.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36740,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:03:34 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:03:34 UTC"},{"id":3576,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Can you provide a little more detail here and/or a URL for MIMIC resources on GitHub?</p>\n<p>You could also note that you will be citing the original source of the data in any research outputs (presentations and publications) arising from the project.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36587,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:05:23 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:05:23 UTC"},{"id":3577,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You could list roles here. E.g., Lorraine Thirsk, PI, negotiated data agreement, responsible for long term maintenance of data....</p>\n<p>Russell Rupok, RA, responsible for data cleaning, setting up AWS storage, submitting code to GitHub...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>(just taking a guess at activities)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36588,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:09:30 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:09:30 UTC"},{"id":3578,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>(Just a suggestion... to expand a little to note...) that all resources and activities are documented (as outlined in earlier sections of this DMP) in order to ensure team members can access and understand all aspects of data handling should any changes in roles occur.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I'm also not sure, depending on your how your credentialed access permissions work for MIMIC-III, if anyone else could take over, so you could note any conditions or need for training of new or changing members relating to appropriate use of the data set.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36589,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:14:58 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:14:58 UTC"},{"id":3579,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Here would be a place to note that this project is receiving support and funding from AU's IDEA Lab, which includes both computing resources (AWS) and RA support. If you don't want to put a cost estimate here, you could note that a budget was created and is available in your project documentation stored in x location. I think that the idea behind this question is so that when a DMP is attached to a funding application, you can directly connect between it and your budget asks.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36590,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:17:51 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:17:51 UTC"},{"id":3580,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>I would provide a little more detail here (or a link) to said framework.</p>\n<p>You could also note that the data is de-identified, so not sensitive in that sense, but that you are managing it according to the terms of the data agreement using institutionally provided and supported resources (SharePoint, AWS) and then if there are any limits to what goes in Google Drive because its not an institutionally provided resource.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36741,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:21:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:21:26 UTC"},{"id":3581,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>I would just put something like \"not applicable\" or \"our team will use the data as agreed to through MIMIC-III's credentialing process. If others want to reuse the data, they would need to sign their own agreement. More information and documentation of the data set is available at <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.13026/C2XW26\">https://doi.org/10.13026/C2XW26</a>\"</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36884,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:24:40 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:24:40 UTC"},{"id":3582,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>texte &agrave; changer</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36885,"archived_by":21368,"created_at":"2022-03-15 15:51:58 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 15:52:14 UTC"},{"id":3583,"user_id":20615,"text":"<p>skjdbflbfjlhjb</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36888,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 18:51:46 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 18:51:46 UTC"},{"id":3584,"user_id":21992,"text":"<p>Additionally, data on pollinator abundances and diversity visiting cucurbit crops on different farms will be collected</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36765,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 22:00:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 22:00:16 UTC"},{"id":3585,"user_id":21992,"text":"<p>If we are encluding that some of the data collected includes the actual data from the monitoring (see above comment), then we'd want to include that data will be collected through the app, online, and paper forms</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36766,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 22:01:45 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 22:01:45 UTC"},{"id":3586,"user_id":21992,"text":"<p>and will use at least one of the tools?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36769,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-15 22:02:21 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-15 22:02:21 UTC"},{"id":3587,"user_id":21908,"text":"<p>Toutes les donn&eacute;es sont encrypt&eacute;es sur un disque dur externe</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36300,"archived_by":21856,"created_at":"2022-03-16 12:39:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-16 13:17:39 UTC"},{"id":3588,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>r&eacute;ponse &agrave; revoir</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36742,"archived_by":21368,"created_at":"2022-03-16 17:30:29 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-16 17:30:40 UTC"},{"id":3589,"user_id":22005,"text":"<p>Not sure how much data to estimate - example gives \"under 30 GB\"</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":37038,"archived_by":22005,"created_at":"2022-03-17 16:23:57 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 19:05:14 UTC"},{"id":3590,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>revoir le texte</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36742,"archived_by":21368,"created_at":"2022-03-17 16:55:41 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-17 16:55:46 UTC"},{"id":3591,"user_id":22005,"text":"<p>Anything specific we should include here?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":37045,"archived_by":22005,"created_at":"2022-03-17 17:36:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 19:04:54 UTC"},{"id":3592,"user_id":22005,"text":"<p>Am I missing anything here?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36999,"archived_by":22005,"created_at":"2022-03-17 17:56:47 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 19:02:15 UTC"},{"id":3593,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>r&eacute;viser la r&eacute;ponse</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36742,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-17 18:10:04 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-17 18:10:04 UTC"},{"id":3594,"user_id":22005,"text":"<p>Wasn't sure what to put here</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":37060,"archived_by":22005,"created_at":"2022-03-17 19:34:25 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 19:11:20 UTC"},{"id":3595,"user_id":22005,"text":"<p>Does this apply to trainees using the data?&nbsp;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":37000,"archived_by":22005,"created_at":"2022-03-17 20:18:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 19:12:38 UTC"},{"id":3596,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>Note pour le titre du projet dans l'onglet \"d&eacute;tails sur projet\" : Mettre dans le guide d'utilisation qu'il faut utiliser le m&ecirc;me titre que dans la BD du D&eacute;canat pour uniformit&eacute;?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37076,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 14:51:19 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 14:51:19 UTC"},{"id":3597,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>Sp&eacute;cification &agrave; apporter lorsque partenariat avec l'industrie</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37081,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 15:37:12 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 15:37:12 UTC"},{"id":3598,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Concernant les copies de sauvegarde, vous indiquez aux six mois. Pour les corpus d'origine, je ne vois aucune probl&egrave;me. Pendant la phase d'analyse/annotation, je recommanderais des copies de sauvegarde plus fr&eacute;quentes pour &eacute;viter de perdre 6 mois de travail. Si vous avez des p&eacute;riodes tr&egrave;s actives d'analyse, il serait peut-&ecirc;tre pertinent d'en faire une sauvegarde toutes les semaines.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36300,"archived_by":21856,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:14:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 15:36:04 UTC"},{"id":3599,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Compte tenu que les formats/types de donn&eacute;es sont essentiellement textuels, je pense que vous n'avez qu'&agrave; pr&eacute;ciser l'espace qui vous est allou&eacute; sur TEAMS. Un commentaire comme \"Le groupe de recherche dispose d'un espace TEAMS avec 1 To fourni par l'universit&eacute;. Nous n'anticipons pas de besoins suppl&eacute;mentaires pour le moment.\" Si jamais vos besoins changeaient en cours de route, vous pourrez modifier cette section (p. ex. si vous avez d&eacute;sormais acc&egrave;s &agrave; des fichiers audio ou vid&eacute;o).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36299,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:24:54 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 17:25:06 UTC"},{"id":3600,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Si c'est pertinent, vous pourriez ajouter \"Les acc&egrave;s &agrave; l'espace TEAMS sont contr&ocirc;l&eacute;s par XX. L'acc&egrave;s &agrave; la page priv&eacute;e du projet Corpus BLABLA sont contr&ocirc;l&eacute;s par XX.\"</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36301,"archived_by":21856,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:26:42 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 15:37:07 UTC"},{"id":3601,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : &Agrave; titre de suggestion, vous pourriez indiquer qu'&agrave; la fin du projet, les donn&eacute;es pourront &ecirc;tre vers&eacute;es dans l'Espace Dataverse de la T&Eacute;LUQ au besoin. Cela permettra d'assurer la p&eacute;rennit&eacute; des donn&eacute;es et une r&eacute;utilisation futures. Ce service vous est offert gratuitement et n'a donc pas d'impact sur votre budget de recherche. Si vous pr&eacute;voyez conserver certains documents pendant une p&eacute;riode d&eacute;finie, par exemple les donn&eacute;es brutes (voir mon commentaire plus bas) avant de les d&eacute;truire, vous pourriez l'indiquer ici le cas &eacute;ch&eacute;ant.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36344,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:28:43 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 18:21:02 UTC"},{"id":3602,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Le format RTF est plus stable que MS Word. Par contre, DOCX et XLSX sont d&eacute;sormais bas&eacute;s sur une norme XML ce qui en facilite la pr&eacute;servation. Pour les sorties en PDF &agrave; partir de Survey Monkey, si vous pouvez choisir autre chose que PDF, cela vous permettra &eacute;galement re r&eacute;utiliser l'information. PDF est bon pour la pr&eacute;servation, mais permet difficilement la r&eacute;utilisation, puisqu'il s'agit d'une \"impression num&eacute;rique\".</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36345,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:32:05 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 17:32:05 UTC"},{"id":3603,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Suggestion de formulation. Plut&ocirc;t que de dire \"possibilit&eacute; de partage apr&egrave;s\", je vous sugg&egrave;re plut&ocirc;t pour les donn&eacute;es secondaires \"Pas de partage durant la phase d'analyse des donn&eacute;es; possibilit&eacute; de partage en acc&egrave;s restreint au moment de la publication selon les exigences li&eacute;es aux publications.\" et pour les donn&eacute;es tertiaires \"Partage en fonction des exigences li&eacute;es aux publications et communications.\" Dans les deux cas, Dataverse pourrait &ecirc;tre une option, en acc&egrave;s restreint au besoin puisque vous projet de recherche comporte une composante de confidentialit&eacute; li&eacute;e &agrave; l'&eacute;thique. Pour les donn&eacute;es brutes, pr&eacute;voyez-vous la destruction des donn&eacute;es une fois qu'elles auront &eacute;t&eacute; trait&eacute;es et analys&eacute;es?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36346,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:37:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 18:20:05 UTC"},{"id":3604,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Je vous sugg&egrave;re \"Une licence Creative Commons Attribution CC-BY 4.0 sera pr&eacute;vue pour tout ensemble de donn&eacute;es partag&eacute; afin de favoriser les collaborations avec d'autres chercheurs ou &eacute;quipes de recherche. Les licences de type Creative Commons sont d&eacute;j&agrave; couramment utilis&eacute;es pour les activit&eacute;s d'apprentissage.\" Il y a d'autres version de Creative Commons qui pourraient s'appliquer, mais je recommande g&eacute;n&eacute;ralement CC-BY.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36373,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:40:27 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 17:40:27 UTC"},{"id":3605,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Vous pourriez pr&eacute;ciser qui est responsable de donn&eacute;es acc&egrave;s aux donn&eacute;es (en &eacute;cho &agrave; la question acc&egrave;s aux donn&eacute;es de la section stockage et sauvegarde).</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36375,"archived_by":21856,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:42:39 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 15:43:23 UTC"},{"id":3606,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Si l'universit&eacute; vous donne acc&egrave;s &agrave; une licence, vous pouvez l'indiquer ici. Souvent, on a acc&egrave;s &agrave; LimeSurvey (vrai pour moi &agrave; l'INRS) ou NVivo (non &agrave; l'INRS, mais oui &agrave; McGill) via l'universit&eacute;. Vous pouvez v&eacute;rifier avec le STI si ce n'est d&eacute;j&agrave; fait.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":36377,"archived_by":21856,"created_at":"2022-03-18 17:44:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 15:44:11 UTC"},{"id":3607,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Je vous sugg&egrave;re la formulation suivante :</p>\n<p>\"Les donn&eacute;es des corpus sont anonymis&eacute;es d&egrave;s la premi&egrave;re &eacute;tape de leur traitement et, par la suite, seulement des informations d&eacute;mographiques g&eacute;n&eacute;rales et pertinentes &agrave; la recherche sont li&eacute;es &agrave; chacun des documents. Dans le cas des sondages, les participants donnent leur consentement libre et &eacute;clair&eacute; avant de pouvoir y r&eacute;pondre, tel que pr&eacute;vu par le certificat d'&eacute;thique.\" Vous pourriez ajouter que le logiciel de sondage ne recueille aucune information personnelle, y compris les adresses IP. Je ne sais pas pour LimeSurvey, mais pour SurveyMonkey, nous avions la possibilit&eacute; de ne pas collecter cette information. LS le fait peut-&ecirc;tre par d&eacute;faut. Plus haut, vous avez parl&eacute; de donn&eacute;es crypt&eacute;es. Vous pourriez faire un court rappel ici : (si c'est pertinent) Les donn&eacute;es des sondages seront crypt&eacute;es et conserv&eacute;es pendant x ann&eacute;es.\"</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36378,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 18:13:28 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 18:13:28 UTC"},{"id":3608,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : En lien avec ce qui est &eacute;crit &agrave; la section Partage et r&eacute;utilisation, je vous sugg&egrave;re une formulation de type :</p>\n<p>\"Seules les donn&eacute;es anonymis&eacute;es seront diffus&eacute;es dans le cadre de publications ou de communications. Le cas &eacute;ch&eacute;ant, l'acc&egrave;s aux donn&eacute;es secondaires et tertiaires pourrait &ecirc;tre en acc&egrave;s restreint, ce qui permet de respecter la confidentialit&eacute; des participants tout en favorisant la collaboration en mati&egrave;re de recherche. Les donn&eacute;es brutes ne seront pas accessibles.\" Si vous choisissez de publier les donn&eacute;es, je vous encourage &eacute;galement &agrave; publier une copie vierge du formulaire de consentement.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36379,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 18:19:20 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 18:22:34 UTC"},{"id":3609,"user_id":20797,"text":"<p><strong>Jonathan</strong> : Si vous le jugez pertinent, vous pouvez pr&eacute;ciser que l'entente d'acc&egrave;s aux corpus pr&eacute;voit l'acc&egrave;s, la r&eacute;utilisation et le partage des donn&eacute;es (en formulant en fonction de ce qu'elle vous permet r&eacute;ellement de faire!)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36380,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 18:24:07 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 18:24:07 UTC"},{"id":3610,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Your sensitive data information may go more in the first question under ethics and legal compliance than here.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Your last paragraph is the sort of thing I've seen more commonly in answering this question. You may want to add that your survey data will be stored in a database (based on your later answer that mentions REDCap), and that the data will also be tabular (spreadsheet).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36452,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:11:34 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:11:34 UTC"},{"id":3611,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p><span class=\"TextRun SCXW251446663 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW251446663 BCX0\">For file naming conventions you should give the date format (e.g., YYYYMMDD or YYYY-MM-DD) that you plan to use. It&rsquo;s also a good idea to give some example file names so anyone referring to the DMP can see what you mean.</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW251446663 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"EOP SCXW251446663 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\">You may also want to explain any version system (e.g.,&nbsp; will dates be sufficient or will also use version numbers?).</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36063,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:14:05 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:14:05 UTC"},{"id":3612,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p><span class=\"TextRun SCXW145828266 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW145828266 BCX0\">You might want to expand this answer a little (e.g., basic methodology information about the study will be included in the </span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2 SCXW145828266 BCX0\">READme</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW145828266 BCX0\"> file, the codebook will describe the survey questions and variables...)</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW145828266 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\">&nbsp;</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36810,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:14:56 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:14:56 UTC"},{"id":3613,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Yes, you could also note that it&nbsp; will be reviewed and updated as necessary.</p>\n<p>If the survey is in REDCap (you've mentioned both it and LimeSurvey), I believe REDCap has an automated feature for codebooks so it could be mentioned here too as a tool (I'm unfamiliar with LimeSurvey's features).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36811,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:17:12 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:17:12 UTC"},{"id":3614,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Sometimes people just say N/A if they aren't using an established metadata standard. If we identify any metadata standards or controlled vocabularies we can add them in here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36065,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:18:50 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:18:50 UTC"},{"id":3615,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You may want to include a file size here (e.g., how big is the SPSS file)? And how long will your team retain copies (you've noted the length of time for LimeSurvey, but is Kharah planning to retain her own copy after submitting to a repository? If so for how long?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36458,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:21:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:21:33 UTC"},{"id":3616,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You've also mentioned both LimeSurvey and REDCap. How is data getting from one to the other?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36465,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:23:39 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:23:39 UTC"},{"id":3617,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Yes, Cheryl, that's a good plan. Some repositories&nbsp; actually take SPSS (.por) files for their distribution copies because it's a common format even though it's proprietary. If you have both formats it may make sense to deposit both (SPSS for ease of reuse and .csv or .tsv for longer term preservation)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36467,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:26:41 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:26:41 UTC"},{"id":3618,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Repositories often have you select licenses that they have available (creative commons options are common). We will need to look into how this works with restricted data (and the particular repository you choose--you may need to do all rights reserved and have each requestor sign an agreement if they don't have a restricted use license option) because you need something more restrictive than the typical creative commons terms.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36468,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:31:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:31:59 UTC"},{"id":3619,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p><span class=\"TextRun SCXW146331636 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW146331636 BCX0\">To help the community know that your data exists, you will select a repository that meets your REB requirements but also will make your data more discoverable (e.g., by being indexed in other search interfaces). You can also cite your data set in any publications or presentations you give. You can link to it from any researcher web presence you may have (e.g., project or researcher website, social media, blog posts). Data papers are also becoming an established&nbsp;venue (there are journals that publish papers that describe data sets with re-use potential, e.g., </span></span><a class=\"Hyperlink SCXW146331636 BCX0\" href=\"https://openpsychologydata.metajnl.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><span class=\"TextRun Underlined SCXW146331636 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"none\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW146331636 BCX0\" data-ccp-charstyle=\"Hyperlink\">https://openpsychologydata.metajnl.com/</span></span></a><span class=\"TextRun SCXW146331636 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW146331636 BCX0\"> ). Any other knowledge mobilization activities you may plan (e.g., giving presentations on data sharing or data curation at disciplinary venues) would also be relevant to mention.</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW146331636 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\">&nbsp;</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36813,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:35:45 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:35:45 UTC"},{"id":3620,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p><span class=\"TextRun SCXW135145844 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW135145844 BCX0\">For responsibilities you may also want to note who will create and update your documentation. Because of your planned restricted data sharing, you may also want to list </span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2 SCXW135145844 BCX0\">Kharah</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW135145844 BCX0\"> as being responsible for reviewing requests for re-use in the long term.</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW135145844 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\">&nbsp;</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36814,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:36:25 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:36:25 UTC"},{"id":3621,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p><span class=\"TextRun SCXW178777467 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW178777467 BCX0\">For personnel changes you can note that your&nbsp;DMP and documentation created can be used to onboard new team members. You could note that it is unlikely that there will be a change in principal investigator at this stage in the project and that if there was that you would consult with the REB about </span><span class=\"NormalTextRun AdvancedProofingIssueV2 SCXW178777467 BCX0\">whether or not</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW178777467 BCX0\"> continued access to the dataset (without </span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2 SCXW178777467 BCX0\">Kharah</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW178777467 BCX0\"> to determine if studies are similar or not) is appropriate. ...or something to that effect.</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW178777467 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\">&nbsp;</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36815,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:37:50 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:37:50 UTC"},{"id":3622,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Repository costs...often free unless you are paying for additional curation services or data review (which not all of&nbsp; them offer).</p>\n<p><span class=\"TextRun SCXW207486809 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2 SCXW207486809 BCX0\">If you want to be able to&nbsp; put a number Kharah,</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW207486809 BCX0\"> could use the approximation of cost for labour from her NDRIO funding application (part of the idea is that you can use a DMP to justify funding asks when you put in funding applications). You c</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun ContextualSpellingAndGrammarErrorV2 SCXW207486809 BCX0\">ould also</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW207486809 BCX0\"> include costs of </span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2 SCXW207486809 BCX0\">LimeSurvey</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW207486809 BCX0\"> and any other platform used for data storage and transfer (you&rsquo;ve </span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2 SCXW207486809 BCX0\">mentioned</span> <span class=\"NormalTextRun SpellingErrorV2 SCXW207486809 BCX0\">REDCap</span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW207486809 BCX0\"> and Dropbox in earlier answers).</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW207486809 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\">&nbsp;</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36816,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:40:34 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:40:43 UTC"},{"id":3623,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p><span class=\"TextRun SCXW240167587 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW240167587 BCX0\">Yes, you could note that you will be restricting re-use to similar studies [and update your answer with the process or license terms you choose]. You could also note that you have consulted with your local REB about your plan for data sharing because you have received permission to share without reconsenting participants. </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"TextRun SCXW240167587 BCX0\" lang=\"EN-US\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW240167587 BCX0\">This question may have more in-depth answers if you had made some sort of agreement with an outside collaborator or company who retains the intellectual property of the overall project which required you to sign a nondisclosure agreement or something of that nature (and therefore can&rsquo;t share data).</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW240167587 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\">&nbsp;</span></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36818,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-18 23:44:53 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-18 23:44:53 UTC"},{"id":3624,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>Ajouter une d&eacute;finition des types de donn&eacute;es</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37080,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 17:55:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 17:55:26 UTC"},{"id":3625,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Plus loin, il est question d'une base de donn&eacute;es. Les donn&eacute;es recueillies seront vers&eacute;es dans une base de donn&eacute;es? Il y est aussi question d'utiliser R, y a-t-il un autre type de donn&eacute;es qui servira lors de l'analyse? Vous listez ici les donn&eacute;es recueillies, ce qui est excellent, mais il semble manquer la suite (ce que les donn&eacute;es deviendront). Il serait aussi pertinent d'indiquer ici les donn&eacute;es que vous allez aller chercher chez vos partenaires (j'ai cru comprendre que les donn&eacute;es sur les ours allaient vous &ecirc;tre fournies?)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36958,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 18:34:25 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 12:25:56 UTC"},{"id":3626,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Quelques ajouts possibles : les donn&eacute;es sur les ours seront dans quel format? Les points GPS vous parviendront dans quel type de fichier? Votre base de donn&eacute;es utilisera quel format?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36959,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 18:36:25 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 18:36:25 UTC"},{"id":3627,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Vous pouvez tout laisser, mais vous n'avez pas besoin d'aller aussi loin dans les explications. Tout simplement indiquer que tous les membres de l'&eacute;quipe vont utiliser une convention de nommage bas&eacute;e sur les recommandations de la Biblioth&egrave;que et que vous allez &eacute;galement avoir des normes de versionnage et de classification est suffisant. Si vous connaissez d&eacute;j&agrave; les conventions que vous allez utiliser, vous pouvez les inclure ici ou dans une annexe (par exemple, garder la derni&egrave;re phrase).</p>\n<p>La mention de Dataverse dans cette section est un peu &eacute;trange. Le d&eacute;p&ocirc;t permet bel et bien le versionnage, mais en cours de projet, je ne pense pas que vous allez l'utiliser. En th&eacute;orie, un jeu de donn&eacute;es d&eacute;pos&eacute; dans Dataverse ne doit pas &ecirc;tre modifi&eacute; (bien qu'on puisse faire des ajouts de donn&eacute;es et des changements de m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es).&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36960,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 18:44:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 12:26:52 UTC"},{"id":3628,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Est-ce &eacute;galement les chercheurs principaux qui seront responsables des &eacute;tudiants?</p>\n<p>Est-ce normal le paragraphe en anglais &agrave; la fin?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36962,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 18:54:10 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 18:54:40 UTC"},{"id":3629,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>C'est une excellente id&eacute;e de partager le PGD avec tous les membres impliqu&eacute;s dans le projet, mais s'il se veut &ecirc;tre la base de la gestion des donn&eacute;es, il faudra inclure les informations concr&egrave;tes (ex. : d&eacute;poser tel fichier de tel format dans tel dossier qui sera nomm&eacute; de telle mani&egrave;re). Sinon, il faudra un document d'accompagnement avec ces informations.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36968,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 18:58:45 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 18:58:45 UTC"},{"id":3630,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Vous pouvez &eacute;galement pr&eacute;voir un co&ucirc;t par rapport au salaire en lien avec la gestion des donn&eacute;es ex. : 10% du salaire d'un chercheur sera consacr&eacute; &agrave; la gestion des donn&eacute;es. Ce n'est pas une obligation, mais &ccedil;a permet de d&eacute;montrer que la gestion des donn&eacute;es a un co&ucirc;t humain.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36961,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:00:53 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 19:00:53 UTC"},{"id":3631,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Par curiosit&eacute;, est-ce que vous allez avoir un site web en lien avec votre projet de recherche?</p>\n<p>Effectivement, &agrave; partir du moment que les donn&eacute;es sont dans Dataverse, les m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es seront moissonn&eacute;es par d'autres d&eacute;p&ocirc;ts (dont le DFDR) et seront donc facilement rep&eacute;rables.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37044,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:04:30 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 19:04:30 UTC"},{"id":3632,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Si vous partagez des donn&eacute;es pseudonymis&eacute;es, ce ne sont pas des donn&eacute;es brutes, mais des donn&eacute;es trait&eacute;es. Possiblement qu'avec vos partenaires gouvernementaux, vous allez partager des donn&eacute;es brutes, mais que dans Dataverse, vous allez partager des donn&eacute;es trait&eacute;es... est-ce exact?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37041,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:07:04 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 19:07:41 UTC"},{"id":3633,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Dans quel type de fichier seront les points GPS?</p>\n<p>Les format vid&eacute;o seront d&eacute;pos&eacute;s en format mp4? Si oui, vous pouvez mentionner qu'il s'agit d'un format acceptable pour la conservation long terme.</p>\n<p>Si les donn&eacute;es sont pseudonymis&eacute;es, pourquoi sont-elles disponibles seulement sur demande? &Agrave; moins que ce soit uniquement la cl&eacute; qui doive &ecirc;tre rendue disponible sur demande?</p>\n<p>Il est fait mention d'une base de donn&eacute;es, est-ce qu'une base de donn&eacute;es sera d&eacute;pos&eacute;e? Si oui, sous quel format?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37034,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:12:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 12:29:50 UTC"},{"id":3634,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Voir commentaire plus loin au sujet des donn&eacute;es brutes, si les donn&eacute;es sont pseudonymis&eacute;es, elle sont trait&eacute;es et non brutes.</p>\n<p>Il est mentionn&eacute; dans une section pr&eacute;c&eacute;dente une dur&eacute;e de conservation de 5 ans. Il faudra pr&eacute;ciser que cette dur&eacute;e ne concerne que les donn&eacute;es &agrave; l'UL, car les donn&eacute;es qui sont dans le Dataverse visent &agrave; &ecirc;tre conserv&eacute;e &agrave; beaucoup plus long terme. Ce qui pose la question de la cl&eacute; de d&eacute;cryptage...&nbsp; vu que celle-ci ne peut &ecirc;tre dans Dataverse, comment et o&ugrave; la conserver? Je n'ai pas de r&eacute;ponse, j'avoue que &ccedil;a peut &ecirc;tre un probl&egrave;me... &Agrave; moins que les donn&eacute;es ne soient plus sensibles apr&egrave;s un temps X? Ex. : apr&egrave;s 10 ans ou 20 ans, est-ce que des positionnements d'esp&egrave;ce en danger pose toujours un risque de braconnage?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37033,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:17:19 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 12:29:26 UTC"},{"id":3635,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>r&eacute;vision faite</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36742,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:18:41 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 19:18:41 UTC"},{"id":3636,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Dans la mesure du possible, il faudrait pr&eacute;ciser un peu les quelques To vu que&nbsp; 1 To, c'est quand m&ecirc;me beaucoup de donn&eacute;es... on parle de 1 &agrave; 5 To? 5 &agrave; 10?</p>\n<p>Pr&eacute;ciser qu'il s'agit ici du stockage des donn&eacute;es &agrave; l'UL.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37023,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:21:49 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 19:21:49 UTC"},{"id":3637,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Peut-&ecirc;tre rappeler ici comment seront prot&eacute;g&eacute;es les donn&eacute;es sensibles vu qu'il est question de disques durs personnels et de disques dans un laboratoire.</p>\n<p>La fr&eacute;quence de sauvegarde lorsque les donn&eacute;es sont du c&ocirc;t&eacute; des ordinateurs personnels est laiss&eacute;e au choix de la personne qui les utilise? Je ne parle ici que de ce qui est sur disques durs externes vu que OneDrive a sa propre s&eacute;curit&eacute;.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37024,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:25:39 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 12:27:42 UTC"},{"id":3638,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>J'en comprends que c'est via VALERIA que les donn&eacute;es seront envoy&eacute;es aux partenaires gouvernementaux?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37032,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-21 19:25:41 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-21 19:25:41 UTC"},{"id":3639,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Cette information serait principalement int&eacute;ressante &agrave; la troisi&egrave;me question de cette section, celle qui porte sur les m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pour cette question, nous nous int&eacute;ressons principalement &agrave; la documentation qui va accompagner les donn&eacute;es. Par exemple, vous allez avoir des fichiers vid&eacute;o qui seront reli&eacute;s &agrave; des animaux. Comment et o&ugrave; seront inscrites les informations qui feront le lien entre les vid&eacute;os, l'emplacement de l'animal, la sorte d'animal et toutes autres informations essentielles?</p>\n<p>Lorsque vous aller analyser les donn&eacute;es, allez vous utiliser un tableau? Si oui, allez-vous cr&eacute;er un dictionnaire de donn&eacute;es pour d&eacute;finir les variables? Allez-vous inclure un fichier README lors du d&eacute;p&ocirc;t dans Dataverse pour expliquer l'origine des donn&eacute;es et comment les comprendre?</p>\n<p>Si vous qualifiez vos variables, allez-vous utiliser un vocabulaire contr&ocirc;l&eacute; sp&eacute;cifique &agrave; votre domaine? Par exemple, vous allez avoir des points GPS, allez-vous utiliser une norme (ex. ISO 19115) pour les &eacute;crire?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36971,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-22 12:14:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 12:24:41 UTC"},{"id":3640,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>Pour cette question, il faut se r&eacute;f&eacute;rer aux r&eacute;ponses &agrave; la question pr&eacute;c&eacute;dente. &Agrave; partir du moment o&ugrave; l'on sait quelles informations doivent &ecirc;tre collect&eacute;es par rapport aux donn&eacute;es elles-m&ecirc;mes, comment s'assurer que toutes les personnes de l'&eacute;quipe les collecteront correctement? Effectivement, partager la documentation, les normes et le PGD &agrave; tous les collaborateurs est une bonne fa&ccedil;on de faire.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37021,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-22 12:18:06 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 12:24:54 UTC"},{"id":3641,"user_id":19574,"text":"<p>C'est effectivement ici qu'on parle des m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es de Dataverse. Je ne suis pas certaine &agrave; 100% que le sch&eacute;ma DDI r&eacute;pondra &agrave; vos besoins, il est surtout centr&eacute; sur les sciences sociales...</p>\n<p>Toutefois, si l'ensemble des champs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux de Dataverse ainsi que la section g&eacute;ospatiales sont remplis, vos jeux de donn&eacute;es seront d&eacute;j&agrave; tr&egrave;s bien d&eacute;crits. Il est possible qu'un d&eacute;p&ocirc;t disciplinaires vous propose d'autres m&eacute;tadonn&eacute;es &agrave; compl&eacute;ter, mais si vous avez collect&eacute; toute la documentation n&eacute;cessaire, ces autres champs ne vous poseront pas de probl&egrave;me.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37022,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-22 12:22:56 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 12:25:20 UTC"},{"id":3642,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>test comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37300,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-22 20:19:56 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 20:19:56 UTC"},{"id":3643,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>My mistake -- LimeSurvey wasn't actually used in the end.&nbsp; The survey went out right from REDCap.&nbsp; :)&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36811,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 16:21:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 16:21:33 UTC"},{"id":3644,"user_id":21874,"text":"<p>Hi Robyn!&nbsp; We were wondering here if this was \"original\" data creation costs or whether this is ongoing costs?&nbsp; Or both?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36816,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 16:48:58 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 16:48:58 UTC"},{"id":3645,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Just a note on library databases.</p>\n<p>Both EBSCOHost and ProQuest are content aggregators who provide access to multiple databases. The \"Discover\" search (the main search and article search on the library home page) is an EBSCO \"discovery layer\" product that searches a subset of their database products and some others, including AU's catalogue (163 different products as of July 2021 when our collections librarian generated a report). Both Academic Search Complete and ERIC are searched when you use EBSO's Discover (as of the previously mentioned July report). If you are aiming to make your search more targeted to Education, you may want to select specific databases (like Education Research Complete, which is an EBSCO database specific to Education and ERIC) and then use EBSCO discover as a back up or for comparison to see if the others are missing relevant results. My reference librarian colleagues have put together a list of suggested databases for Ed here: <a href=\"https://libguides.athabascau.ca/education/journal_databases\">https://libguides.athabascau.ca/education/journal_databases&nbsp;</a></p>\n<p>ProQuest is similar in that you can do a \"Global\" search of all the ProQuest Databases we have subscription access to at AU, or you can specifically search their Education database ProQuest Education Journals.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37255,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 16:54:18 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 16:54:18 UTC"},{"id":3646,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You should be able to check where Zotero is saving your files to your computer under Edit &gt; Preferences &gt; Advanced &gt;Files and Folders.</p>\n<p>If you want to save an additional copy, you should ensure that the data directory location is included when you make your backups.</p>\n<p>Zotero will also sync everything to their cloud storage until you run out of space (and then you get a little exclamation point warning on the top right of the screen so that you can change your subscription if you want to continue to add your files to the cloud).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>For your own purposes within Zotero, you may want to come up with a naming convention for your \"collections\" (the term Zotero uses for folders used to organize items imported into Zotero). For example, you may want to include the date you ran a search in the name, and if you have folders of removed/irrelevant items, you may want to include dates there for when they were removed (or some other system so that you can match your folders of literature to your Excel spreadsheet).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37273,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 17:15:20 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 17:15:20 UTC"},{"id":3647,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You will be collecting metadata in Zotero (the citation information it collects is metadata about each item), so Zotero is a tool you will be using to document your data.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37276,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 17:20:22 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 17:20:22 UTC"},{"id":3648,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>I'm not sure SRDR is the best fit for long term preservation of this project. Taking a quick look, it seems to have a focus on health (its maintained by the Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality in the US). There could be more interdisciplinary options depending on what your long-term sharing and preservation goals are (happy to discuss that with you).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37281,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 17:37:29 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 17:37:29 UTC"},{"id":3649,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Yes, you would likely want to save your Excel files as .tsv or .csv for preservation (but be careful as some features won't save...like multiple sheets in a workbook, you need one .csv for each worksheet). You would also want to save a description of your process and an explanation of how your files are organized and relate to one another (e.g., in a .txt Readme file to accompany your files on your external drives or any data your deposit with an external repository).&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37282,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 17:46:48 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 17:46:48 UTC"},{"id":3650,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>For your purposes, I think you would just note that those are the people you will be sharing with.</p>\n<p>Some systematic reviews are doing meta-analyses and may have other forms of data to make available (so replicability can be checked once they publish their final reports). If you wanted to, you could publicly deposit your excel sheet lists of citation information and your methodology in a repository. That would allow others to do similar reviews (or updated reviews) based on your data. (Which is what the published systematic reviews in SRDR are enabling)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37283,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 17:53:21 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 17:53:21 UTC"},{"id":3651,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>These are all great options. Additionally, what they're looking for here is if your data is shareable, how will people find it? So, if you make your data open, will you provide links and cite it in each of these listed venues?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37285,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 17:56:44 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 17:56:44 UTC"},{"id":3652,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>AU does not necessarily keep copies of researchers' data, but a general recommendation is that researchers retain their data for at least 5 years. That way you can respond to questions and requests arising from publications about your project. If you deposit your data in a repository, that repository should have a policy regarding retention. (And AU is working on more policy/repository options around this in the future).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37286,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 18:01:34 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 18:01:34 UTC"},{"id":3653,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Depending what version of NVivo you want to use....AU has access to discounted 24 month licenses for students for ~100 CDN through <a href=\"https://athabasca.onthehub.com/WebStore/ProductsByMajorVersionList.aspx?cmi_mnuMain_child=68b60607-2ea2-e811-8109-000d3af41938&amp;cmi_mnuMain=f189368a-f0a6-e811-8109-000d3af41938\">On the Hub</a>. Note these are for NVivo 12 Pro, Plus, or Mac (which is no longer the latest version of NVivo). If you want the latest version, you can get a student license through NVivo for ~99 USD. I haven't tried the newest version, but student licenses for 12 were for the full version of the software.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37288,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 18:11:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 18:11:37 UTC"},{"id":3654,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>You may have to think about copyright if you want to share your data (for example, you can't share full copies of the published articles, but you can likely share lists of citations, etc.).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37292,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 18:13:25 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 18:13:25 UTC"},{"id":3655,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>Please state that the data is not sensitive. State what type of security for viruses etc are used on your laptop. State that the laptop and 2TB hard drives will be securely stowed in a home office area when not in use (i.e. indicate that you know what proper storage of the physical pieces means).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37279,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:38:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:38:26 UTC"},{"id":3656,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>use \"dissertation supervisor AND AU data librarian\"</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37280,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:39:23 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:39:23 UTC"},{"id":3657,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>I bow to Robyn's expertise here...I suggest an education repository if there is one - even if it is small or relatively new.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37281,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:41:14 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:41:14 UTC"},{"id":3658,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>This is a decision point that you will think about - for now and in preparation for candidacy, you need to state that you are still thinking about your options here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37283,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:43:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:43:09 UTC"},{"id":3659,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>Rosemarri - yes - I agree with your choice here. The repository that you select will likely have open licensing as part of contributing to the repository. What you decide and do here will be part of your Chapter 4 and 5.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37284,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:45:06 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:45:06 UTC"},{"id":3660,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>Robyn and I can help you with the license that you choose.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37284,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:45:47 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:45:47 UTC"},{"id":3661,"user_id":22069,"text":"<p>Je ne sais pas pour les types de fichiers des objectifs 1,3,4</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37427,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:46:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:46:31 UTC"},{"id":3662,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>I love Robyn's comments here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37285,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:47:20 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:47:20 UTC"},{"id":3663,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>In your dissertation where you talk about the DMP, you will need to say that the DMP is dynamic and that you return to it periodically. This includes AU changes, as per Robyn's comments. (I think that you want the word \"researcher\" at the beginning of this sentence).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37286,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:49:48 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:49:48 UTC"},{"id":3664,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>Robyn - any details about NVivo deals for faculty? ;)</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37288,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:51:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:51:33 UTC"},{"id":3665,"user_id":21504,"text":"<p>Very helpful comment from Robyn - she is correct. You can also have hyperlinks - for OA journal articles this would let people right into the article. If the article is behind a paywall, the hyperlink is usually to an abstract, or an abbreviated abstract. The \"sharing\" part of your dissertation is an important part of your work.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37292,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-25 19:54:20 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-25 19:54:20 UTC"},{"id":3666,"user_id":22069,"text":"<p>Je ne sais pas pour les autres parties du projet, mais pour l'objectif 2 les fichiers ne sont pas tr&egrave;s volumineux, je dirais qu'au final on va atteindre 1 Go d'espace maximum. On peut l'entreposer ind&eacute;finiment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37453,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-28 14:51:29 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-28 14:51:29 UTC"},{"id":3667,"user_id":22069,"text":"<p>Je ne sais pas</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37481,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-28 20:12:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-28 20:12:37 UTC"},{"id":3668,"user_id":22069,"text":"<p>Je ne sais pas</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37482,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-28 20:12:46 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-28 20:12:46 UTC"},{"id":3669,"user_id":22069,"text":"<p>Je ne sais pas, d'apr&egrave;s moi &ccedil;a ne devrait pas co&ucirc;ter tr&egrave;s cher, nous n'avons pas de licence &agrave; payer. Peut-&ecirc;tre un disque dur externe si nous n'en n'avons pas d&eacute;j&agrave; un.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37483,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-28 20:15:48 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-28 20:15:48 UTC"},{"id":3670,"user_id":22069,"text":"<p>Je ne sais pas quoi &eacute;crire pour cette question</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37485,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-29 14:51:12 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-29 14:51:12 UTC"},{"id":3671,"user_id":22069,"text":"<p>Je crois qu'ici il faudrait ajouter plus de d&eacute;tails sur les mesures prises concr&egrave;tement pour g&eacute;rer s&eacute;curitairement les donn&eacute;es sensibles.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37484,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-29 14:56:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-29 14:56:37 UTC"},{"id":3672,"user_id":22069,"text":"<p>Je crois qu'il faut ajouter plus de d&eacute;tails sur la propri&eacute;t&eacute; intellectuelle des donn&eacute;es.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37487,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-29 15:09:11 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-29 15:09:11 UTC"},{"id":3673,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>Since neither Jerrica nor Tammy live in Toronto, is there someone else we could enlist to help us with uploading paper surveys? If not, we can organize a joint venture into the office as needed.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":35511,"archived_by":21207,"created_at":"2022-03-31 19:05:11 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-21 14:16:41 UTC"},{"id":3674,"user_id":1,"text":"<p>test comment</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37576,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-03-31 21:32:50 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-31 21:32:50 UTC"},{"id":3675,"user_id":21893,"text":"<p>Thank you for your comments.&nbsp; I made changes in the DMP to reflect your comments.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Are you aware of an education repository that would be appropriate?&nbsp; I thought the repository was the institution who granted the credential.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37281,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-03 19:06:19 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-03 19:06:19 UTC"},{"id":3676,"user_id":21893,"text":"<p>I did not expect to share full articles of other's work in any presentations or publications.&nbsp; Data from full articles would be included in aggregate form.&nbsp; Does this mean during my Methods or Results section I could not refer to those articles specifically or could I request permission to use?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Can I still add data from full articles into my aggregate? or do I have to change my method?&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37292,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-03 19:48:46 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-03 19:48:46 UTC"},{"id":3677,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Your dissertation itself would be deposited with AU (FGS coordinates that process and AU Library maintains the repository). However, it is good practice to also preserve and store your data (in case someone reading your dissertation contacts you to ask about it). Generally, that's up to the researcher, not the institution to do (although some have policies that state how long you need to keep your data). You may keep copies yourself, but if you want to deposit your data in a repository and share it openly, we can look into options. AU does not currently have a data repository (it's on the list of services I'm hoping we can develop), but there are options nationally (FRDR and DataVerse) as well as some international and generalist repositories. I did a quick search for data repositories specific to Education (using re3data.org), and I don't see any that stand out at first look, but we can take a closer look if that's of interest.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37281,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-05 22:30:46 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-05 22:30:46 UTC"},{"id":3678,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>Lol, On the Hub does provide software for faculty and staff, but the NVivo discount isn't as good. It's more like $730 CDN for NVivo 12. For the newest version, licenses are more like $850 USD for a single academic license directly from NVivo. The upside is that those licenses aren't time bound (student licenses expire after 2 years and have to be repurchased).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37288,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-05 22:41:38 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-05 22:41:38 UTC"},{"id":3679,"user_id":2671,"text":"<p>My initial comment was referring more to if you share data set than how you can include your data in your dissertation (and any other publications). You can use full articles in your data set (e.g., full copy pdfs in NVivo that you then code to themes), and you can refer to them when writing your dissertation or other publications and presentations (as in paraphrasing or quoting), but you couldn't include the entire full text articles in those presentations or publications (as you noted). If you are sharing your data set itself publicly (beyond your supervisory committee), you can't publicly share the full text articles you collected, just lists of them (or links to them as Connie noted), because of copyright.</p>\n<p>Shorter answer: no you don't need to change your method. :)&nbsp; There are just additional considerations/limitations, because of copyright, if you want to make your data set open and accessible to others.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37292,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-05 22:55:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-05 22:55:59 UTC"},{"id":3680,"user_id":464,"text":"<p>hey mindy not sure of this question can you take a loook</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37917,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-07 19:57:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-07 19:57:09 UTC"},{"id":3681,"user_id":22132,"text":"<p>Change if we make this open data</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19531,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-08 13:32:44 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-08 13:32:44 UTC"},{"id":3682,"user_id":22132,"text":"<p>Discuss if we make open science</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19532,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-08 13:33:23 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-08 13:33:23 UTC"},{"id":3683,"user_id":22132,"text":"<p>If open science, we would publish to clinicaltrials.gov and/or osf.io</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":19533,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-08 13:33:57 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-08 13:33:57 UTC"},{"id":3684,"user_id":4506,"text":"<p>Geoff do this section please</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37978,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-08 21:56:44 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-08 21:56:44 UTC"},{"id":3685,"user_id":22117,"text":"<p>I think it would be interesting to ask for the \"data source\": eg human, animal, others? and add a line to indicate whether ethics and/or other certificates were obtained or applied for.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38022,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-11 17:29:03 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-12 15:55:41 UTC"},{"id":3686,"user_id":22117,"text":"<p>include question : is research conducted by and with First Nations, M&eacute;tis and Inuit communities? add space to write contact of First Nations, Metis, or Inuit representative and tick box to recognize Indigenous data sovereignty and include options for renegotiation of the DMP.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This question/requirement is copy/pasted from the CIHR website.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38022,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-11 17:35:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-11 17:43:29 UTC"},{"id":3687,"user_id":22117,"text":"<p>PI conducting human studies are often asked to include something about how they have considered the question of Equity Diversity and Inclusion for recruitment processes and development opportunities. Maybe it would be good to add a field for this specific question?!</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":38022,"archived_by":22117,"created_at":"2022-04-11 17:46:02 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-12 13:56:10 UTC"},{"id":3688,"user_id":22117,"text":"<p>Maybe this question fits better in the next section about Storage/Backup?!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38025,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-11 17:49:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-12 13:56:59 UTC"},{"id":3689,"user_id":22117,"text":"<p>I do not know how to dissociate the organization, naming and tracking of files (the previous question) from the metadata documentation (this question).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38065,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-12 14:34:43 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-12 14:34:43 UTC"},{"id":3690,"user_id":22117,"text":"<p>Here again, this is described in the previous section. File organization, documentation and version control go hand in hand for our research projects&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38067,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-12 14:36:04 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-12 14:36:04 UTC"},{"id":3691,"user_id":22117,"text":"<p>I am not sure if Western has vetted Globus but this is state-of-the-art for the secure transfer of large data files. Maybe a link should be provided to see the lists of software that have been vetted by Western?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38071,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-12 14:53:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-12 15:02:05 UTC"},{"id":3692,"user_id":22117,"text":"<p>I do not understand what preservation-ready means. To the best of my knowledge, this is not applicable to my field</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38088,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-12 15:40:29 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-12 15:40:29 UTC"},{"id":3693,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>Just leaving this here in case its a viable option (but maybe not with interRAI):</p>\n<p>The merged, coded dataset will be uploaded to Zenodo upon publication of the study results. Zenodo accepts all data file formats and metadata records, and have their own version coding procedures that they maintain. More information on their Terms of Use can be found here: https://about.zenodo.org/policies/</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35918,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-18 18:18:38 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-18 18:18:38 UTC"},{"id":3694,"user_id":21207,"text":"<div class=\"display-readonly-textarea-content\">\n<p>Just leaving this here in case its a viable option:</p>\n<p>The merged, coded dataset will be uploaded to Zenodo upon publication of the study results. Zenodo accepts all data file formats and metadata records, and have their own version coding procedures that they maintain. More information on their Terms of Use can be found here: https://about.zenodo.org/policies/</p>\n</div>","archived":0,"answer_id":38381,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-18 18:25:27 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-18 18:25:27 UTC"},{"id":3695,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>If we upload data to Zenodo, then we can use their metadata standard.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38382,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-18 18:25:49 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-18 18:25:49 UTC"},{"id":3696,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>Ask Stephanie about google drive storage space.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38385,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-18 19:18:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-18 19:18:37 UTC"},{"id":3697,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>Note on how to describe the level of identifying information:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Directly identifying information &ndash; the information identifies a specific individual through direct identifiers (e.g., name, social insurance number, personal health number).</li>\n<li>Indirectly identifying information &ndash; the information can reasonably be expected to identify an individual through a combination of indirect identifiers (e.g., date of birth, place of residence or unique personal characteristic).</li>\n<li>Coded information &ndash; direct identifiers are removed from the information and replaced with a code. Depending on access to the code, it may be possible to re-identify specific participants (e.g., the principal investigator retains a list that links the participants&rsquo; code names with their actual names so data can be re-linked if necessary).</li>\n<li>Anonymized information &ndash; the information is irrevocably stripped of direct identifiers, a code is not kept to allow future re-linkage, and risk of re-identification of individuals from remaining indirect identifiers is low or very low.</li>\n<li>Anonymous information &ndash; the information never had identifiers associated with it (e.g.,&nbsp;anonymous surveys) and risk of identification of individuals is low or very low.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Retention for 10 years is standard.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35510,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-19 14:10:41 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-19 14:10:41 UTC"},{"id":3698,"user_id":21207,"text":"<p>When will Tammy download survey data?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":38383,"archived_by":21207,"created_at":"2022-04-21 14:07:02 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-21 14:32:54 UTC"},{"id":3699,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>corriger les fautes de fran&ccedil;ais</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38535,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-22 18:53:03 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-22 18:53:03 UTC"},{"id":3700,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>ok c'Est fait</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38535,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-22 18:53:30 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-22 18:53:30 UTC"},{"id":3701,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>fautes &agrave; corriger</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":38537,"archived_by":21368,"created_at":"2022-04-22 19:17:03 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-22 19:17:18 UTC"},{"id":3702,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>revoir les fautes d'orthographes</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38643,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-26 15:42:09 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-26 15:42:09 UTC"},{"id":3703,"user_id":22022,"text":"<p>\"Donn&eacute;e sensible\" ne fait pas partie du lexique de l'&eacute;thique de la recherche.&nbsp;<br />J'imagine que cela inclut le type de donn&eacute;es &eacute;num&eacute;r&eacute;es (partenariats commerciaux, participants humains, animaux ou produits biologiques dangereux). Je ne voudrais juste pas que cela am&egrave;ne une confusion pour certains chercheurs (qui pourraient dire que quoiqu'il y ait recrutement de participants, les donn&eacute;es collect&eacute;es ne sont pas \"sensibles\" selon leur interpr&eacute;tation).&nbsp;<br />De plus, je pense qu'on pourrait mettre un peu plus d'information pour s'assurer que les projets avec des &ecirc;tres humains ne tombent pas \"sous le radar\".&nbsp;<br />Dans la configuration actuelle du PDG, on demande simplement aux chercheurs de dire ce qu'ils vont faire&nbsp;<em>si&nbsp;</em>il y a de l'&eacute;thique/conformit&eacute;/etc. Mais les chercheurs ne sont pas toujours bien au courant de &ccedil;a.&nbsp;<br /><br />Peut-&ecirc;tre serait-il possible d'ajouter une question ou des cases dans la premi&egrave;re section \"collecte de donn&eacute;es\" qui permettrait de bien identifier les projets qui n&eacute;cessiteront, ou non, un certificat &eacute;thique ? (i.e. recrutement de participants pr&eacute;vus, entrevue avec des professionnels, utilisation secondaire de donn&eacute;es, mat&eacute;riel biologique, etc.). Ou bien tout simplement ajouter une explication plus pr&eacute;cise sur ce qu'on entend par \"projet de recherche avec des participants humains\".<br /><br /></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":37081,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-27 14:49:00 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-27 14:49:00 UTC"},{"id":3704,"user_id":22022,"text":"<p>M&ecirc;me commentaire par rapport &agrave; \"donn&eacute;es sensibles\".&nbsp;<br />De plus, je me questionne sur la pertinence d'indiquer dans le guide :<br /><br />\"La d&eacute;claration de consentement peut indiquer certaines conditions pr&eacute;cisant l'utilisation des donn&eacute;es par d'autres chercheurs. Par exemple, elle peut stipuler que les donn&eacute;es seront uniquement partag&eacute;es &agrave; des fins de recherche sans but lucratif ou que les donn&eacute;es ne seront pas crois&eacute;es avec des donn&eacute;es personnelles provenant d'autres sources.\"<br /><br />Ce n'est pas une pratique courante &agrave; l'&Eacute;TS. Les modalit&eacute;s de l'utilisation secondaires sont standardis&eacute;es pour tous les projets.&nbsp;<br />J'imagine que de telles clauses pourraient &ecirc;tre mises en place dans des cas extr&ecirc;mement pr&eacute;cis, mais je ne pense pas que &ccedil;a soit pertinent de l'indiquer ici.<br /><br />Clause standard sur l'utilisation secondaire des donn&eacute;es :&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Le(la) chercheur(euse) responsable souhaite utiliser vos donn&eacute;es de recherche pour r&eacute;aliser d&rsquo;autres projets de recherche dans le domaine de &lt;&nbsp;Compl&eacute;ter&nbsp;&gt;.</p>\n<p>Ces projets de recherche seront &eacute;valu&eacute;s et approuv&eacute;s par le Comit&eacute; d&rsquo;&eacute;thique de la recherche avant leur r&eacute;alisation. De plus, le Comit&eacute; en assurera le suivi. Vos donn&eacute;es de recherche seront conserv&eacute;es de fa&ccedil;on s&eacute;curitaire sur des serveurs de l&rsquo;&Eacute;cole de technologie sup&eacute;rieure. Afin de pr&eacute;server votre identit&eacute; et la confidentialit&eacute; de vos donn&eacute;es de recherche, vous ne serez identifi&eacute;(e) que par un num&eacute;ro de code.</p>\n<p>Vos donn&eacute;es de recherche seront conserv&eacute;es aussi longtemps qu'elles peuvent avoir une utilit&eacute; pour l&rsquo;avancement des connaissances scientifiques. Lorsqu&rsquo;elles n&rsquo;auront plus d&rsquo;utilit&eacute;, vos donn&eacute;es de recherche seront d&eacute;truites. Par ailleurs, notez qu&rsquo;en tout temps, vous pouvez demander la non-utilisation de vos donn&eacute;es de recherche en vous adressant au(&agrave; la) chercheur(euse) responsable de ce projet de recherche.</p>\n<p>Acceptez-vous que vos donn&eacute;es de recherche soient utilis&eacute;es &agrave; ces conditions?&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ☐&nbsp;&nbsp; Oui&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ☐&nbsp;&nbsp; Non</p>\n<p><br /><br /></p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38652,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-27 15:25:36 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-27 15:25:36 UTC"},{"id":3705,"user_id":22022,"text":"<p>Une autre fa&ccedil;on de permettre la r&eacute;utilisation des donn&eacute;es de recherche est leur mise en banque. Il y a deux banques &agrave; l'&Eacute;TS qui contiennent des donn&eacute;es collect&eacute;es sur des participants humains (CRITIAS et LIO).<br />D'autres banques pourraient &ecirc;tre constitu&eacute;es &agrave; l'avenir.<br />Or, du point de vue du C&Eacute;R de l'&Eacute;TS, on distingue entre <em>utilisation secondaire</em> et&nbsp;<em>mise en banque</em>. Peut-&ecirc;tre que cette nuance a sa place ici ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38652,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-27 15:32:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-27 15:32:31 UTC"},{"id":3706,"user_id":22022,"text":"<p>Les donn&eacute;es brutes sont des donn&eacute;es obtenues directement de l'instrument, de la simulation ou de l'enqu&ecirc;te.</p>\n<p>Les donn&eacute;es trait&eacute;es d&eacute;coulent d'une certaine manipulation des donn&eacute;es brutes afin d'&eacute;liminer les erreurs ou les valeurs aberrantes, de pr&eacute;parer les donn&eacute;es en vue de l'analyse, d'obtenir de nouvelles variables ou <strong>d'anonymiser les participants humains.<br /><br />Commentaire :&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>Puisque l'&eacute;thique de la recherche ne fait pas la diff&eacute;rence entre donn&eacute;e brute et donn&eacute;e trait&eacute;e, je sugg&egrave;re de retirer la section en gras</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38653,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-27 15:40:10 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-27 15:40:10 UTC"},{"id":3707,"user_id":22022,"text":"<p>Si vous pr&eacute;voyez une r&eacute;utilisation secondaire de vos donn&eacute;es, assurez-vous de consulter le&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:CER@etsmtl.ca\">comit&eacute; d'&eacute;thique de la recherche</a>&nbsp;<strong>avant le d&eacute;but du projet.<br /><br /></strong>Je ne suis pas s&ucirc;re de comprendre la pertinence de cette phrase.<br />S'ils pr&eacute;voient une utilisation secondaire des donn&eacute;es dans un proje<em>t n'impliquant pas</em> de donn&eacute;es collect&eacute;es sur les humains, alors pas besoin de contacter le C&Eacute;R.<br /><br />Si le projet implique des participants humains, alors ils devront contacter le C&Eacute;R avant le d&eacute;but du projet, qu'ils pr&eacute;voient une utilisation secondaire ou non.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38653,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-04-27 16:02:50 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-27 16:02:50 UTC"},{"id":3708,"user_id":21741,"text":"<p>need to check these numbers</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39023,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-03 17:10:47 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-03 17:10:47 UTC"},{"id":3709,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>James: For transferring of the survey tables, rather than using email I suggest instead creating a google folder where IST can directly upload the raw survey data. Can discuss.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":27974,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 13:54:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 13:54:16 UTC"},{"id":3710,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>James: We should also describe how long a copy of the data will remain in Qualtrics - can discuss.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38336,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 13:58:47 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 13:58:47 UTC"},{"id":3711,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>James: UofA's Google drive is great for storing and providing access to data, but &nbsp;by and large the data will not actually be worked on within Google drive. Some additional description here regarding how data will be worked with, and this may also include ensuring that analytic files, etc are also uploaded back into the project space on Google drive. Can discuss.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38337,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 14:01:46 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 14:01:46 UTC"},{"id":3712,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>James: When we meet we can discuss your needs, Dataverse, etc, and help to determine what will work best for you.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38340,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 14:04:38 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 14:04:38 UTC"},{"id":3713,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>James: Again, can discuss your needs and what will work best for you.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38342,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 14:05:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 14:05:52 UTC"},{"id":3714,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>James: Can discuss.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38343,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 14:06:18 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 14:06:18 UTC"},{"id":3715,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>James: We can discuss and likely firm this up a bit.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":38344,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 14:06:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 14:06:52 UTC"},{"id":3716,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>r&eacute;viser la r&eacute;ponse</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39034,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 14:23:58 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 14:23:58 UTC"},{"id":3717,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>r&eacute;viser la r&eacute;ponse</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39090,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-04 17:20:43 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 17:20:43 UTC"},{"id":3718,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>texte &agrave; revoir</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39118,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-05 12:54:44 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-05 12:54:44 UTC"},{"id":3719,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>texte &agrave; revoir</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39118,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-05 12:54:44 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-05 12:54:44 UTC"},{"id":3720,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>revoir la r&eacute;ponse</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39119,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-05 15:12:04 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-05 15:12:04 UTC"},{"id":3721,"user_id":21368,"text":"<p>revoir la r&eacute;ponse</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39124,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-05 16:22:54 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-05 16:22:54 UTC"},{"id":3722,"user_id":21643,"text":"<p>Is that all the text you want to add?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39125,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-05 16:42:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-05 16:42:24 UTC"},{"id":3723,"user_id":16960,"text":"<p>I will add real info!</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39125,"archived_by":16960,"created_at":"2022-05-05 16:42:51 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-05 16:43:57 UTC"},{"id":3724,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>For exemplar purposes, I think you will want to share some more information about documentation. The things that Heather suggested are great ideas. Things like standard operating procedures can also serve as documentation. Basically, you want to indicate how the team will know what to do with the data throughout the project (and beyond, if applicable).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35472,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 15:52:11 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-06 15:52:11 UTC"},{"id":3725,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>Agreed with Heather; you do want to have more detail on the long-term storage of the MRI data. External hard drives are good, and you could put them in a budget, but then you'll probably also need to plan for how you'll make sure the images stay available over the long term (because hard drives and data do degrade). Are there any repositories you know of in your discipline that take MRI data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35475,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 16:02:02 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-06 16:02:02 UTC"},{"id":3726,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>You could also talk with the CSM Legal folks, who might be able to set up a data sharing agreement that you could have as a template.<br /><br />Also, I think you want to clarify that the data will be made available on request only, rather than restricted access, if you're not planning to put it into a repository.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35476,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 16:06:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-06 16:06:33 UTC"},{"id":3727,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>When you say that the manager of the CIPAC will be provide support for data storage resources, does that include things like regular backups? If not, who's responsible for that?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35477,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 16:08:12 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-06 16:08:12 UTC"},{"id":3728,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>Also, if there are personnel costs associated with the roles involved, you can indicate those here.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35478,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 16:08:41 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-06 16:08:41 UTC"},{"id":3729,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>For exemplar purposes, you might need to explain what level 4 storage is (e.g., make reference to the policy that sets this out, explain who hosts level 4 storage).</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":35480,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 16:12:01 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-06 16:12:01 UTC"},{"id":3730,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>Est-ce qu'on fera des enregistrements audio et transcriptions&nbsp; des entretiens t&eacute;l&eacute;phoniques ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39159,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 19:57:27 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-11 15:11:18 UTC"},{"id":3731,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>Compl&eacute;ter au besoin pour les donn&eacute;es audio/transcription.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39160,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 20:02:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-06 20:02:24 UTC"},{"id":3732,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>Si on a des enregistrements et des transcriptions : les mettre dans des r&eacute;pertoires distincts.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39161,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-06 20:14:55 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-11 15:10:56 UTC"},{"id":3733,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>Voir &eacute;ventuellement pour les transcriptions si on fait des entrevues.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39227,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-09 17:43:42 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-09 17:43:42 UTC"},{"id":3734,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>&agrave; revoir/compl&eacute;ter si on publie des transcription d'entrevues</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39233,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-09 18:14:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-09 18:14:24 UTC"},{"id":3735,"user_id":5770,"text":"<p>On dit \"En r&eacute;pondant &agrave; ce sondage, vous acceptez que les r&eacute;sultats agr&eacute;g&eacute;s soient rendus disponibles &agrave; tous publiquement\" pas explicitement qu'on permet la r&eacute;utilisation...??</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39234,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-09 18:23:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-09 18:23:24 UTC"},{"id":3736,"user_id":20615,"text":"<p>Je pense que non, les notes suffiront... particuli&egrave;rement si on participe les 3 aux entrevues.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39159,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-10 13:01:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-10 13:01:52 UTC"},{"id":3737,"user_id":20615,"text":"<p>Et un dictionnaire de donn&eacute;es?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39162,"archived_by":20615,"created_at":"2022-05-10 13:05:39 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-10 13:16:23 UTC"},{"id":3738,"user_id":20615,"text":"<p>C'est implicite en effet... Mais on parle ici de la r&eacute;utilisation des donn&eacute;es sensibles seulement. Si on anonymise nos \"donn&eacute;es sensibles\" avant de les partager, la question ne nous concerne plus.&nbsp;</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39234,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-10 13:23:05 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-10 13:23:05 UTC"},{"id":3739,"user_id":2916,"text":"<p>I'm not sure other types - can you populate?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39261,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-10 15:39:15 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-10 15:39:15 UTC"},{"id":3740,"user_id":3619,"text":"<p>Details in this box might change if we gather client characteristics data in aggregate from CMHA Champlain East.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39153,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-11 23:20:42 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-11 23:20:42 UTC"},{"id":3741,"user_id":3619,"text":"<p>Who will be responsible for creating and maintaining the README file?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39166,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-11 23:23:34 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-11 23:23:34 UTC"},{"id":3742,"user_id":3619,"text":"<p>Who will perform accuracy checks and how often?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39168,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-11 23:24:19 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-11 23:24:19 UTC"},{"id":3743,"user_id":3619,"text":"<p>Who will conduct the accuracy/quality assurance check, and on what schedule?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39157,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-11 23:34:01 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-11 23:34:01 UTC"},{"id":3744,"user_id":3619,"text":"<p>Need a bit of a work plan to be sure someone is personally responsible for making sure that the data management activities are kept up to date so that if someone suddenly leaves the project, a smooth transfer of responsibility can occur.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39174,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-11 23:42:08 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-11 23:42:08 UTC"},{"id":3745,"user_id":22304,"text":"<p>fill in these details</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39367,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-12 13:02:59 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-12 13:02:59 UTC"},{"id":3746,"user_id":22304,"text":"<p>come back to this</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39397,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-12 13:49:50 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-12 13:49:50 UTC"},{"id":3747,"user_id":20604,"text":"<p>TEST</p>\n<p>Les co&ucirc;ts associ&eacute;s au stockage devraient &ecirc;tre indiqu&eacute;s dans la premi&egrave;re section.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39443,"archived_by":20604,"created_at":"2022-05-12 20:07:55 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-18 17:00:58 UTC"},{"id":3748,"user_id":5257,"text":"<p>Note: We should contact the RDM &amp; metadata team at UofA Library to help us with our file naming conventions and metadata needs!</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":10560,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-13 14:46:23 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-13 14:46:23 UTC"},{"id":3749,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>I'm not sure what's meant by 5xx years here, or how they'll be available - who will be hosting the external storage system?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36137,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-13 19:59:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-13 19:59:16 UTC"},{"id":3750,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>It seems like \"(Check creative commons licenses)\" is something you wanted to expand on - have you gotten any futher information or made any further decisions about what you'll be doing?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36141,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-13 20:01:15 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-13 20:01:15 UTC"},{"id":3751,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>I'm not quite sure what's meant by \"Organization of data analysis or programming challenges\" here. How will that help the research community learn about the existence of your data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36142,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-13 20:06:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-13 20:06:26 UTC"},{"id":3752,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>Something to consider here: what will happen in terms of data sharing if the PI leaves the project (goes elsewhere, retires, something else)?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36143,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-13 20:07:43 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-13 20:07:43 UTC"},{"id":3753,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>It's usually not a good idea to say \"N/A\" without further explanation - why is it not applicable to your project?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36146,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-13 20:08:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-13 20:08:37 UTC"},{"id":3754,"user_id":21601,"text":"<p>Can you expand on this? Is it not currently implemented because it's not needed, or is it something that you're planning to implement in the future?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":36144,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-13 20:11:23 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-13 20:11:23 UTC"},{"id":3755,"user_id":22272,"text":"<p>project supervisor</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39526,"archived_by":22272,"created_at":"2022-05-16 18:24:42 UTC","updated_at":"2022-06-01 20:51:15 UTC"},{"id":3756,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>All: I added Sarah here as a starting point. Please feel free to change as needed.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39529,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-16 19:27:44 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-16 19:27:44 UTC"},{"id":3757,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>Need to estimate capacity and number of hard drive needed.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39527,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-16 19:34:02 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-16 19:34:02 UTC"},{"id":3758,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>Need to estimate budget needed</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39527,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-16 19:37:08 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-16 19:37:08 UTC"},{"id":3759,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>I added split-beam echosounder data. Are there any other echosounder data that you will collect?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39530,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-16 19:40:33 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-16 19:40:33 UTC"},{"id":3760,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>I don't know the data format for the echosounders.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39531,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-16 19:47:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-16 19:47:26 UTC"},{"id":3761,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>A template ReadMe.txt file should probably be created and modified for each deployment to help with the consistency of information being reported.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39559,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-17 19:24:55 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-17 19:24:55 UTC"},{"id":3762,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>Will there be any secondary data collection ?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39575,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-17 22:16:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-17 22:16:31 UTC"},{"id":3763,"user_id":21499,"text":"<p>ceci est un test</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39604,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-18 16:00:39 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-18 16:00:39 UTC"},{"id":3764,"user_id":21499,"text":"<p>autre test</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39604,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-18 16:01:16 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-18 16:01:16 UTC"},{"id":3765,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>Is it actually appropriate (relevant?) to upload metadata to the Fisheries and Oceans Canada Library ? Have you ever done it?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39694,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-18 20:31:08 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-18 20:31:08 UTC"},{"id":3766,"user_id":22323,"text":"<p>See other CC licenses here:</p>\n<p>https://creativecommons.org/licenses/#:~:text=Attribution,most%20accommodating%20of%20licenses%20offered.</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39697,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-18 20:38:38 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-18 20:38:38 UTC"},{"id":3767,"user_id":12249,"text":"<p>Y a-t-il des &eacute;l&eacute;ments &agrave; inscrire concernant la cr&eacute;ation de donn&eacute;es? Quel type de donn&eacute;es aurez-vous suite &agrave; l'analyse des donn&eacute;es brutes?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39713,"archived_by":12249,"created_at":"2022-05-19 14:20:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-31 13:10:09 UTC"},{"id":3768,"user_id":12249,"text":"<p>Y a-t-il des &eacute;l&eacute;ments &agrave; inscrire concernant la cr&eacute;ation, le couplage, l'acquisition ou la consignation des donn&eacute;es?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39713,"archived_by":12249,"created_at":"2022-05-19 14:20:53 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-19 14:21:01 UTC"},{"id":3769,"user_id":12249,"text":"<p>Je comprends qu&rsquo;il s&rsquo;agit du stockage interne des donn&eacute;es. Elles ne sont alors accessibles qu&rsquo;aux personnes qui participent au projet.</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39715,"archived_by":12249,"created_at":"2022-05-19 14:22:17 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-31 13:12:51 UTC"},{"id":3770,"user_id":12249,"text":"<p>Qu&rsquo;est-ce qu&rsquo;on devrait inscrire ici?</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39719,"archived_by":12249,"created_at":"2022-05-19 14:22:50 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-31 13:14:07 UTC"},{"id":3771,"user_id":12249,"text":"<p>Est-ce correct? Ne pas oublier que c&rsquo;est un mod&egrave;le et qu&rsquo;il peut diff&eacute;rer de la r&eacute;alit&eacute;&hellip;</p>","archived":1,"answer_id":39721,"archived_by":12249,"created_at":"2022-05-19 14:23:20 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-31 13:15:07 UTC"},{"id":3772,"user_id":22316,"text":"<p>Can't find a suitable one on re3</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39880,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-20 00:28:22 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-20 00:28:22 UTC"},{"id":3773,"user_id":22316,"text":"<p>Not sure here, obviously no on the raw data for CA, but for the rest of it?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39882,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-20 00:28:38 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-20 00:28:38 UTC"},{"id":3774,"user_id":22316,"text":"<p>Is this me?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39885,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-20 00:28:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-20 00:28:52 UTC"},{"id":3775,"user_id":22325,"text":"<p>Mariam, how much storage space do you estimate I will need for my data?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39909,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-20 22:06:53 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-20 22:06:53 UTC"},{"id":3776,"user_id":22325,"text":"<p>Mariam, is this an appropriate answer or should it be analyzed or final data instead?</p>","archived":0,"answer_id":39913,"archived_by":null,"created_at":"2022-05-20 22:14:17 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-20 22:14:17 UTC"},{"id":3777,"user_id":2